:lestrade a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Detective ;
    ex:lastName "Lestrade" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Lestrade" ;
    ex:description "Lestrade is a Scotland Yard detective. Little, sallow, rat-faced, dark-eyed fellow. Lean and ferret-like. Beady eyes. Visits Holmes three or four times a week. Investigates Stangerson's murder at Halliday's Private Hotel. Rival of Gregson. First to discover the RACHE inscription at the Lauriston Gardens crime scene. Arrived in Devonshire by express train with an unsigned warrant for Stapleton's arrest. Participated in the ambush at Merripit House. Left in possession of the house after the events. Described as a small, wiry bulldog of a man. Had learned to respect Holmes's methods since their earlier work together. Investigating the disappearance of Lady St. Simon. Attired in a pea-jacket and cravat giving him a nautical appearance. Had been dragging the Serpentine searching for the body. Found wedding dress, white satin shoes, bride's wreath and veil, and wedding ring floating near the margin (found by a park-keeper). Discovered a note signed 'F.H.M.' in the dress pocket but failed to notice the hotel bill on the reverse side. Believed Flora Millar had decoyed the bride." ;
    ex:occupation "Police Detective" ;
    ex:employedBy :metropolitanPolice ;
    ex:investigates :baskervilleInvestigation ;
    ex:investigates :brixtonRoadInvestigation ;
    ex:investigates :nobleBachelorInvestigation ;
    ex:investigates :norwoodBuilderCase ;
    ex:investigatesCase :boscombeValleyInvestigation ;
    ex:knows :aliceTurner ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
