:221bLandlady a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Landlady ;
    ex:prefLabel "Landlady of 221B Baker Street" ;
    ex:description "The unnamed landlady of 221B Baker Street. She became accustomed to Watson's late habits and wanted Watson to put down her sick terrier. Her maid or servant answers the door. She is not named in A Study in Scarlet." ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :studyInScarletDoc .

:abbeyGrangeLodgeKeeper a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Abbey Grange Lodge-Keeper" ;
    ex:description """An old lodge-keeper at Abbey Grange whose haggard face bore the reflection of the disaster. Opened the park gate for Holmes and Watson. Name not given in the text.""" ;
    ex:occupation "Lodge-keeper" ;
    ex:employedBy :eustaceBrackenstall ;
    ex:worksAt :abbeyGrange ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :abbeyGrangeDoc .

:abernettyFamily a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Abernetty Family" ;
    ex:description "A family referenced by Holmes in connection with a 'dreadful business' that was first brought to his notice by the depth which the parsley had sunk into the butter upon a hot day. The case is only mentioned in passing as an example of cases with unpromising beginnings." ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :sixNapoleonsDoc .

:abrahamLincoln a ex:RealPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Abraham" ;
    ex:lastName "Lincoln" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Abraham Lincoln" ;
    ex:description "Abraham Lincoln, the historical American president, is referenced as a physical comparison for Neil Gibson's appearance. Watson describes Gibson as 'An Abraham Lincoln keyed to base uses instead of high ones.'" ;
    ex:occupation "president of the United States" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :thorBridgeDoc .

:adairFamilyServant a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Servant ;
    ex:prefLabel "Adair family servant" ;
    ex:description "Unnamed female servant at 427 Park Lane. Deposed at the inquest that she heard Ronald Adair enter the front room on the second floor. Had lit a fire there and opened the window because it smoked. Name not given in the text." ;
    ex:employedBy :earlOfMaynooth ;
    ex:locatedIn :427ParkLane ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :emptyHouseDoc .

:adamsManorHouse a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:prefLabel "Adams Manor House Criminal" ;
    ex:description "An unnamed criminal associated with Adams Manor House. Referenced in connection with a case handled by Holmes. Name is not given in the text." ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :greekInterpreterDoc .

:adelbertGruner a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "Adelbert" ;
    ex:lastName "Gruner" ;
    ex:title "Baron" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Baron Adelbert Gruner" ;
    skos:altLabel "Baron Gruner" ;
    skos:altLabel "Adelbert Gruner" ;
    ex:description """Baron Adelbert Gruner is an Austrian described by Holmes as a murderer. He is extraordinarily handsome, of middle size, built upon graceful and active lines. His face is swarthy, almost Oriental, with large dark languorous eyes, raven black hair and moustache (the latter short, pointed, and carefully waxed with little waxed tips under his nose). His features are regular and pleasing save for his straight thin-lipped mouth, described as a murderer's mouth. His voice is engaging, his manners perfect, and he appears about thirty though he is actually forty-two. He killed his wife in a so-called accident at the Splugen Pass and was tried at Prague, escaping conviction on a technical legal point and the suspicious death of a witness. He came to England and lives at Vernon Lodge near Kingston, a large house he obtained through shady speculations. He is a horse fancier who briefly played polo at Hurlingham, a recognized authority on Chinese pottery who has written a book on the subject, and a collector of fine ceramics. He keeps a brown leather book with lock and gold arms cataloguing the women he has ruined with photographs, names, and details. He is engaged to Violet de Merville and has won her complete devotion. He arranged the beating of Holmes in Regent Street and referenced the crippling of Le Brun. He is disfigured by vitriol thrown by Kitty Winter during Holmes's burglary of Vernon Lodge. The marriage to Violet de Merville is subsequently cancelled.""" ;
    ex:nationality "Austrian" ;
    ex:age 42 ;
    ex:occupation "collector, authority on Chinese pottery" ;
    ex:livesAt :vernonLodge ;
    ex:engagedTo :violetDeMerville ;
    ex:perpetratorOf :murderBaronessGruner ;
    ex:victimOf :vitriolAttackOnGruner ;
    ex:owns :grunerLoveDiary ;
    ex:owns :grunerPotteryBook ;
    ex:owns :tangVase ;
    ex:knows :violetDeMerville ;
    ex:knows :kittyWinter ;
    ex:knows :generalDeMerville ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:formerPartnerOf :kittyWinter ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :illustriousClientDoc .

:admiralGreen a ex:RealPerson, ex:Admiral ;
    ex:prefLabel "Admiral Green" ;
    ex:lastName "Green" ;
    ex:description "Admiral Green is the famous admiral who commanded the Sea of Azof fleet during the Crimean War. He is the father of the Hon. Philip Green. He is referenced as a real historical figure." ;
    ex:occupation "admiral" ;
    ex:parentOf :philipGreen ;
    ex:commandedFleetAt :seaOfAzov ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :disappearanceLadyFrancesCarfaxDoc .

:adolphMayer a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Spy ;
    ex:firstName "Adolph" ;
    ex:lastName "Mayer" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Adolph Mayer" ;
    ex:description "Foreign spy or international agent. Resides at 13 Great George Street, Westminster. Listed by Mycroft Holmes among few agents who would handle a big affair." ;
    ex:livesAt :13GreatGeorgeStreet ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :brucePartingtonPlansDoc .

:admiralSinclair a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:lastName "Sinclair" ;
    ex:title "Admiral" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Admiral Sinclair" ;
    ex:description "Admiral who lives at Barclay Square, London. Sir James Walter visited him on Monday evening, providing Sir James's alibi. Testified to Sir James's arrival in London." ;
    ex:livesAt :barclaySquare ;
    ex:knows :sirJamesWalter ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :brucePartingtonPlansDoc .

:agatha a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Agatha" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Agatha" ;
    ex:description "Milverton's housemaid at Appledore Towers. Holmes, disguised as Escott the plumber, becomes engaged to her to gather information about the house layout, Milverton's habits, and the location of the safe. She locks up the guard dog on the evenings Holmes visits. Holmes mentions she has a 'hated rival' who will replace him once his back is turned." ;
    ex:occupation "housemaid" ;
    ex:worksAt :appledoreTowers ;
    ex:employedBy :charlesAugustusMilverton ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :milvertonDoc .

:aldrige a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Aldrige" ;
    ex:description "Mentioned by Lestrade as comparison for Browner's appearance. Helped in 'the bogus laundry affair'. Not further described." ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :cardboardBoxDoc .

:alecFairbairn a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Alec" ;
    ex:lastName "Fairbairn" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Alec Fairbairn" ;
    skos:altLabel "Fairbairn" ;
    ex:description "Sailor, dashing and swaggering. Smart and curled. Had seen half the world. Wonderful polite ways. Came to visit Sarah first, then became friends with all. Had affair with Mary Browner. Murdered by Jim Browner at sea near New Brighton - head crushed with oak stick. One of the victims whose ear was sent." ;
    ex:gender "male" ;
    ex:occupation "sailor" ;
    ex:knows :sarahCushing ;
    ex:knows :jimBrowner ;
    ex:knows :maryBrowner ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :cardboardBoxDoc .

:alexanderHamiltonGarrideb a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Alexander Hamilton" ;
    ex:lastName "Garrideb" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Alexander Hamilton Garrideb" ;
    ex:description "A wealthy deceased American who made his money in real estate and afterwards in the wheat pit at Chicago. He purchased a vast tract of land along the Arkansas River, west of Fort Dodge, Kansas, encompassing grazing-land, lumber-land, arable-land, and mineralized-land. He had no known kith or kin and took pride in the unusual name Garrideb. He left a will dividing his property into three parts, each worth five million dollars, to be shared among three adult men named Garrideb. He died within a year of making this arrangement. According to the story told by Killer Evans, though the entire Garrideb inheritance scheme may have been fabricated." ;
    ex:occupation "real estate magnate and wheat trader" ;
    ex:livesAt :kansas ;
    ex:deceased "true" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :threeGarridebsDoc .

:alexis a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Alexis" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Alexis" ;
    ex:description "Noble, unselfish, loving friend of Anna. Fellow member of the Nihilist Brotherhood but hated violence and wrote letters dissuading the group from violent action. These letters would have saved him from conviction. Sergius tried to swear away his life but failed to get execution; Alexis was sent as a convict to a salt mine in Siberia where he works and lives like a slave. Anna's mission was to recover the diary and letters to send to the Russian Government to procure his release." ;
    ex:knows :annaCoram ;
    ex:memberOf :nihilistBrotherhood ;
    ex:participantIn :nihilistBetrayal ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :goldenPinceNezDoc .

:algar a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Detective ;
    ex:prefLabel "Algar" ;
    ex:description "Holmes's friend in the Liverpool police force. Holmes sent telegram asking him to check on Mrs. Browner and whether Browner departed on May Day." ;
    ex:occupation "Police Detective" ;
    ex:employedBy :liverpoolPolice ;
    ex:friendOf :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :cardboardBoxDoc .

:aliceMorphy a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Alice" ;
    ex:lastName "Morphy" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Alice Morphy" ;
    ex:description "Alice Morphy is the daughter of Professor Morphy, colleague of Professor Presbury at Camford. She is described as a very perfect girl both in mind and body. She is young and became engaged to the sixty-one-year-old Professor Presbury, though several other candidates closer to her age also sought her hand. She seemed to like the professor despite his eccentricities, with only his age standing in the way." ;
    ex:childOf :professorMorphy ;
    ex:fianceeOf :professorPresbury ;
    ex:knows :professorPresbury ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :creepingManDoc .

:aliceRucastle a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Alice" ;
    ex:lastName "Rucastle" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Alice Rucastle" ;
    skos:altLabel "Miss Rucastle", "Miss Alice" ;
    ex:description """Alice Rucastle is the daughter of Jephro Rucastle by his first wife. She is about twenty years old or more. She had rights of her own by will, but her father wanted her to sign a paper giving him control of her money. When she refused, he kept worrying her until she got brain-fever, and for six weeks was at death's door. Her beautiful hair was cut off during the illness. Her father told the governess Violet Hunter that Alice had gone to Philadelphia, but in reality she was imprisoned in a locked wing of the Copper Beeches with a barricaded door. Mr. Fowler, her suitor, remained faithful throughout. She escaped through the skylight with Fowler's help and the Tollers' assistance, and married Fowler by special license in Southampton the day after their flight.""" ;
    ex:childOf :jephroRucastle ;
    ex:engagedTo :mrFowler ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :mrFowler ;
    ex:knows :mrFowler, :jephroRucastle, :mrsRucastle, :mrsTollerCB ;
    ex:hasParticipatedIn :imprisonmentOfAliceRucastle, :escapeOfAliceRucastle, :marriageOfFowlerAndAlice ;
    ex:livesAt :copperBeeches ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :copperBeechesDoc .

:aloysiusGarcia a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Aloysius" ;
    ex:lastName "Garcia" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Aloysius Garcia" ;
    skos:altLabel "Garcia" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Garcia" ;
    ex:description "A young man of Spanish descent who rented Wisteria Lodge between Esher and Oxshott. Claimed to be connected with the Spanish embassy, though he was unknown there. Good-looking, pleasing manners, spoke perfect English. Son of the former highest dignitary in San Pedro. Led a plot to assassinate Don Murillo (the Tiger of San Pedro) as revenge. Invited Scott Eccles to stay as an unwitting alibi. Murdered on Oxshott Common by Murillo, his head smashed with a sandbag. Had two companions of humble station: his servant Jose and the mulatto cook." ;
    ex:livesAt :wisteriaLodge ;
    ex:nationality "San Pedran" ;
    ex:knows :johnScottEccles ;
    ex:knows :missBurnet ;
    ex:knows :jose ;
    ex:knows :wisteriaLodgeCook ;
    ex:knows :donMurillo ;
    ex:memberOf :sanPedroRevengeSociety ;
    ex:killedBy :donMurillo ;
    ex:childOf :garciaSenior ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :wisteriaLodgeDoc .

:andersonFulworth a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:PoliceOfficer ;
    ex:lastName "Anderson" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Anderson (Fulworth Constable)" ;
    skos:altLabel "Anderson" ;
    ex:description "Anderson is the village constable at Fulworth. A big man with a ginger moustache, he is of the slow, solid Sussex breed that covers much good sense under a heavy silent exterior. He is the first officer on the scene of McPherson's death and seeks Holmes's advice, worried about repercussions from his superiors at Lewes." ;
    ex:occupation "Village constable" ;
    ex:hasParticipatedIn :mcPhersonDeathInvestigation ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes, :haroldStackhurst, :ianMurdoch ;
    ex:livesAt :fulworth ;
    ex:memberOf :sussexConstabulary ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :lionsManeDoc .

:andersonSoldier a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Soldier, ex:Victim ;
    ex:lastName "Anderson" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Anderson" ;
    ex:description "Anderson was a soldier who served with Godfrey Emsworth and Baldy Simpson during the Boer War. The three became separated from their unit at the Battle of Buffelsspruit outside Pretoria. Anderson and Simpson were both killed by the Boers during this engagement." ;
    ex:knows :godfreyEmsworth ;
    ex:knows :baldySimpson ;
    ex:killedAt :battleOfBuffelsspruit ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :blanchedSoldierDoc .

:annaCoram a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "Anna" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Anna" ;
    skos:altLabel "Anna Coram" ;
    ex:description "Russian woman, wife of Sergius (Professor Coram). Married at twenty when he was fifty. Former Nihilist revolutionary. Betrayed by her husband to the police; sentenced to exile in Siberia but not for life. After release, spent months searching for her husband in England to recover diary and letters that could free her friend Alexis from a Siberian salt mine. Hired agent from private detective firm as the second secretary to infiltrate Coram's household. Entered Yoxley Old Place to steal papers from locked bureau, was seized by Willoughby Smith, and accidentally killed him with a sealing-wax knife. Lost her golden pince-nez in the struggle. Extremely short-sighted, took wrong corridor and ended up in Professor's bedroom. Hidden by Coram behind a secret bookcase for over a day. Described as having thick nose, close-set eyes, puckered forehead, rounded shoulders, long obstinate chin—not handsome but with noble bearing. Took poison before emerging from hiding, died despite Holmes wresting phial from her. Gave packet of diary and letters to be delivered to Russian Embassy to free Alexis." ;
    ex:nationality "Russian" ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :professorCoram ;
    ex:knows :alexis ;
    ex:memberOf :nihilistBrotherhood ;
    ex:participantIn :murderOfWilloughbySmith ;
    ex:participantIn :goldenPinceNezInvestigation ;
    ex:participantIn :nihilistBetrayal ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :goldenPinceNezDoc .

:annieFraser a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:prefLabel "Annie Fraser" ;
    ex:firstName "Annie" ;
    ex:lastName "Fraser" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mrs. Shlessinger" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mrs. Peters" ;
    skos:altLabel "Fraser" ;
    ex:description "Annie Fraser is an Englishwoman and the accomplice and so-called wife of Holy Peters (Henry Peters). She poses as Mrs. Shlessinger when Peters adopts his missionary disguise. She is described as a tall, pale woman with ferret eyes. She is a worthy helpmate to Peters in his scheme of beguiling lonely ladies. She pawned one of Lady Frances's Spanish pendants at Bovington's and was followed by Philip Green to 36 Poultney Square, Brixton." ;
    ex:nationality "English" ;
    ex:hasPhysicalFeature "tall, pale, ferret eyes" ;
    ex:knows :henryPeters, :ladyFrancesCarfax, :roseSpender ;
    ex:livesAt :36PoultneySq ;
    ex:partnerOf :henryPeters ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :disappearanceLadyFrancesCarfaxDoc .

:annieMorrison a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Annie" ;
    ex:lastName "Morrison" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Annie Morrison" ;
    ex:description "A person mentioned in the murder note sent to William Kirwan. The note states that meeting at the east gate 'may be of the greatest service to you and also to Annie Morrison.' Her relationship to Alec Cunningham, William Kirwan, and the events is not revealed in the text. Holmes notes that 'we do not yet know what the relations may have been between Alec Cunningham, William Kirwan, and Annie Morrison.'" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :reigateSquiresDoc .

:anthonyServant a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Servant ;
    ex:firstName "Anthony" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Anthony" ;
    skos:altLabel "Antonio" ;
    skos:altLabel "the old manservant" ;
    ex:description "Old manservant at Merripit House, the Stapletons' residence on Dartmoor. Described as a strange, wizened, rusty-coated old man. His real name was likely Antonio, suggesting Spanish or Spanish-American origins (Anthony being uncommon in England while Antonio is common in Spanish countries). Served the Stapletons for several years, dating back to their schoolmastering days as the Vandeleurs, so he was aware that his master and mistress were husband and wife. He cared for the hound in the Grimpen Mire during Stapleton's absence in London. After the case concluded, he disappeared and escaped from the country." ;
    ex:employedBy :jackStapleton ;
    ex:worksAt :merripitHouse ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :houndOfTheBaskervillesDoc .

:appledoreUnderGardener a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Appledore Under-Gardener" ;
    ex:description "An unnamed under-gardener at Appledore Towers who nearly catches Watson during the escape from the burglary. He grabs Watson's ankle as Watson scales the garden wall, but Watson kicks free." ;
    ex:occupation "under-gardener" ;
    ex:worksAt :appledoreTowers ;
    ex:employedBy :charlesAugustusMilverton ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :milvertonDoc .

:annieHarrison a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Annie" ;
    ex:lastName "Harrison" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Annie Harrison" ;
    skos:altLabel "Annie" ;
    skos:altLabel "Miss Harrison" ;
    ex:description "Percy Phelps's fiancée and sister of Joseph Harrison. A striking-looking woman, a little short and thick for symmetry, but with a beautiful olive complexion, large dark Italian eyes, and a wealth of deep black hair. Daughter of an iron-master somewhere up Northumberland way. Came to Woking with her brother as escort when Phelps got engaged to her. Nursed Phelps devotedly for nine weeks during his brain-fever. Holmes described her as a girl of strong character and a good sort. On Holmes's instructions she locked herself in Phelps's sickroom all day and locked the door from outside at night, enabling Holmes to catch the thief." ;
    ex:childOf :harrisonFather ;
    ex:engagedTo :percyPhelps ;
    ex:siblingOf :josephHarrison ;
    ex:knows :percyPhelps ;
    ex:knows :josephHarrison ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:knows :johnWatson ;
    ex:livesAt :briarbrae ;
    ex:nurses :percyPhelps ;
    ex:siblingOf :josephHarrison ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :navalTreatyDoc .

:archieStamford a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Forger, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "Archie" ;
    ex:lastName "Stamford" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Archie Stamford" ;
    ex:description "A forger caught by Holmes and Watson near Farnham, mentioned in passing." ;
    ex:occupation "forger" ;
    ex:gender "male" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
