:alecCunningham a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "Alec" ;
    ex:lastName "Cunningham" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Alec Cunningham" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Alec" ;
    skos:altLabel "young Alec" ;
    skos:altLabel "young Mr. Cunningham" ;
    skos:altLabel "Master Alec" ;
    ex:description "Son of old Mr. Cunningham, described as a dashing young fellow with a bright, smiling expression and showy dress. He was the ringleader of the plot to murder William Kirwan, their coachman who was blackmailing them. He wrote the stronger hand in the murder note (wrote his words first, leaving blanks). During Holmes's investigation, he attacked Holmes by clutching his throat with both hands and tried to grab a revolver during the arrest. Described as a 'perfect demon' and a dangerous man to play games with. Holmes noted the murder scheme showed 'positive genius' and traced the influence of young Alec." ;
    ex:childOf :oldCunningham ;
    ex:livesAt :cunninghamHouse ;
    ex:participantIn :actonBurglary, :williamKirwanMurder, :attackOnHolmes, :cunninghamArrest ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :reigateSquiresDoc .

:arthurCadoganWest a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Arthur" ;
    ex:lastName "Cadogan West" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Arthur Cadogan West" ;
    skos:altLabel "Cadogan West" ;
    skos:altLabel "Cadogen West" ;
    skos:altLabel "West" ;
    skos:altLabel "young Cadogan West" ;
    ex:description "A twenty-seven-year-old unmarried clerk at Woolwich Arsenal who had been ten years in the service. Reputation for being hot-headed and imperious but a straight, honest man. Engaged to Violet Westbury with wedding planned for New Year. Had saved a few hundred pounds. His duties brought him into daily personal contact with the Bruce-Partington plans. On Monday evening in November 1895, left his fiancee abruptly in the fog about 7:30pm, having spotted Colonel Valentine Walter heading toward the Arsenal office. Took the 8:15 train from Woolwich to London Bridge in an excited and nervous state. Followed Walter to Hugo Oberstein's house at 13 Caulfield Gardens, where he confronted the thieves. Struck on the head by Oberstein with a life-preserver and died within five minutes. His body was placed on the roof of an Underground train from Oberstein's back window and fell off near Aldgate Station at the points and curve. Found by plate-layer Mason at 6am Tuesday with head badly crushed. Had seven of ten stolen Bruce-Partington papers in his pocket, along with £2.15 in his purse, a check-book on the Woolwich branch of the Capital and Counties Bank, and two dress-circle tickets for the Woolwich Theatre. Next in rank to Sidney Johnson in the office. Described by his fiancee as the most single-minded, chivalrous, patriotic man upon earth." ;
    ex:age "27" ;
    ex:occupation "clerk at Woolwich Arsenal" ;
    ex:employedBy :woolwichArsenalOrg ;
    ex:engagedTo :violetWestbury ;
    ex:knows :violetWestbury ;
    ex:knows :sidneyJohnson ;
    ex:knows :sirJamesWalter ;
    ex:killedBy :hugoOberstein ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :brucePartingtonPlansDoc .

:arthurHStaunton a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "Arthur" ;
    ex:lastName "Staunton" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Arthur H. Staunton" ;
    ex:description "A rising young forger listed in Holmes's commonplace book under letter S. Mentioned only in passing when Holmes searches for information on the Staunton name." ;
    ex:occupation "Forger" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :missingThreeQuarterDoc .

:augustoBarelli a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Deputy ;
    ex:firstName "Augusto" ;
    ex:lastName "Barelli" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Augusto Barelli" ;
    ex:description "Augusto Barelli is the father of Emilia Lucca. He is the chief lawyer and once the deputy of the Posilippo area near Naples. Gennaro Lucca was in his employment. He forbade the match between his daughter and Gennaro, causing them to elope." ;
    ex:occupation "chief lawyer and deputy" ;
    ex:livesAt :posilippo ;
    ex:parentOf :emiliaLucca ;
    ex:knows :gennaroLucca ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :redCircleDoc .

:avengerHusband a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Nobleman, ex:Victim ;
    ex:prefLabel "Husband of Milverton's Avenger" ;
    ex:description "An unnamed nobleman and statesman described by his wife as 'the noblest gentleman that ever lived, a man whose boots I was never worthy to lace'. He died of a broken heart after Milverton sent compromising letters about his wife to him. His identity, like his wife's, is suppressed by Watson. At the end of the story, his 'time-honoured title' is read by Watson beneath the avenger's photograph in a shop window." ;
    ex:occupation "nobleman and statesman" ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :milvertonAvenger ;
    ex:blackmailedBy :charlesAugustusMilverton ;
    ex:engagedTo :colonelDorking ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :milvertonDoc .

:babyFerguson a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim ;
    ex:prefLabel "Baby Ferguson" ;
    ex:description "The infant child of Robert Ferguson and his second Peruvian wife, just under one year of age. Described as a very beautiful child, dark-eyed and golden-haired, a wonderful mixture of the Saxon and the Latin. The baby was the victim of poisoning by half-brother Jack Ferguson, who pricked the child with curare-dipped arrows from the South American weapons collection. The baby's mother was caught apparently biting the child's neck but was in fact sucking out the poison to save the child's life, leaving a small angry red pucker on the cherub throat." ;
    ex:childOf :robertFerguson ;
    ex:childOf :mrsFerguson ;
    ex:gender "male" ;
    ex:halfSiblingOf :jackFerguson ;
    ex:livesAt :cheesemans ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :sussexVampireDoc .

:bakerStreetCookThorBridge a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Baker Street Cook (Thor Bridge)" ;
    ex:description "An unnamed cook at 221B Baker Street during the Thor Bridge case. She makes hard-boiled eggs for breakfast and reads the Family Herald, a love romance periodical. Holmes attributes the overcooked eggs to her being absorbed in the magazine." ;
    ex:occupation "cook" ;
    ex:gender "female" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :thorBridgeDoc .

:baldySimpson a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Soldier, ex:Victim ;
    ex:lastName "Simpson" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Baldy Simpson" ;
    skos:altLabel "Simpson" ;
    ex:description "Baldy Simpson was a soldier who served with Godfrey Emsworth and Anderson during the Boer War. The three became separated from their unit during the Battle of Buffelsspruit outside Pretoria. Simpson and Anderson were both killed by the Boers during this engagement." ;
    ex:knows :godfreyEmsworth ;
    ex:knows :andersonSoldier ;
    ex:killedAt :battleOfBuffelsspruit ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :blanchedSoldierDoc .

:bannisterServant a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Servant ;
    ex:lastName "Bannister" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Bannister" ;
    ex:description "Servant to Hilton Soames at the College of St. Luke's for ten years. A little, white-faced, clean-shaven, grizzly-haired fellow of about fifty. Accidentally left his duplicate key in Soames's door on the day the exam proofs were on the desk. Previously served as butler to Sir Jabez Gilchrist, father of the student Gilchrist. Upon recognizing Gilchrist's tan gloves on the chair, Bannister sat on them to conceal the evidence, then let Gilchrist escape from the bedroom after Soames left. Counseled Gilchrist to do the right thing, invoking the memory of his father." ;
    ex:occupation "College servant; formerly butler" ;
    ex:knows :hiltonSoames ;
    ex:knows :gilchrist ;
    ex:knows :sirJabezGilchrist ;
    ex:worksAt :collegeOfStLukes ;
    ex:servantOf :hiltonSoames ;
    ex:formerlyEmployedBy :sirJabezGilchrist ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :threeStudentsDoc .

:barkerDetective a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Detective ;
    ex:lastName "Barker" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Mr. Barker" ;
    ex:description "Private detective described by Holmes as his hated rival upon the Surrey shore. A tall, dark, heavily moustached, rather military-looking man who wears gray-tinted sun-glasses and a large Masonic tie-pin. Engaged by Dr. Ray Ernest's family to investigate Ernest's disappearance. Had been watching The Haven for several days and spotted Watson as a suspicious character. Encountered Holmes during his nocturnal burglary and they continued the investigation together. Helped Holmes confront and restrain Amberley. His first name is not given in the text." ;
    ex:occupation "private detective" ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:knows :josiahAmberley ;
    ex:hasParticipantIn :holmesBurglaryHaven ;
    ex:hasParticipantIn :confrontationAmberley ;
