:barneyStockdale a ex:FictionalPerson , ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "Barney" ;
    ex:lastName "Stockdale" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Barney Stockdale" ;
    skos:altLabel "Barney" ;
    ex:description "A criminal and principal of Steve Dixie, more astute than his subordinate. Part of the Spencer John gang, specializing in assaults, intimidation, and similar dirty work. Husband of Susan Stockdale. Employed by Isadora Klein to steal Douglas Maberley's manuscript. Spoke with Susan over the hedge at The Three Gables. Led the burglary of The Three Gables in which Mrs. Maberley was chloroformed. Previously had Douglas Maberley beaten under Isadora Klein's window." ;
    ex:employedBy :isadoraKlein ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :susanStockdale ;
    ex:knows :steveDixie , :isadoraKlein , :susanStockdale ;
    ex:memberOf :spencerJohnGang ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :threeGablesDoc .

:baronDowson a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:lastName "Dowson" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Baron Dowson" ;
    ex:description "Baron Dowson is a criminal who was hanged. The night before his execution he said that in Holmes's case what the law had gained the stage had lost, praising Holmes's impersonation abilities." ;
    ex:title "Baron" ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :mazarinStoneDoc .

:baronMaupertuis a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:lastName "Maupertuis" ;
    ex:title "Baron" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Baron Maupertuis" ;
    skos:altLabel "Maupertuis" ;
    ex:description "Described as the most accomplished swindler in Europe. Connected to the Netherland-Sumatra Company and its colossal schemes involving politics and finance. Holmes's investigation of Maupertuis extended over two months, during which the police of three countries had failed to catch him. The case left Holmes exhausted and ill." ;
    ex:occupation "swindler" ;
    ex:memberOf :netherlandSumatraCompany ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :reigateSquiresDoc .

:baronVonHerling a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Diplomat ;
    ex:firstName "Von Herling" ;
    ex:title "Baron" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Baron Von Herling" ;
    skos:altLabel "the secretary" ;
    ex:description "Chief secretary of the German legation in London. A huge man — deep, broad, and tall — with a slow, heavy fashion of speech which had been his main asset in his political career. Has a broad bald head. Visits Von Bork on the eve of war to discuss espionage successes and England's unpreparedness, then departs for Carlton Terrace in his 100-horse-power Benz limousine with chauffeur." ;
    ex:occupation "diplomat" ;
    ex:knows :vonBork ;
    ex:memberOf :germanLegationLondon ;
    ex:owns :vonHerlingBenz ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :hisLastBowDoc .

:beatriceFalder a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Beatrice" ;
    ex:lastName "Falder" ;
    ex:title "Lady" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Lady Beatrice Falder" ;
    skos:altLabel "Lady Beatrice" ;
    ex:description "Lady Beatrice Falder is the widowed sister of Sir Robert Norberton. She owned Shoscombe Old Place through a life interest from her late husband Sir James Falder, with the estate reverting to Sir James's brother upon her death. She loved horses, especially Shoscombe Prince, and was the special pride of the Shoscombe spaniels breed. She suffered from a weak heart and dropsy and was known to take a glass of wine. She died of dropsy approximately one week before the story's resolution. Her death was concealed by Sir Robert, and her body was hidden first in the old well-house and then in the family crypt." ;
    ex:causeOfDeath "dropsy" ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :jamesFalder ;
    ex:siblingOf :robertNorberton ;
    ex:livesAt :shoscombeOldPlace ;
    ex:owns :beatriceSpaniel ;
    ex:hasParticipantIn :deathOfBeatriceFalder ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :shoscombeOldPlaceDoc .

:bentleysPorter a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Porter at Bentley's Hotel" ;
    skos:altLabel "the day porter" ;
    ex:description "Day porter at Bentley's private hotel in London, goes off duty at eleven. Witnessed the bearded messenger delivering a note to Godfrey Staunton, saw Staunton nearly collapse, and observed the two leaving together at half-past ten heading toward the Strand. Only distinguished the word 'time' from their conversation." ;
    ex:occupation "Hotel porter" ;
    ex:employedBy :bentleysHotel ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :missingThreeQuarterDoc .

:beppo a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal, ex:Sculptor ;
    ex:firstName "Beppo" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Beppo" ;
    ex:description "An Italian criminal whose surname is unknown. Formerly a skilful sculptor who earned an honest living but took to evil courses. A well-known ne'er-do-well among the Italian colony in London. Has an alert, sharp-featured simian face with thick eyebrows and a peculiar projection of the lower part of the face. Worked at Gelder & Co. where he hid the stolen black pearl of the Borgias in a wet plaster Napoleon bust before being arrested for knifing another Italian. Sentenced to one year. After release, systematically tracked down and smashed the six busts searching for the pearl. Got employment at Morse Hudson's shop to trace three busts. Used his cousin at Gelder's to find the other three buyers. Killed Pietro Venucci during a confrontation at Harker's house. Arrested by Holmes, Watson, and Lestrade at Laburnum Lodge, Chiswick. Could speak English perfectly well. Had been in jail twice previously - once for petty theft, once for the stabbing." ;
    ex:nationality "Italian" ;
    ex:occupation "sculptor and workman" ;
    ex:employedBy :gelderCoFirm ;
    ex:employedBy :morseHudsonShop ;
    ex:cousinOf :beppoCousin ;
    ex:kills :pietroVenucci ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :sixNapoleonsDoc .

:beppoCousin a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Beppo's Cousin" ;
    ex:description "An unnamed cousin of Beppo who works at Gelder & Co. Through this cousin, Beppo found out which retail firms had bought the Napoleon busts after his release from prison." ;
    ex:worksAt :gelderCo ;
    ex:cousinOf :beppo ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :sixNapoleonsDoc .

