:bobCarruthers a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "Bob" ;
    ex:lastName "Carruthers" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Bob Carruthers" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Carruthers" ;
    skos:altLabel "Bob" ;
    ex:description "Dark, sallow, clean-shaven, silent man with polite manners and a pleasant smile. A widower with one daughter aged ten. Employed Violet Smith as music teacher at Chiltern Grange at £100/year. Deeply interested in South African gold shares, went to the City two or three times a week. Originally came from South Africa with Woodley after Ralph Smith's death, having played cards on the voyage for who would marry Violet (Woodley won). Fell in love with Violet and proposed marriage, which she refused. Secretly followed Violet on her bicycle rides wearing a false coal-black beard as disguise to protect her from Woodley and Williamson. Tore Woodley off Violet during an earlier assault. Shot Woodley during the forced marriage scene. Was likely given a light sentence by the court." ;
    ex:occupation "investor in South African gold shares" ;
    ex:gender "male" ;
    ex:disguisedAs :carrutherssFalseBeard ;
    ex:employs :violetSmith ;
    ex:employs :mrsDixon ;
