:charlesAugustusMilverton a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Blackmailer, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Charles" ;
    ex:lastName "Milverton" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Charles Augustus Milverton" ;
    skos:altLabel "C.A.M." ;
    skos:altLabel "Milverton" ;
    ex:description "A notorious blackmailer described by Holmes as 'the worst man in London'. A man of about fifty with a large intellectual head, round plump hairless face, perpetual frozen smile, keen grey eyes behind broad golden-rimmed glasses, resembling Mr. Pickwick in benevolence of appearance. He pays high sums for compromising letters from treacherous servants and genteel ruffians, then extorts money from his victims threatening exposure. He lives at Appledore Towers in Hampstead, owns a carriage and pair, is a heavy sleeper retiring punctually at ten-thirty, employs a secretary and servants, and keeps a guard dog. He carries a large revolver. He is shot dead in his study by an unnamed woman whose husband died after Milverton sent compromising letters to him." ;
    ex:occupation "blackmailer and extortionist" ;
    ex:livesAt :appledoreTowers ;
    ex:owns :milvertonRevolver ;
    ex:owns :milvertonSafe ;
    ex:owns :milvertonNotebook ;
    ex:employs :agatha ;
