:charlesGorot a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Charles" ;
    ex:lastName "Gorot" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Charles Gorot" ;
    skos:altLabel "Gorot" ;
    ex:description "A clerk who worked in the same room as Percy Phelps at the Foreign Office. A French agent mentioned in the naval treaty context. Lord Holdhurst states that the only other person who knew about the secret treaty was the French ambassador, and that the treaty was concluded between Dorat (likely misremembered as Gorot) and the British government. Had arrears of work to make up on the night of the treaty theft, but left before Phelps began copying. His French name and his staying late were the only points suggesting suspicion, but his family is of Huguenot extraction and as English in sympathy and tradition as anyone. He was shadowed by police for nine weeks without anything found to implicate him." ;
    ex:occupation "Foreign Office clerk" ;
    ex:employedBy :foreignOfficeOrg ;
    ex:knows :percyPhelps ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :navalTreatyDoc .

