:colonelEmsworth a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Soldier ;
    ex:lastName "Emsworth" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Colonel Emsworth" ;
    skos:altLabel "Emsworth the Crimean V.C." ;
    ex:description "Colonel Emsworth is a huge, bow-backed man with a smoky skin, straggling gray beard, and a red-veined nose. He is described as the greatest martinet in the Army in his day. He holds the Victoria Cross from the Crimean War. He is Godfrey Emsworth's father and lives at Tuxbury Old Park near Bedford. He attempted to conceal his son's apparent leprosy by hiding him in a lodge on the estate grounds, telling inquirers that Godfrey had gone on a voyage round the world. He was hostile to James Dodd's inquiries and threatened to call the county police when Holmes and Dodd returned to investigate." ;
    ex:militaryRank "Colonel" ;
    ex:militaryDecoration "Victoria Cross (Crimean War)" ;
