    ex:lastName "Ras" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Daulat Ras" ;
    ex:description "Indian student at the College of St. Luke's, occupying the second floor room on the same staircase as Soames. Described as quiet, inscrutable, silent, little, and hook-nosed. Well up in his work though Greek is his weak subject. Steady and methodical. Visited Soames before the incident to ask particulars about the examination; the proofs were rolled up at that time. Paced his room restlessly in the evening (studying). Holmes found his pencils and knives satisfactory (not matching the evidence)." ;
