:dolores a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:DomesticWorker ;
    ex:firstName "Dolores" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Dolores" ;
    ex:description "Dolores is the personal maid of Mrs. Ferguson, described as a tall, slim, brown-faced girl. She had been with Mrs. Ferguson for some years before her marriage to Robert Ferguson, and is described as more friend than servant. She speaks broken English with an accent. She is fiercely protective of and loyal to her mistress, taking food to her during her confinement and expressing fear for her health. She holds the key to Mrs. Ferguson's room and facilitates Watson's medical visit and later Holmes's revelatory visit." ;
    ex:employedBy :mrsFerguson ;
