:donMurillo a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal, ex:Dictator ;
    ex:firstName "Juan" ;
    ex:lastName "Murillo" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Don Murillo" ;
    skos:altLabel "Henderson" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Henderson" ;
    skos:altLabel "The Tiger of San Pedro" ;
    skos:altLabel "Juan Murillo" ;
    skos:altLabel "Marquess of Montalva" ;
    ex:description "Known as the Tiger of San Pedro, the most lewd and bloodthirsty tyrant to govern any country with a pretence to civilization. Ruled San Pedro for ten or twelve years through strength, fearlessness, and cruelty. Murdered rivals including Victor Durando. When a universal rising threatened, he secretly conveyed his treasures aboard a ship and fled with his two children and secretary Lopez. Lived in England as Mr. Henderson at High Gable, near Oxshott. A man of fifty, strong, active, with iron-gray hair, great bunched black eyebrows, the step of a deer and the air of an emperor. Yellow and sapless but tough as whipcord. Enormously rich. Murdered Garcia on Oxshott Common. Confined and tortured Miss Burnet. Escaped England via Edmonton Street lodging-house. Eventually murdered in Madrid at the Hotel Escurial under the identity of the Marquess of Montalva." ;
    ex:occupation "former dictator" ;
    ex:physicalDescription "Man of fifty, strong, active, iron-gray hair, great bunched black eyebrows, step of a deer, air of an emperor, yellow and sapless, tough as whipcord, dark deepset brooding eyes, parchment face" ;
    ex:livesAt :highGable ;
    ex:dictatorOf :sanPedro ;
    ex:nationality "San Pedran" ;
    ex:hasSecretary :lopez ;
    ex:parentOf :hendersonElderDaughter ;
    ex:parentOf :hendersonYoungerDaughter ;
    ex:kills :aloysiusGarcia ;
    ex:kills :victorDurando ;
    ex:knows :lopez ;
    ex:knows :missBurnet ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :wisteriaLodgeDoc .

:dorak a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "A." ;
    ex:lastName "Dorak" ;
    ex:prefLabel "A. Dorak" ;
    skos:altLabel "Dorak" ;
    ex:description "A. Dorak is a Bohemian man described as elderly and suave. He keeps a large general store on Commercial Road in London. He serves as the agent for H. Lowenstein of Prague, supplying rejuvenation serum to Professor Presbury and at least one other client in England. His letters to Presbury are written in a crabbed, illiterate hand, dated from Commercial Road, and signed 'A. Dorak'. They consist of invoices for fresh bottles and receipts acknowledging money. Holmes identifies his name as Slavonic." ;
    ex:occupation "general store keeper" ;
    ex:nationality "Bohemian" ;
    ex:livesAt :commercialRoad ;
    ex:agentOf :lowenstein ;
    ex:supplies :rejuvenationSerum ;
    ex:knows :professorPresbury ;
    ex:knows :lowenstein ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :creepingManDoc .

:douglasMaberley a ex:FictionalPerson , ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Douglas" ;
    ex:lastName "Maberley" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Douglas Maberley" ;
    ex:description "Deceased son of Mary and Mortimer Maberley. Was a British attache at Rome, known throughout London as a magnificent, debonair, and splendid man. Had a love affair with Isadora Klein, who rejected his marriage proposal. Was beaten by Barney Stockdale's men under Klein's window. Became moody, morose, and cynical. Wrote a novel thinly disguising his affair with Klein, sending one copy to her and one to his publisher. Died of pneumonia in Rome." ;
    ex:occupation "attache" ;
    ex:authorOf :maberleyManuscript ;
    ex:childOf :maryMaberley , :mortimerMaberley ;
    ex:knows :isadoraKlein ;
    ex:loverOf :isadoraKlein ;
    ex:livesAt :rome ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :threeGablesDoc .

:drAinstree a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Doctor ;
    ex:lastName "Ainstree" ;
    ex:honorific "Dr." ;
    ex:prefLabel "Dr. Ainstree" ;
    ex:description "Dr. Ainstree is described by Watson as the greatest living authority upon tropical disease, currently in London. Watson threatens to fetch him to attend Holmes." ;
    ex:occupation "tropical disease specialist" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :dyingDetectiveDoc .

:drBarnicot a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Doctor ;
    ex:lastName "Barnicot" ;
    ex:title "Dr." ;
    ex:prefLabel "Dr. Barnicot" ;
    ex:description "A well-known medical practitioner with one of the largest practices on the south side of the Thames. His residence and principal consulting-room are at Kennington Road, with a branch surgery and dispensary at Lower Brixton Road, two miles away. An enthusiastic admirer of Napoleon, with a house full of books, pictures, and relics of the French Emperor. Purchased two duplicate plaster casts of Devine's Napoleon head from Morse Hudson. Both busts were smashed by Beppo." ;
    ex:occupation "medical practitioner" ;
    ex:livesAt :barnicotResidence ;
    ex:worksAt :barnicotResidence ;
    ex:worksAt :barnicotSurgery ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :sixNapoleonsDoc .

:drFerrier a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Doctor ;
    ex:lastName "Ferrier" ;
    ex:title "Dr." ;
    ex:prefLabel "Dr. Ferrier" ;
    ex:description "A doctor who lives near Percy Phelps in Woking. He was traveling on the same Woking train on the night of the treaty theft. The detective at Waterloo station told him enough about what had happened. He took charge of Phelps, who had a fit at the station and was practically a raving maniac before reaching home. He cared for Phelps during his illness along with Annie Harrison. He attended Percy Phelps during his nervous illness following the theft of the naval treaty. He treated Phelps at Briarbrae over the course of nine weeks of brain fever." ;
    ex:occupation "doctor" ;
    ex:knows :percyPhelps ;
    ex:livesAt :woking ;
    ex:treats :percyPhelps ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :navalTreatyDoc .

:drHorsom a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Doctor ;
    ex:prefLabel "Dr. Horsom" ;
    ex:lastName "Horsom" ;
    skos:altLabel "Horsom" ;
    ex:description "Dr. Horsom is a physician with a practice at 13 Firbank Villas. He was called by Peters to attend Rose Spender at 36 Poultney Square. He found the old woman dying of pure senility, witnessed her pass away, and signed the death certificate indicating senile decay. He noted nothing suspicious in the house save the absence of servants." ;
    ex:occupation "physician" ;
    ex:livesAt :13FirbankVillas ;
    ex:attendedTo :roseSpender ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :disappearanceLadyFrancesCarfaxDoc .

:drMooreAgar a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Doctor ;
    ex:firstName "Moore" ;
    ex:lastName "Agar" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Dr. Moore Agar" ;
    skos:altLabel "Moore Agar" ;
    ex:description "A doctor of Harley Street whose dramatic introduction to Holmes is mentioned but not recounted. In March 1897, he gave positive injunctions that Holmes must lay aside all his cases and surrender to complete rest or face permanent disqualification from work. His orders led to Holmes and Watson's retreat to Cornwall." ;
    ex:occupation "doctor" ;
    ex:locatedIn :harleyStreet ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :devilsFootDoc .

:drRichards a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Doctor ;
    ex:lastName "Richards" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Dr. Richards" ;
    ex:description "A local doctor in Cornwall, sent for on an urgent call to Tredannick Wartha on the morning after the poisoning. Arrived by carriage and overtook Mortimer Tregennis on his morning walk. Nearly fainted himself upon seeing the scene, falling into a chair. Declared Brenda must have been dead at least six hours." ;
    ex:occupation "doctor" ;
    ex:locatedIn :cornwall ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :devilsFootDoc .

