:eduardoLucas a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Spy, ex:Singer, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Eduardo" ;
    ex:lastName "Lucas" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Eduardo Lucas" ;
    skos:altLabel "M. Henri Fournaye" ;
    ex:description "International spy and secret agent, one of three heads of the profession known to Holmes. Well known in society circles for his charming personality and reputation as one of the best amateur tenors in the country. Unmarried publicly, thirty-four years of age. Lived at 16 Godolphin Street, Westminster. Keen student of international politics, indefatigable gossip, remarkable linguist, and untiring letter-writer. On intimate terms with leading politicians of several countries. Had promiscuous but superficial relations with women. Habits regular, conduct inoffensive. Lived a double life as M. Henri Fournaye in Paris, sometimes spending three months there. His wife Mme. Henri Fournaye was of Creole origin. Blackmailed Lady Hilda with her pre-marriage letter in exchange for the diplomatic document. Had a spy in Hope's office. Murdered by Mme. Fournaye by stabbing with a curved Indian dagger at his home. Had hidden the diplomatic letter under a floorboard beneath the drugget before being killed." ;
    ex:occupation "international spy and secret agent; amateur tenor" ;
    ex:age 34 ;
    ex:livesAt :16GodolphinStreet ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :mmeHenriFournaye ;
    ex:employs :mrsPringle ;
    ex:employs :johnMitton ;
    ex:knows :ladyHildaTrelawneyHope ;
    ex:hasAlias :henriFournaye ;
    ex:blackmails :ladyHildaTrelawneyHope ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :secondStainDoc .

