:edwardRucastle a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Edward" ;
    ex:lastName "Rucastle" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Edward Rucastle" ;
    ex:description """Edward Rucastle is the six-year-old son of Jephro Rucastle and his second wife. He is small for his age with a head which is quite disproportionately large. His whole life appears to be spent in alternation between savage fits of passion and gloomy intervals of sulking. Giving pain to any creature weaker than himself seems to be his one idea of amusement, and he shows remarkable talent in planning the capture of mice, little birds, and insects. He kills cockroaches with a slipper.""" ;
    ex:childOf :jephroRucastle, :mrsRucastle ;
    ex:knows :violetHunter ;
    ex:livesAt :copperBeeches ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :copperBeechesDoc .

:ejc a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "E. J. C." ;
    ex:description "E. J. C. is the person who signed the letter from Morrison, Morrison, and Dodd to Holmes on behalf of the firm ('per E. J. C.'). Likely a clerk or junior partner. No further identification is given in the text." ;
    ex:employedBy :morrisonMorrisonAndDodd ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :sussexVampireDoc .

:eugeniaRonder a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "Eugenia" ;
    ex:lastName "Ronder" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Eugenia Ronder" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mrs. Ronder" ;
    skos:altLabel "The Veiled Lodger" ;
    ex:description "Eugenia Ronder is a former circus performer who was raised on the sawdust and could do springs through the hoop before age ten. She married the showman Ronder, who was cruel and abusive. She fell in love with Leonardo the strong man and together they planned her husband's murder. On the night of the murder at Abbas Parva, the lion Sahara King attacked her after she opened its cage, terribly mutilating her face. Leonardo fled instead of helping her. She lived as a veiled lodger at Mrs. Merrilow's house in South Brixton for seven years. She confessed the truth to Holmes in late 1896. She contemplated suicide but was dissuaded by Holmes, sending him a bottle of prussic acid as proof she would follow his advice. Her full name is Eugenia Ronder." ;
    ex:gender "female" ;
    ex:occupation "circus performer" ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :ronder ;
    ex:loverOf :leonardo ;
    ex:livesAt :mrsMerrilowHouse ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes, :johnWatson, :mrsMerrilow, :leonardo, :ronder, :jimmyGriggs ;
    ex:confessedTo :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:hasParticipatedIn :abbasParvaIncident, :veiledLodgerInvestigation ;
    ex:attackedBy :saharaKing ;
    ex:employedBy :rondersWildBeastShow ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :veiledLodgerDoc .

