:fitzroyMcPherson a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Fitzroy" ;
    ex:lastName "McPherson" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Fitzroy McPherson" ;
    skos:altLabel "McPherson" ;
    ex:description "Fitzroy McPherson is the science master at The Gables coaching establishment. A fine upstanding young fellow, his life was crippled by heart trouble following rheumatic fever, though he was a natural athlete who excelled in every game that did not strain him too greatly. Summer and winter he went swimming. He was secretly engaged to Maud Bellamy, keeping it hidden because his elderly, dying uncle might disinherit him for an unsuitable marriage. He was killed by a Cyanea capillata (Lion's Mane jellyfish) while preparing to bathe in the tidal lagoon below the chalk cliffs. His dying words were 'the Lion's Mane,' which ultimately led Holmes to the solution. He owned an Airedale terrier that later died at the same spot." ;
    ex:occupation "Science master" ;
    ex:causeOfDeath "Stung by Cyanea capillata jellyfish" ;
    ex:hasMedicalCondition "Heart trouble following rheumatic fever" ;
    ex:employedBy :haroldStackhurst ;
    ex:friendOf :ianMurdoch ;
    ex:hasRelative :mcPhersonUncle ;
    ex:isEngagedTo :maudBellamy ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes, :haroldStackhurst, :ianMurdoch, :maudBellamy, :tomBellamy, :williamBellamy ;
    ex:owns :mcPhersonDog ;
    ex:victimOf :deathOfMcPherson ;
    ex:worksAt :theGables ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :lionsManeDoc .

:gibsonChildren a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Gibson Children" ;
    ex:description "The two young children of Neil and Maria Gibson at Thor Place. Their education is superintended by governess Grace Dunbar. They are not named individually in the text." ;
    ex:childOf :neilGibson ;
    ex:childOf :mariaGibson ;
    ex:hasGoverness :graceDunbar ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :thorBridgeDoc .

:graceDunbar a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Governess ;
    ex:firstName "Grace" ;
    ex:lastName "Dunbar" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Grace Dunbar" ;
    skos:altLabel "Miss Dunbar" ;
    ex:description "Grace Dunbar is the governess to Neil Gibson's two children at Thor Place. She is a very beautiful brunette, tall, with a noble figure and commanding presence, a strong clear-cut yet sensitive face. She answered an advertisement for the position. Gibson developed feelings for her but she refused his advances. She stayed because others depended on her and she could use her influence over Gibson for good, tempering his ruthless business practices. She was hated by Mrs. Gibson out of jealousy. She was accused of murdering Mrs. Gibson after a revolver was found in her wardrobe and her note was found in the dead woman's hand. She was held at Winchester awaiting the Assizes. Holmes proved her innocence by demonstrating Mrs. Gibson's suicide method." ;
    ex:occupation "governess" ;
    ex:employedBy :neilGibson ;
    ex:livesAt :thorPlace ;
    ex:knows :neilGibson ;
    ex:knows :mariaGibson ;
    ex:knows :joyceCummings ;
    ex:framedBy :mariaGibson ;
    ex:governessOf :gibsonChildren ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :thorBridgeDoc .

:hainesJohnson a ex:FictionalPerson , ex:Criminal ;
    ex:lastName "Haines-Johnson" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Haines-Johnson" ;
    ex:description "A man who presented himself as a house agent, auctioneer, and valuer to Mrs. Mary Maberley, offering to buy The Three Gables and all its contents. Likely a false identity used as a front for Isadora Klein's agents. His business was not listed in the directory. Drew up a purchase agreement with a clause preventing Mrs. Maberley from removing any possessions from the house." ;
    ex:occupation "house agent (purported)" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :threeGablesDoc .

:haroldStackhurst a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Harold" ;
    ex:lastName "Stackhurst" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Harold Stackhurst" ;
    skos:altLabel "Stackhurst" ;
    ex:description "Harold Stackhurst is the owner of The Gables, a well-known coaching establishment near Holmes's Sussex retirement villa. A former rowing Blue and excellent all-round scholar, he employs about twenty young fellows preparing for various professions with a staff of several masters. He and Holmes are friendly enough to drop in on each other without invitation. He discovers McPherson dying on the cliff path and later rescues Ian Murdoch from the same jellyfish attack. He fires Murdoch in anger after the confrontation at The Haven but later reconciles with him." ;
    ex:occupation "Coaching establishment owner" ;
    ex:employs :fitzroyMcPherson, :ianMurdoch ;
    ex:friendOf :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:hasParticipatedIn :mcPhersonDeathInvestigation, :destructionOfCyanea ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes, :fitzroyMcPherson, :ianMurdoch, :maudBellamy ;
    ex:livesAt :theGables ;
    ex:owns :theGables ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :lionsManeDoc .

:harvey a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Servant ;
    ex:lastName "Harvey" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Harvey" ;
    ex:description "Harvey is one of John Mason's stable lads at Shoscombe Old Place. He operates the central heating furnace in the cellar under Lady Beatrice's room. He discovers a charred bone fragment while raking out the cinders and brings it to Mason." ;
    ex:occupation "stable lad" ;
    ex:employedBy :robertNorberton ;
    ex:worksAt :shoscombeOldPlace ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :shoscombeOldPlaceDoc .

:holmesHousekeeperLionsMane a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Holmes's Housekeeper (Sussex)" ;
    ex:description "Holmes's old housekeeper at his Sussex retirement villa. She is unnamed in the text. She is the one who first tells Holmes about the death of McPherson's dog, having heard through the local gossip network, which triggers Holmes's key insight into the case." ;
    ex:occupation "Housekeeper" ;
    ex:employedBy :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:livesAt :holmesSussexVilla ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :lionsManeDoc .

:howardGarrideb a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Howard" ;
    ex:lastName "Garrideb" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Howard Garrideb" ;
    ex:description "A fictitious person invented by Killer Evans as part of his Three Garridebs scheme. Purported to be a constructor of agricultural machinery operating from Grosvenor Buildings, Aston, Birmingham. Evans planted a fake advertisement in a local Birmingham newspaper using American spellings and terminology to create the appearance of a third Garrideb, in order to lure Nathan Garrideb to Birmingham and gain access to the hidden counterfeiting press." ;
    ex:occupation "constructor of agricultural machinery (fictitious)" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :threeGarridebsDoc .

:hansSloane a ex:RealPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Hans" ;
    ex:lastName "Sloane" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Hans Sloane" ;
    skos:altLabel "Sir Hans Sloane" ;
    ex:description "A real historical figure referenced by Nathan Garrideb, who aspired to be 'the Hans Sloane of my age.' Sir Hans Sloane was an Irish-British physician and collector whose collection formed the foundation of the British Museum." ;
    ex:occupation "physician and collector" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :threeGarridebsDoc .

:ianMurdoch a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Ian" ;
    ex:lastName "Murdoch" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Ian Murdoch" ;
    skos:altLabel "Murdoch" ;
    ex:description "Ian Murdoch is the mathematical coach at The Gables coaching establishment. A tall, dark, thin man with coal-black eyes and swarthy face, he is taciturn and aloof, living in a high abstract region of surds and conic sections. He has occasional ferocious outbursts of temper, having once hurled McPherson's dog through a plate-glass window. Despite earlier tensions with McPherson, they became close friends, as Murdoch loved Maud Bellamy but stepped aside when she chose McPherson, becoming their go-between and carrying their messages. He was initially suspected of McPherson's murder but was exonerated when he himself was stung by the same Cyanea capillata jellyfish. He survived due to having a stronger heart than McPherson." ;
    ex:occupation "Mathematical coach" ;
    ex:employedBy :haroldStackhurst ;
    ex:friendOf :fitzroyMcPherson ;
    ex:goBetweenFor :fitzroyMcPherson, :maudBellamy ;
    ex:hasParticipatedIn :mcPhersonDeathInvestigation ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes, :haroldStackhurst, :fitzroyMcPherson, :maudBellamy ;
    ex:victimOf :attackOnMurdoch ;
    ex:worksAt :theGables ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :lionsManeDoc .

:inspectorBardle a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:PoliceOfficer ;
    ex:lastName "Bardle" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Inspector Bardle" ;
    skos:altLabel "Bardle" ;
    ex:description "Inspector Bardle is an inspector of the Sussex Constabulary. A steady, solid, bovine man with thoughtful eyes, he consults Holmes unofficially about the McPherson case. He considers arresting Ian Murdoch but Holmes persuades him the case is too weak. He is present when Murdoch staggers in injured and when Holmes identifies the Cyanea capillata as the killer. He is deeply impressed by Holmes's solution." ;
    ex:occupation "Police inspector" ;
    ex:rank "Inspector" ;
    ex:hasParticipatedIn :mcPhersonDeathInvestigation, :destructionOfCyanea ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:memberOf :sussexConstabulary ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :lionsManeDoc .

:inspectorMacKinnon a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:PoliceOfficer ;
    ex:lastName "MacKinnon" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Inspector MacKinnon" ;
    ex:description "A smart young police inspector who arrived at The Haven after Amberley's arrest. Holmes allowed MacKinnon to take credit for solving the case. The North Surrey Observer later published a report crediting MacKinnon with the brilliant deductions that led to solving the case." ;
    ex:occupation "police inspector" ;
    ex:hasParticipantIn :confrontationAmberley ;
    ex:hasParticipantIn :investigationRetiredColourman ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :retiredColourmanDoc .

:inspectorThreeGables a ex:FictionalPerson , ex:PoliceOfficer ;
    ex:prefLabel "Inspector (Three Gables Case)" ;
    ex:description "An unnamed police inspector who investigated the burglary at The Three Gables. Described as bustling and rubicund, with twenty-five years of experience. Greeted Holmes as an old friend. Regarded the case as a common ordinary burglary well within police capacity." ;
    ex:occupation "police inspector" ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :threeGablesDoc .

:isadoraKlein a ex:FictionalPerson , ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "Isadora" ;
    ex:lastName "Klein" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Isadora Klein" ;
    ex:description "A celebrated beauty of pure Spanish blood, whose family had been leaders in Pernambuco for generations. Married the aged German sugar king Klein and became the richest as well as the most lovely widow upon earth. Had several lovers, including Douglas Maberley, whose marriage proposal she rejected. Had Douglas beaten by Barney Stockdale's men under her window. About to marry the young Duke of Lomond. Hired Barney Stockdale and Susan to steal Douglas's manuscript novel that described their affair under thinly disguised names. Lived in one of the finest corner-houses of the West End on Grosvenor Square. Burned the stolen manuscript. Paid five thousand pounds to Mrs. Maberley through Holmes." ;
    ex:nationality "Spanish" ;
    ex:engagedTo :dukeOfLomond ;
    ex:employs :barneyStockdale , :susanStockdale ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :mrKlein ;
    ex:knows :douglasMaberley , :barneyStockdale , :susanStockdale , :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:livesAt :isadoraKleinHouse ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :threeGablesDoc .

:isadoraPersano a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Isadora" ;
    ex:lastName "Persano" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Isadora Persano" ;
    ex:description "Isadora Persano is a well-known journalist and duellist mentioned in the preamble. He was found stark staring mad with a match box in front of him which contained a remarkable worm said to be unknown to science. His case is among the unsolved records in Watson's dispatch box." ;
    ex:occupation "journalist, duellist" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :thorBridgeDoc .

:jackFerguson a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "Jack" ;
    ex:lastName "Ferguson" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Jack Ferguson" ;
    skos:altLabel "Jacky" ;
    skos:altLabel "Master Jacky" ;
    ex:description "Jack Ferguson is the fifteen-year-old son of Robert Ferguson by his first wife. He is pale-faced and fair-haired with excitable light blue eyes. He suffered a fall in childhood that left him with a twisted spine, weak back, and shambling gait. Despite his physical disability, he is mentally very developed and intensely affectionate toward his father and devoted to the memory of his dead mother. His love for his father has become distorted into jealous hatred of his half-brother, the baby, whose health and beauty contrast his own weakness. He secretly poisoned the baby using curare-dipped arrows from the South American weapons collection on the wall, having first tested the poison on the family dog Carlo. Holmes prescribes a year at sea as remedy." ;
    ex:age "15" ;
    ex:childOf :robertFerguson ;
    ex:childOf :fergusonsFirstWife ;
    ex:gender "male" ;
    ex:halfSiblingOf :babyFerguson ;
    ex:livesAt :cheesemans ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :sussexVampireDoc .

:jamesFalder a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Baronet ;
    ex:firstName "James" ;
    ex:lastName "Falder" ;
    ex:title "Sir" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Sir James Falder" ;
    skos:altLabel "Sir James" ;
    ex:description "Sir James Falder is the late husband of Lady Beatrice Falder. He was the former owner of Shoscombe Old Place. The estate was held as a life interest by Lady Beatrice and was set to revert to Sir James's brother upon her death. His ancestors are buried in the crypt beneath the old chapel in Shoscombe Park." ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :beatriceFalder ;
    ex:owns :shoscombeOldPlace ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :shoscombeOldPlaceDoc .

:jamesFalderBrother a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Sir James Falder's Brother" ;
    ex:description "The unnamed brother of Sir James Falder. The Shoscombe Old Place estate is set to revert to him upon the death of Lady Beatrice Falder, Sir James's widow. His name is not given in the text." ;
    ex:siblingOf :jamesFalder ;
    ex:inheritsFrom :beatriceFalder ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :shoscombeOldPlaceDoc .

:jamesPhillimore a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "James" ;
    ex:lastName "Phillimore" ;
    ex:prefLabel "James Phillimore" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. James Phillimore" ;
    ex:description "James Phillimore is mentioned in the preamble as one of Watson's unfinished tales. He stepped back into his own house to get his umbrella and was never more seen in this world. His case is among the unsolved records in Watson's dispatch box at Cox and Co." ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :thorBridgeDoc .

:jcElman a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "J.C." ;
    ex:lastName "Elman" ;
    ex:prefLabel "J.C. Elman" ;
    skos:altLabel "Reverend J.C. Elman" ;
    ex:description "The vicar of Moosmoor cum Little Purlington in Essex. Holds an M.A. degree. Listed in Crockford's Clerical Directory. A big, solemn, rather pompous clergyman. His name was used without his knowledge by Holmes on a forged telegram sent to Josiah Amberley. Denied having sent any wire and was angered by the deception." ;
    ex:occupation "vicar" ;
    ex:livesAt :vicarage_littlePurlington ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :retiredColourmanDoc .

:jeanBaptisteGreuze a ex:RealPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Jean Baptiste" ;
    ex:lastName "Greuze" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Jean Baptiste Greuze" ;
    skos:altLabel "Greuze" ;
    ex:description "Real French artist who flourished between 1750 and 1800. Holmes references him to demonstrate Moriarty's hidden wealth, noting that Moriarty owns a Greuze painting despite earning only seven hundred pounds a year. Holmes mentions that a Greuze painting entitled La Jeune Fille a l'Agneau fetched over forty thousand pounds at the Portalis sale in 1865." ;
    ex:occupation "Painter" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :valleyOfFearDoc .

:jephroRucastle a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "Jephro" ;
    ex:lastName "Rucastle" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Jephro Rucastle" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Rucastle" ;
    ex:description """Jephro Rucastle is the owner of the Copper Beeches, five miles from Winchester. He is a prodigiously stout man with a very smiling face and a great heavy chin which rolls down in fold upon fold over his throat. He is about forty-five years old, a widower who has remarried a woman much younger than himself. Outwardly genial and jovial, he conceals a cruel and dangerous nature. He imprisoned his daughter Alice in a locked wing of his house to prevent her marriage and to maintain control over her inheritance. He hired Violet Hunter as governess with peculiar conditions — cutting her hair short and wearing an electric-blue dress — to impersonate Alice and deceive her suitor Mr. Fowler. He threatened to throw Violet to the mastiff when she explored the forbidden wing. He was attacked and horribly mangled by his own starved mastiff Carlo, surviving only as a broken man kept alive by his devoted wife.""" ;
    ex:occupation "gentleman" ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :mrsRucastle ;
    ex:parentOf :aliceRucastle, :edwardRucastle ;
    ex:employs :violetHunter, :tollerCB, :mrsTollerCB ;
    ex:owns :copperBeeches, :carloMastiff ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes, :johnWatson, :violetHunter, :missStoper, :mrFowler ;
    ex:hasParticipatedIn :imprisonmentOfAliceRucastle, :maulingOfJephroRucastle, :copperBeechesInvestigation ;
    ex:livesAt :copperBeeches ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :copperBeechesDoc .

:jgWood a ex:RealPerson ;
    ex:firstName "J. G." ;
    ex:lastName "Wood" ;
    ex:prefLabel "J. G. Wood" ;
    skos:altLabel "John George Wood" ;
    ex:description "J. G. Wood is a famous naturalist and observer, author of the book 'Out of Doors.' He nearly perished from contact with a Cyanea capillata jellyfish while swimming off the coast of Kent. His detailed written account of the experience, including the distinctive scarlet lines on the skin and the cardiac effects, was the key reference that enabled Holmes to identify the creature responsible for McPherson's death." ;
    ex:occupation "Naturalist and author" ;
    ex:authorOf :outOfDoorsBook ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :lionsManeDoc .

:jimmyGriggs a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Clown ;
    ex:firstName "Jimmy" ;
    ex:lastName "Griggs" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Jimmy Griggs" ;
    skos:altLabel "Griggs" ;
    skos:altLabel "Little Jimmy Griggs" ;
    ex:description "Jimmy Griggs is the clown in Ronder's Wild Beast Show, referred to as little Jimmy Griggs. Despite having little to be funny about given the show's difficulties, he did what he could to hold things together along with Leonardo and Mrs. Ronder. He helped drive the lion Sahara King off Mrs. Ronder after the Abbas Parva incident." ;
    ex:gender "male" ;
    ex:occupation "clown" ;
    ex:employedBy :rondersWildBeastShow ;
    ex:hasParticipatedIn :abbasParvaIncident ;
    ex:knows :eugeniaRonder, :ronder, :leonardo ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :veiledLodgerDoc .

:johnMason a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Trainer, ex:Client ;
    ex:firstName "John" ;
    ex:lastName "Mason" ;
    ex:prefLabel "John Mason" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mason" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Mason" ;
    ex:description "John Mason is the head trainer at Shoscombe Old Place, employed by Sir Robert Norberton. He is tall, clean-shaven, with a firm, austere expression. He controls both horses and boys. Concerned about Sir Robert's erratic behavior, he writes to Sherlock Holmes requesting an investigation. He reports that Lady Beatrice has stopped visiting the stables and that Sir Robert visits the old crypt at night. He accompanies Holmes and Watson to the crypt and shows them the location where mummy remains were found." ;
    ex:occupation "head trainer" ;
    ex:employedBy :robertNorberton ;
    ex:worksAt :shoscombeOldPlace ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes, :stephensButler ;
    ex:hasParticipantIn :shoscombeInvestigation, :cryptExploration ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :shoscombeOldPlaceDoc .

:johnsonOxfordRugby a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:lastName "Johnson" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Johnson" ;
    ex:description "Oxford rugby player described by Cyril Overton as one of the 'Oxford fliers' who could easily outrun Moorhouse, the Cambridge reserve." ;
    ex:occupation "Rugby footballer" ;
    ex:affiliatedWith :oxfordUniversity ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :missingThreeQuarterDoc .

:jonathanWild a ex:RealPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "Jonathan" ;
    ex:lastName "Wild" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Jonathan Wild" ;
    ex:description "Real historical master criminal who lived around 1750. Holmes uses him as an analogy for Moriarty, describing Wild as the hidden force behind London criminals who sold his brains and organization on a fifteen per cent commission." ;
    ex:occupation "Criminal mastermind" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :valleyOfFearDoc .

:josiahAmberley a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Josiah" ;
    ex:lastName "Amberley" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Josiah Amberley" ;
    skos:altLabel "the retired colourman" ;
    skos:altLabel "the old colourman" ;
    ex:description "Retired junior partner of Brickfall and Amberley, manufacturers of artistic materials. Retired from business in 1896 at age sixty-one. Married in early 1897 a woman twenty years younger than himself. An avid chess player with an artificial limb. Known locally as a miser and harsh husband. Murdered his wife and Dr. Ray Ernest by luring them into his strong-room and flooding it with gas, then covered the smell by painting the house. Hid the bodies in a disused well concealed by a dog-kennel. Attempted suicide with a poison pellet when confronted by Holmes and Barker. Holmes suggests his destination is more likely Broadmoor than the scaffold." ;
    ex:occupation "manufacturer of artistic materials (retired)" ;
    ex:livesAt :theHavenLewisham ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :mrsAmberley ;
    ex:knows :rayErnest ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:knows :johnWatson ;
    ex:employs :brickfallAndAmberley ;
    ex:hasParticipantIn :murderAmberleyErnest ;
    ex:hasParticipantIn :confrontationAmberley ;
    ex:hasParticipantIn :journeyLittlePurlington ;
    ex:hasParticipantIn :investigationRetiredColourman ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :retiredColourmanDoc .

:josiahBarnes a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Innkeeper ;
    ex:firstName "Josiah" ;
    ex:lastName "Barnes" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Josiah Barnes" ;
    skos:altLabel "Barnes" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Barnes" ;
    ex:description "Josiah Barnes is the innkeeper and sporting host of the Green Dragon inn at Crendall, three miles from Shoscombe. He is described as old. He eagerly discusses fishing with Holmes and Watson and warns them about Sir Robert Norberton's hostility toward strangers near his training quarters. He received Lady Beatrice's pet spaniel from Sandy Bain on Sir Robert's orders." ;
    ex:occupation "innkeeper" ;
    ex:worksAt :greenDragon ;
    ex:owns :greenDragon ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :shoscombeOldPlaceDoc .

:joyceCummings a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Lawyer ;
    ex:firstName "Joyce" ;
    ex:lastName "Cummings" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Joyce Cummings" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Cummings" ;
    ex:description "Joyce Cummings is a rising barrister entrusted with the defence of Grace Dunbar. He accompanies Holmes and Watson to see Miss Dunbar in her cell at Winchester. Holmes tells him he will give him a case that will make England ring." ;
    ex:occupation "barrister" ;
    ex:knows :graceDunbar ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:knows :johnWatson ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :thorBridgeDoc .

:killerEvans a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "James" ;
    ex:lastName "Winter" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Killer Evans" ;
    skos:altLabel "James Winter" ;
    skos:altLabel "Morecroft" ;
    skos:altLabel "John Garrideb" ;
    ex:description "A dangerous American criminal whose real name is James Winter, also known as Morecroft and 'Killer' Evans. He posed as John Garrideb, Counsellor at Law from Moorville, Kansas, to perpetrate an elaborate scheme to access a hidden counterfeiting press. Short, powerful man with a round, fresh, clean-shaven face and intense, arresting eyes. Aged forty-four, native of Chicago. Known to have shot three men in the United States. Escaped from penitentiary through political influence. Came to London in 1893. Shot and killed Rodger Prescott, a fellow criminal, in a night-club on the Waterloo Road in January 1895 over a card game, and served five years in prison. Released in 1901 and placed under police supervision. Invented the Three Garridebs scheme to lure Nathan Garrideb away from his rooms so he could access Prescott's hidden counterfeiting equipment in the cellar below. When confronted by Holmes and Watson, he drew a revolver and fired two shots, wounding Watson in the thigh. Holmes subdued him by striking him on the head with a pistol. He was arrested and returned to prison." ;
    skos:altLabel "Killer Evans" ;
    ex:occupation "criminal" ;
    ex:age "44" ;
    ex:birthPlace :chicago ;
    ex:nationality "American" ;
    ex:hasKilled :rodgerPrescott ;
    ex:investigatedBy :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:knows :nathanGarrideb ;
    ex:knows :rodgerPrescott ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :threeGarridebsDoc .

:kleinFootman a ex:FictionalPerson , ex:Servant ;
    ex:prefLabel "Footman (Isadora Klein's House)" ;
    ex:description "A machine-like footman at Isadora Klein's house in Grosvenor Square. Attempted to deny Holmes and Watson entry by claiming his mistress was not at home." ;
    ex:occupation "footman" ;
    ex:employedBy :isadoraKlein ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :threeGablesDoc .

:lamberleyVet a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Lamberley Veterinarian" ;
    ex:description "An unnamed veterinarian who examined the Ferguson family's spaniel Carlo. He diagnosed the dog's paralysis as spinal meningitis, though it was actually caused by curare poisoning. His name is not given in the text." ;
    ex:gender "male" ;
    ex:occupation "veterinarian" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :sussexVampireDoc .

:langdalePike a ex:FictionalPerson , ex:Informant ;
    ex:firstName "Langdale" ;
    ex:lastName "Pike" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Langdale Pike" ;
    ex:description "A strange, languid creature who serves as Sherlock Holmes's human book of reference upon all matters of social scandal. Spends his waking hours in the bow window of a club on St. James's Street. Acts as both receiving-station and transmitter for all the gossip of the metropolis. Makes a four-figure income from paragraphs contributed weekly to gossip papers. Holmes discreetly helps Pike with knowledge and is helped in turn." ;
    ex:occupation "gossip columnist" ;
    ex:frequents :stJamesStreetClub ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :threeGablesDoc .

:leonardo a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal, ex:Acrobat ;
    ex:firstName "Leonardo" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Leonardo" ;
    skos:altLabel "Leonardo the Strong Man" ;
    ex:description "Leonardo is a professional acrobat and strong man in Ronder's Wild Beast Show. He is described as having a magnificent physique with huge arms folded across his swollen chest and a heavy moustache. He became the lover of Eugenia Ronder, and together they planned the murder of her husband. Leonardo crafted a club with a leaden head and five long steel nails spread like a lion's paw. He struck Ronder's skull on the night of the murder at Abbas Parva but lost his nerve when the lion attacked Eugenia, shouting in terror and fleeing. He gave evidence at the inquest and helped drive the lion off Mrs. Ronder along with Griggs and others. He drowned while bathing near Margate approximately a month before Holmes and Watson's visit to Mrs. Ronder in late 1896. He was described by Mrs. Ronder as having a poor spirit hidden in a splendid body." ;
    ex:gender "male" ;
    ex:occupation "strong man and acrobat" ;
    ex:loverOf :eugeniaRonder ;
    ex:employedBy :rondersWildBeastShow ;
    ex:kills :ronder ;
    ex:drownedAt :margate ;
    ex:hasParticipatedIn :abbasParvaIncident ;
    ex:knows :eugeniaRonder, :ronder, :jimmyGriggs ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :veiledLodgerDoc .

:lordSoutherton a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:lastName "Southerton" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Lord Southerton" ;
    ex:description """Lord Southerton is the owner of the preserves (woods) surrounding the Copper Beeches estate on three sides. He is mentioned but does not appear in the story.""" ;
    ex:owns :southertonPreserves ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :copperBeechesDoc .

:lowenstein a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "H." ;
    ex:lastName "Lowenstein" ;
    ex:prefLabel "H. Lowenstein" ;
    skos:altLabel "Lowenstein" ;
    skos:altLabel "Lowenstein of Prague" ;
    ex:description "H. Lowenstein is an obscure scientist based in Prague who strives for the secret of rejuvenescence and the elixir of life. He is tabooed by the medical profession for refusing to reveal the source of his wondrous strength-giving serum. He used serum from the black-faced langur monkey for Professor Presbury's treatment because a specimen was accessible, though he notes that anthropoid serum would have been better and nearer to human. He has one other client in England and uses A. Dorak as his agent for both. His letter to Presbury bears an Austrian stamp with Prague postmark and is written in an educated hand. Holmes threatens to write to him holding him criminally responsible for the poisons he circulates." ;
    ex:occupation "scientist" ;
    ex:livesAt :prague ;
    ex:hasAgent :dorak ;
    ex:knows :professorPresbury ;
    ex:knows :dorak ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :creepingManDoc .

:lysanderStarr a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Lysander" ;
    ex:lastName "Starr" ;
    ex:title "Dr." ;
    ex:prefLabel "Dr. Lysander Starr" ;
    ex:description "A person mentioned by Holmes as a former correspondent who was mayor of Topeka in 1890. Holmes used the name to test John Garrideb's truthfulness, and later revealed that he never actually knew such a person. John Garrideb claimed to remember him, confirming Holmes's suspicion that the American was lying. The historical existence of this person is uncertain - Holmes may have invented the name entirely." ;
    ex:occupation "mayor of Topeka (claimed)" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :threeGarridebsDoc .

:macphail a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Coachman ;
    ex:lastName "Macphail" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Macphail" ;
    ex:description "Macphail is the coachman at Professor Presbury's house in Camford. He sleeps over the stables. He has previously witnessed Presbury's strange behavior and was not surprised when Roy attacked the professor. He was woken by the uproar of the final attack and later guarded the injured Presbury." ;
    ex:occupation "coachman" ;
    ex:livesAt :presburyHouse ;
    ex:employedBy :professorPresbury ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :creepingManDoc .

:mariaGibson a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Maria" ;
    ex:lastName "Gibson" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Maria Gibson" ;
    skos:altLabel "Maria Pinto" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mrs. Gibson" ;
    ex:description "Maria Gibson, née Maria Pinto, is a Brazilian woman and the wife of Neil Gibson. She was the daughter of a government official at Manaos. Described as once very beautiful — a child of the sun and of passion, with a deep rich nature, passionate, whole-hearted, tropical, ill-balanced. She loved her husband devotedly even after his love faded and he treated her with cold cutting contempt. She was bitterly jealous of Grace Dunbar's influence over her husband. She committed suicide at Thor Bridge by shooting herself behind the right temple, using an ingenious method to dispose of the weapon (tied to a string and stone that pulled it into Thor Mere) while framing Miss Dunbar for murder by planting a matching revolver in Dunbar's wardrobe and extracting a note from her. Found by a gamekeeper about eleven o'clock, clad in her dinner dress with a shawl over her shoulders, the note clutched in her left hand." ;
    ex:nationality "Brazilian" ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :neilGibson ;
    ex:childOf :mariaPintoFather ;
    ex:framed :graceDunbar ;
    ex:diedAt :thorBridge ;
    ex:birthPlace :manaos ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :thorBridgeDoc .

:mariaPintoFather a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Maria Pinto's Father" ;
    ex:description "The unnamed father of Maria Gibson née Pinto. He was a government official at Manaos, Brazil." ;
    ex:occupation "government official" ;
    ex:parentOf :mariaGibson ;
    ex:livesAt :manaos ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :thorBridgeDoc .

:marlowBates a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Marlow" ;
    ex:lastName "Bates" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Marlow Bates" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Bates" ;
    ex:description "Marlow Bates is the manager of Neil Gibson's estate at Thor Place. He is a thin, nervous wisp of a man with frightened eyes and a twitching, hesitating manner, on the brink of an absolute nervous breakdown. He visits Holmes at Baker Street before Gibson arrives to warn that Gibson is a villain and was brutal to his wife. He has given notice and will leave in a couple of weeks. He shows Holmes and Watson Gibson's firearms collection at Thor Place." ;
    ex:occupation "estate manager" ;
    ex:employedBy :neilGibson ;
    ex:livesAt :thorPlace ;
    ex:knows :neilGibson ;
    ex:knows :fergusonThorBridge ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:knows :johnWatson ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :thorBridgeDoc .

:maryMaberley a ex:FictionalPerson , ex:Client ;
    ex:firstName "Mary" ;
    ex:lastName "Maberley" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Mary Maberley" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mrs. Maberley" ;
    ex:description "An engaging elderly woman of refinement and culture, client of Sherlock Holmes in the Three Gables case. Widow of Mortimer Maberley, who was an early client of Holmes. Mother of Douglas Maberley. Lives at The Three Gables, Harrow Weald. Was chloroformed during the burglary of her house. Received a five thousand pound check from Isadora Klein through Holmes to travel round the world." ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :mortimerMaberley ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes , :mrSutro ;
    ex:livesAt :theThreeGables ;
    ex:parentOf :douglasMaberley ;
    ex:victimOf :burglaryThreeGables ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :threeGablesDoc .

:maryMaidGables a ex:FictionalPerson , ex:Servant ;
    ex:firstName "Mary" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Mary (Maid at Three Gables)" ;
    ex:description "A young girl working as a maid at The Three Gables. Her name is not given in the text beyond 'Mary the maid.' During the burglary, she heard the noise and screamed out of the window, which brought the police." ;
    ex:occupation "maid" ;
    ex:employedBy :maryMaberley ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :threeGablesDoc .

:emiliaLucca a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Emilia" ;
    ex:lastName "Lucca" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Emilia Lucca" ;
    skos:altLabel "Signora Lucca" ;
    skos:altLabel "Emilia Barelli" ;
    ex:description "Emilia Lucca, née Barelli, is a tall and beautiful Italian woman from Posilippo near Naples. She is the daughter of Augusto Barelli, the chief lawyer and once deputy of that area. She fell in love with Gennaro Lucca, who was in her father's employment. When her father forbade the match, they eloped, married at Bari, and sold her jewels to emigrate to America. She lived in New York for four years before fleeing to London to escape Giuseppe Gorgiano and the Red Circle. In London, she is the mysterious lodger hidden in Mrs. Warren's house in Great Orme Street, communicating only through printed slips and receiving coded messages through the Daily Gazette agony column and candle signals from her husband. She is joyful upon discovering Gorgiano is dead and reveals her identity to the police." ;
    ex:nationality "Italian" ;
    ex:birthPlace :posilippo ;
    ex:livesAt :mrsWarrensHouse ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :gennaroLucca ;
    ex:childOf :augustoBarelli ;
    ex:knows :giuseppeGorgiano ;
    ex:knows :titoCastalotte ;
    ex:fleeingFrom :giuseppeGorgiano ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :redCircleDoc .

:maudBellamy a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Maud" ;
    ex:lastName "Bellamy" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Maud Bellamy" ;
    skos:altLabel "Maudie" ;
    skos:altLabel "Miss Bellamy" ;
    ex:description "Maud Bellamy is the daughter of Tom Bellamy of Fulworth, described by Holmes as the beauty of the neighbourhood who would draw attention everywhere, with a perfect clear-cut face and delicate colouring of the downlands. She possesses strong character as well as great beauty. She was secretly engaged to Fitzroy McPherson, keeping the engagement hidden because his dying uncle might disinherit him. She has no mother, with her father and brother William as her only guardians. Ian Murdoch had been an admirer before he understood her relationship with McPherson. She used the nickname 'Maudie' in correspondence." ;
    ex:childOf :tomBellamy ;
    ex:isEngagedTo :fitzroyMcPherson ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes, :haroldStackhurst, :fitzroyMcPherson, :ianMurdoch ;
    ex:livesAt :theHaven ;
    ex:siblingOf :williamBellamy ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :lionsManeDoc .

:mcPhersonUncle a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "McPherson's Uncle" ;
    ex:description "McPherson's uncle is an unnamed elderly man who is said to be very old and dying. Fitzroy McPherson kept his engagement to Maud Bellamy secret because his uncle might have disinherited him if he had married against the uncle's wishes. His name is not given in the text." ;
    ex:hasRelative :fitzroyMcPherson ;
    ex:uncleOf :fitzroyMcPherson ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :lionsManeDoc .

:mercerAgent a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Detective ;
    ex:lastName "Mercer" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Mercer (Holmes's Agent)" ;
    ex:description "Mercer is Sherlock Holmes's general utility man who looks up routine business. Holmes describes him to Watson as 'since your time,' indicating Mercer joined Holmes's network after Watson's departure from Baker Street. Holmes sends Mercer to investigate A. Dorak on the Commercial Road, and Mercer reports back by telegram that Dorak is a suave, elderly Bohemian who keeps a large general store." ;
    ex:occupation "investigator" ;
    ex:employedBy :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :creepingManDoc .

:merivale a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:PoliceOfficer ;
    ex:lastName "Merivale" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Inspector Merivale" ;
    skos:altLabel "Merivale" ;
    ex:description "Inspector Merivale is a police officer at Scotland Yard. He asked Sherlock Holmes to examine the St. Pancras case, in which a cap was found beside a dead policeman. Holmes notes that since he ran down a coiner by the zinc and copper filings in his cuff seam, Scotland Yard has begun to realize the importance of the microscope." ;
    ex:occupation "police inspector" ;
    ex:employedBy :scotlandYard ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :shoscombeOldPlaceDoc .

:michaelStableHand a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:DomesticWorker ;
    ex:firstName "Michael" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Michael" ;
    ex:description "Michael is the stable-hand at Cheeseman's, Lamberley, who sleeps in the house. He is mentioned by Ferguson when listing the inmates of his household. No further details are given in the text." ;
    ex:employedBy :robertFerguson ;
    ex:gender "male" ;
    ex:occupation "stable-hand" ;
    ex:worksAt :cheesemans ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :sussexVampireDoc .

:missStoper a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:lastName "Stoper" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Miss Stoper" ;
    ex:description """Miss Stoper is the manager of Westaway's, a well-known governess employment agency in the West End of London. The agency was founded by Westaway but is managed by Miss Stoper. She sits in her own little office while ladies seeking employment wait in an anteroom. She introduced Violet Hunter to Jephro Rucastle and was sharp-tongued when Violet initially refused the position, suggesting it was useless to keep her name on the books. She later provided Violet's address to Rucastle.""" ;
    ex:occupation "agency manager" ;
    ex:employedBy :westaways ;
    ex:knows :violetHunter, :jephroRucastle ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :copperBeechesDoc .

:mortimerMaberley a ex:FictionalPerson , ex:Client ;
    ex:firstName "Mortimer" ;
    ex:lastName "Maberley" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Mortimer Maberley" ;
    ex:description "Deceased husband of Mary Maberley and father of Douglas Maberley. Was an early client of Sherlock Holmes some years before the Three Gables case." ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :maryMaberley ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:parentOf :douglasMaberley ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :threeGablesDoc .

:mortonOxfordRugby a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:lastName "Morton" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Morton" ;
    ex:description "Oxford rugby player described by Cyril Overton as one of the 'Oxford fliers' who could easily outrun Moorhouse, the Cambridge reserve." ;
    ex:occupation "Rugby footballer" ;
    ex:affiliatedWith :oxfordUniversity ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :missingThreeQuarterDoc .

:mrFowler a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:lastName "Fowler" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Mr. Fowler" ;
    ex:description """Mr. Fowler is Alice Rucastle's suitor and later husband. Described by Holmes as a persevering man and a good seaman. He watched the Copper Beeches from the Southampton Road, hoping to see Alice. When Violet Hunter, wearing Alice's dress, waved him away, he was deceived into thinking Alice no longer wanted his attentions. He subsequently blockaded the house, bribed Mrs. Toller, kept Toller supplied with drink, and arranged a ladder for Alice's escape through the skylight. He married Alice by special license in Southampton the day after their flight and now holds a government appointment in Mauritius.""" ;
    ex:occupation "seaman" ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :aliceRucastle ;
    ex:engagedTo :aliceRucastle ;
    ex:knows :aliceRucastle, :mrsTollerCB, :tollerCB, :jephroRucastle ;
    ex:hasParticipatedIn :escapeOfAliceRucastle, :marriageOfFowlerAndAlice ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :copperBeechesDoc .

:mrKlein a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:lastName "Klein" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Mr. Klein" ;
    ex:description "An aged German sugar king who married Isadora Klein. Now deceased, leaving Isadora as the richest as well as the most lovely widow upon earth." ;
    ex:nationality "German" ;
    ex:occupation "sugar magnate" ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :isadoraKlein ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :threeGablesDoc .

:mrsAmberley a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim ;
    ex:lastName "Amberley" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Mrs. Amberley" ;
    ex:description "Wife of Josiah Amberley, twenty years younger than her husband. Described as good-looking from a photograph. Made wretched by her husband's niggardly ways. Suspected of having an intrigue with Dr. Ray Ernest. Murdered by her husband who gassed her in the strong-room of The Haven. Her first name is not given in the text." ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :josiahAmberley ;
    ex:knows :rayErnest ;
    ex:livesAt :theHavenLewisham ;
    ex:hasParticipantIn :murderAmberleyErnest ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :retiredColourmanDoc .

:mrsFerguson a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim ;
    ex:prefLabel "Mrs. Ferguson" ;
    ex:description "Mrs. Ferguson is the second wife of Robert Ferguson, a Peruvian lady and the daughter of a Peruvian merchant involved in the importation of nitrates. Described as very beautiful with a fiery, tropical, jealous nature, she is nonetheless deeply loving toward her husband. She is accused of vampirism after being caught apparently biting her baby's neck, but in truth she was sucking curare poison from wounds inflicted by her stepson Jack using poisoned arrows from her South American weapons collection. She also attacked Jack in protective anger. She is attended by her loyal maid Dolores and is confined to her room during Holmes's investigation, suffering from high fever and mental distress. Her name is not given in the text." ;
    ex:childOf :mrsFergusonsFather ;
    ex:gender "female" ;
    ex:hasServant :dolores ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :robertFerguson ;
    ex:livesAt :cheesemans ;
    ex:nationality "Peruvian" ;
    ex:parentOf :babyFerguson ;
    ex:stepParentOf :jackFerguson ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :sussexVampireDoc .

:mrsFergusonsFather a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Mrs. Ferguson's Father" ;
    ex:description "The unnamed father of Mrs. Ferguson (Robert Ferguson's second wife). He is a Peruvian merchant involved in the importation of nitrates. Ferguson met his future wife through business connections with this merchant. His name is not given in the text." ;
    ex:gender "male" ;
    ex:nationality "Peruvian" ;
    ex:occupation "merchant (nitrates importation)" ;
    ex:parentOf :mrsFerguson ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :sussexVampireDoc .

:mrsMason a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:DomesticWorker ;
    ex:lastName "Mason" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Mrs. Mason" ;
    ex:description "Mrs. Mason is the nurse caring for the Ferguson baby at Cheeseman's, Lamberley. She is described as a tall, gaunt woman, sour and silent in manner but with a heart of gold and devoted to the child. She discovered Mrs. Ferguson apparently biting the baby's neck and was horrified, accepting five pounds for her silence. She later told Ferguson what she had seen. She swore not to leave the baby night or day. Mrs. Ferguson eventually confided the truth to Mrs. Mason, who knew the wife was sucking poison from the wound." ;
    ex:employedBy :robertFerguson ;
    ex:gender "female" ;
    ex:occupation "nurse" ;
    ex:worksAt :cheesemans ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :sussexVampireDoc .

:mrsMerrilow a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Landlady ;
    ex:lastName "Merrilow" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Mrs. Merrilow" ;
    ex:description "Mrs. Merrilow is an elderly, motherly, buxom woman of the landlady type who lives in South Brixton. She has been the landlady of Mrs. Eugenia Ronder for seven years. She came to Holmes when her lodger's health began failing and she heard Mrs. Ronder crying 'Murder!' in the night. She is anxious not to lose her valuable lodger." ;
    ex:occupation "landlady" ;
    ex:livesAt :mrsMerrilowHouse ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes, :johnWatson, :eugeniaRonder ;
    ex:hasLodger :eugeniaRonder ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :veiledLodgerDoc .

:mrsRucastle a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Mrs. Rucastle" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mrs. Jephro Rucastle" ;
    ex:description """Mrs. Rucastle is the second wife of Jephro Rucastle, not more than thirty years old while her husband is about forty-five. They have been married about seven years. She is a silent, pale-faced woman described as colourless in mind as well as feature. She is passionately devoted to both her husband and her little son Edward, with light grey eyes that wander continually between them. She has some secret sorrow and is often lost in deep thought with a sad look, sometimes found in tears. She has no sense of humour. She noticed Violet using a mirror to see Mr. Fowler on the road and alerted her husband.""" ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :jephroRucastle ;
    ex:parentOf :edwardRucastle ;
    ex:knows :violetHunter, :jephroRucastle ;
    ex:livesAt :copperBeeches ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :copperBeechesDoc .

:mrsSaunders a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Servant ;
    ex:lastName "Saunders" ;
    ex:title "Mrs." ;
    ex:prefLabel "Mrs. Saunders" ;
    ex:description "The caretaker or charwoman at 136 Little Ryder Street. She works in the basement up until four o'clock and has a key to the premises. She admitted Holmes and Watson to Nathan Garrideb's rooms on the afternoon of the confrontation with Killer Evans." ;
    ex:occupation "caretaker" ;
    ex:employedAt :136LittleRyderStreet ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :threeGarridebsDoc .

:mrSutro a ex:FictionalPerson , ex:Lawyer ;
    ex:lastName "Sutro" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Mr. Sutro" ;
    skos:altLabel "Sutro" ;
    ex:description "Lawyer to Mrs. Mary Maberley, living in Harrow. A gray old gentleman. Identified a problematic clause in the house purchase agreement that would have prevented Mrs. Maberley from taking any possessions out of the house. Sent a telegram to Holmes informing him of the burglary at The Three Gables." ;
    ex:occupation "lawyer" ;
    ex:knows :maryMaberley , :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:livesAt :harrow ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :threeGablesDoc .

:mrsTollerCB a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Mrs. Toller" ;
    ex:description """Mrs. Toller is the wife of Toller and a servant at the Copper Beeches. She is a very tall and strong woman with a sour face, as silent as Mrs. Rucastle and much less amiable. She was locked in the wine-cellar by Violet Hunter to facilitate Holmes's investigation. After being released by Rucastle, she revealed the full truth about Alice's imprisonment: that Alice had rights by will, refused to sign them over, was kept prisoner after developing brain-fever, and that Violet was hired to impersonate her. She was sympathetic to Alice and was bribed by Mr. Fowler to assist in the escape.""" ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :tollerCB ;
    ex:employedBy :jephroRucastle ;
    ex:knows :aliceRucastle, :mrFowler, :violetHunter, :jephroRucastle, :mrsRucastle ;
    ex:hasParticipatedIn :escapeOfAliceRucastle, :copperBeechesInvestigation ;
    ex:livesAt :copperBeeches ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :copperBeechesDoc .

:nathanGarridebBrother a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Nathan Garrideb's Brother" ;
    ex:description "The deceased brother of Nathan Garrideb. Nathan mentions that he had a brother but he is dead. No name is given in the text." ;
    ex:siblingOf :nathanGarrideb ;
    ex:deceased "true" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :threeGarridebsDoc .

:nathanGarrideb a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Nathan" ;
    ex:lastName "Garrideb" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Nathan Garrideb" ;
    ex:description "An elderly reclusive collector and antiquarian living at 136 Little Ryder Street, London. Very tall, loose-jointed, round-backed person, gaunt and bald, some sixty-odd years of age, with a cadaverous face, large round spectacles, and a small projecting goat's beard. His room resembled a small museum filled with geological and anatomical specimens, butterflies, moths, ancient coins, flint instruments, fossil bones, plaster skulls, and a powerful microscope. He occasionally visited Sotheby's or Christie's but otherwise seldom left his room. He had a deceased brother and female relatives only. He was duped by Killer Evans's elaborate Three Garridebs scheme, believing he stood to inherit five million dollars from the estate of Alexander Hamilton Garrideb. After the scheme was exposed, he never recovered from the shock of his dissipated dreams and was last heard of at a nursing-home in Brixton, having lost his reason." ;
    ex:occupation "collector and antiquarian" ;
    ex:livesAt :136LittleRyderStreet ;
    ex:owns :nathanGarridebCollection ;
    ex:knows :killerEvans ;
    ex:knows :mrsSaunders ;
