:professorMorphy a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Morphy" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Professor Morphy" ;
    skos:altLabel "Morphy" ;
    ex:description "Professor Morphy is a colleague of Professor Presbury at Camford, holding the chair of comparative anatomy. He is the father of Alice Morphy. He raised no objection to Presbury's suit for his daughter, as Presbury was rich." ;
    ex:occupation "professor of comparative anatomy" ;
    ex:worksAt :camfordUniversityOrg ;
    ex:parentOf :aliceMorphy ;
    ex:hasColleague :professorPresbury ;
    ex:knows :professorPresbury ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :creepingManDoc .

:professorPresbury a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Physiologist, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Presbury" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Professor Presbury" ;
    skos:altLabel "Presbury" ;
    ex:description "Professor Presbury is a famous Camford physiologist aged sixty-one with a European reputation. He is a widower with one daughter, Edith. Described as rich, virile, positive, and combative in character. Portly, large-featured, grave, tall, and frock-coated with keen, observant, cunning eyes behind large horn glasses. He became engaged to the young Alice Morphy, daughter of his colleague Professor Morphy. Driven by desire to appear younger, he secretly traveled to Prague for a fortnight where he arranged to receive rejuvenation serum from H. Lowenstein, derived from black-faced langur monkey. The serum was supplied through A. Dorak on Commercial Road, London. After taking the serum on a nine-day cycle, Presbury exhibited simian behavior including crawling on hands and feet, climbing the ivy-covered wall of his house with incredible agility, and developing thick horny knuckles. His wolfhound Roy detected the change and attacked him repeatedly. During the final observed episode, Roy broke free and bit Presbury seriously in the throat near the carotid artery. He survived after Watson and Bennett dressed the wound." ;
    ex:occupation "physiologist, university professor" ;
    ex:age 61 ;
    ex:livesAt :presburyHouse ;
    ex:worksAt :camfordUniversityOrg ;
    ex:parentOf :edithPresbury ;
    ex:hasFiancee :aliceMorphy ;
    ex:hasColleague :professorMorphy ;
    ex:hasAssistant :trevorBennett ;
    ex:owns :roy ;
    ex:owns :presburyWoodenBox ;
    ex:knows :professorMorphy ;
    ex:knows :lowenstein ;
    ex:knows :dorak ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :creepingManDoc .

:rayErnest a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Doctor, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Ray" ;
    ex:lastName "Ernest" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Dr. Ray Ernest" ;
    ex:description "Young unmarried doctor living near Josiah Amberley at Lewisham. A chess player who was frequently in the Amberley house. Suspected of having an intrigue with Mrs. Amberley. Murdered by Josiah Amberley who gassed him in the strong-room. Before dying, he wrote 'We we--' on the wall with a purple indelible pencil, apparently trying to write 'We were murdered.' His family later engaged the private detective Mr. Barker to investigate." ;
    ex:occupation "doctor" ;
    ex:knows :josiahAmberley ;
    ex:knows :mrsAmberley ;
    ex:livesAt :lewisham ;
    ex:hasParticipantIn :murderAmberleyErnest ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :retiredColourmanDoc .

:robertFerguson a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Client ;
    ex:firstName "Robert" ;
    ex:lastName "Ferguson" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Robert Ferguson" ;
    skos:altLabel "Big Bob Ferguson" ;
    skos:altLabel "Bob Ferguson" ;
    ex:description "Robert Ferguson, known as 'Big Bob Ferguson,' is a tea broker at Ferguson and Muirhead of Mincing Lane, London. A former Rugby three-quarter for Richmond, he is described as once having a great frame and fine turn of speed, though now aged with scanty flaxen hair and bowed shoulders. He married twice: his first wife is deceased, leaving a son Jack, and his second wife is a Peruvian lady whom he married about five years before the events of the story. He lives at Cheeseman's, an ancient farmhouse in Lamberley, Sussex. He consults Holmes about his second wife's apparent vampirism, which is in fact her sucking poison from their baby's wound." ;
    ex:employedBy :fergusonAndMuirhead ;
    ex:hasLawyer :morrisonMorrisonAndDodd ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :mrsFerguson ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:knows :johnWatson ;
    ex:livesAt :cheesemans ;
    ex:occupation "tea broker" ;
    ex:owns :carlo ;
    ex:parentOf :jackFerguson ;
    ex:parentOf :babyFerguson ;
    ex:clientOf :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :sussexVampireDoc .

:robertNorberton a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Baronet, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "Robert" ;
    ex:lastName "Norberton" ;
    ex:title "Sir" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Sir Robert Norberton" ;
    skos:altLabel "Sir Robert" ;
    skos:altLabel "Norberton" ;
    ex:description "Sir Robert Norberton is a baronet who lives at Shoscombe Old Place with his widowed sister Lady Beatrice Falder. He is described as the most daredevil rider in England, having finished second in the Grand National. He is deeply in debt and is considered a dangerous man. He once horsewhipped Sam Brewer, the Curzon Street money-lender, on Newmarket Heath, nearly killing him. He enters his horse Shoscombe Prince in the Derby and stakes everything on the outcome. When his sister dies of dropsy, he conceals her death with the help of her maid Carrie Evans and her husband Norlett, an actor who impersonates Lady Beatrice. He hides the body first in the old well-house and then in the family crypt. Shoscombe Prince wins the Derby, netting Sir Robert eighty thousand pounds in bets, and he receives lenient treatment from the police and coroner." ;
    ex:occupation "sporting gentleman" ;
    ex:livesAt :shoscombeOldPlace ;
    ex:siblingOf :beatriceFalder ;
    ex:owns :shoscombePrince, :shoscombePrinceHalfBrother ;
    ex:debtorOf :samBrewer ;
    ex:employs :johnMason, :sandyBain, :harvey, :stephensButler ;
    ex:knows :carrieEvans, :norlett ;
    ex:hasParticipantIn :shoscombeInvestigation, :brewerHorsewhipping, :concealmentOfDeath, :cryptConfrontation, :gunRoomConfession ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :shoscombeOldPlaceDoc .

:rodgerPrescott a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "Rodger" ;
    ex:lastName "Prescott" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Rodger Prescott" ;
    skos:altLabel "Waldron" ;
    ex:description "A famous forger and coiner from Chicago who lived in London under the alias Waldron at 136 Little Ryder Street. He was a tall, dark man with a beard. He operated a counterfeiting press hidden in a secret cellar beneath his rooms, producing notes indistinguishable from Bank of England currency. He was shot and killed by Killer Evans in a night-club on the Waterloo Road in January 1895 during a card game. Prescott was identified as the aggressor in the altercation. His counterfeiting equipment remained hidden in the cellar until Evans's scheme to recover it was foiled by Holmes." ;
    ex:occupation "forger and coiner" ;
    ex:nationality "American" ;
    ex:birthPlace :chicago ;
    ex:livesAt :136LittleRyderStreet ;
    ex:owns :prescottCounterfeitingPress ;
    ex:deceased "true" ;
    ex:knows :killerEvans ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :threeGarridebsDoc .

:ronder a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim, ex:Showman ;
    ex:lastName "Ronder" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Ronder" ;
    ex:description "Ronder is a showman and owner of Ronder's Wild Beast Show, described as a rival of Wombwell and Sanger and one of the greatest showmen of his day. He is described as a huge, porcine person with a dreadful face resembling a human wild boar, with small vicious eyes and a heavy-jowled face. He was a ruffian, bully, and beast who took to drink and became horrible in his cups. He deserted his wife for others, tied her down and lashed her with a riding-whip, and was frequently had up for assault and cruelty to beasts. He was murdered at Abbas Parva when Leonardo struck his skull with a five-clawed club, though the inquest returned a verdict of death from misadventure, attributing his death to the lion Sahara King." ;
    ex:gender "male" ;
    ex:occupation "showman" ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :eugeniaRonder ;
    ex:owns :rondersWildBeastShow ;
    ex:hasParticipatedIn :abbasParvaIncident ;
    ex:killedBy :leonardo ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :veiledLodgerDoc .

