:sergeantCoventry a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:PoliceOfficer ;
    ex:lastName "Coventry" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Sergeant Coventry" ;
    ex:description "Sergeant Coventry is a local police sergeant who first examined the Thor Bridge affair. He is tall, thin, and cadaverous, with a secretive and mysterious manner that conveys the idea he knows more than he dares say. He has a trick of suddenly sinking his voice to a whisper. Behind these mannerisms he is a decent, honest fellow not too proud to admit he is out of his depth. He prefers Holmes to Scotland Yard. His humble cottage serves as the local police station, half a mile from the Thor Place estate." ;
    ex:occupation "police sergeant" ;
    ex:rank "Sergeant" ;
    ex:livesAt :coventryCottage ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:knows :johnWatson ;
    ex:knows :neilGibson ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :thorBridgeDoc .

