:eustaceBrackenstall a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim, ex:Baronet ;
    ex:firstName "Eustace" ;
    ex:lastName "Brackenstall" ;
    ex:title "Sir" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Sir Eustace Brackenstall" ;
    skos:altLabel "Sir Eustace" ;
    ex:description """Wealthy baronet of Abbey Grange, Marsham, Kent. One of the richest men in Kent. Described as about forty years of age, tall, well-made, with dark handsome aquiline features and a short black beard. A confirmed drunkard who was a perfect fiend when half drunk. Cruel to his wife Lady Brackenstall (née Mary Fraser) - once drenched her dog with petroleum and set it on fire, threw a decanter at the maid Theresa Wright, and stabbed his wife's arm with a hat-pin. Killed by Captain Jack Croker with his own poker after striking Lady Brackenstall with his blackthorn cudgel. Found dead on the tiger-skin hearthrug in the dining room, wearing an embroidered night-shirt and trousers.""" ;
    ex:occupation "Baronet" ;
    ex:physicalAppearance "About forty, tall, well-made, dark handsome aquiline features, short black beard, white teeth" ;
    ex:causeOfDeath "Struck on the head with a poker by Captain Jack Croker" ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :maryFraser ;
    ex:livesAt :abbeyGrange ;
    ex:killedBy :jackCroker ;
