:femaleSearcherSY a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Female Searcher at Scotland Yard" ;
    ex:description "An unnamed woman at Scotland Yard who conducted the physical search of Mrs. Tangey. She reported that no signs of the papers were found on Mrs. Tangey." ;
    ex:employedBy :scotlandYard ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :navalTreatyDoc .

:forbes a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Detective ;
    ex:lastName "Forbes" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Forbes" ;
    ex:description "A Scotland Yard detective assigned to investigate the theft of the naval treaty from the Foreign Office. Holmes describes him as tolerably smart but having no imagination. He focused his investigation on Mrs. Tangey and failed to recover the treaty.  Also described as a small, foxy man with a sharp but by no means amiable expression. Decidedly frigid toward Holmes initially, accusing him of using police information and taking credit. Holmes called him young and inexperienced. He shadowed Tangey the commissionaire and Charles Gorot for nine weeks without result. He set one of his female agents on Mrs. Tangey. He came out to Briarbrae when Phelps wired him. Holmes wired full particulars to Forbes after recovering the treaty." ;
    ex:occupation "police detective" ;
    ex:memberOf :scotlandYard ;
    ex:investigates :navalTreatyInvestigation ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:knows :johnWatson ;
    ex:knows :percyPhelps ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :navalTreatyDoc .

:foreignPotentateSecondStain a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Noble ;
    ex:prefLabel "Foreign Potentate (Second Stain)" ;
    skos:altLabel "the foreign potentate" ;
    skos:altLabel "the indiscreet Sovereign" ;
    ex:description "An unnamed foreign potentate who wrote the provocative diplomatic letter that is the centre of the case. Ruffled by recent Colonial developments of Britain. Wrote the letter hurriedly and on his own responsibility; his Ministers know nothing. Holmes deduced his identity and wrote the name on a slip of paper. Described as having acted in an indiscreet and hot-headed manner. A cipher telegram was sent to him about the loss. The publication of his letter would be a greater blow to him and his country than to Britain." ;
    ex:occupation "foreign sovereign" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :secondStainDoc .

:forestRowVicar a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Vicar of Forest Row" ;
    skos:altLabel "the old vicar" ;
    ex:description "The old vicar near Woodman's Lee who called upon Peter Carey to remonstrate with him upon his conduct and was savagely assaulted. Carey was summoned for the assault. Name not given in text." ;
    ex:occupation "vicar" ;
    ex:livesAt :forestRow ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :blackPeterDoc .

:fortescueExamPrinter a ex:FictionalPerson ;
