    ex:description """General de Merville is known for his service at the Khyber. Once a strong soldier, he is now a broken, demoralized, weak, doddering old man, utterly incapable of contending with Baron Gruner. He is the father of Violet de Merville and lives at 104 Berkeley Square. He arranges for Holmes and Kitty Winter to visit Violet at his home. He may have been the one to show the incriminating book to Violet to break off the engagement.""" ;
