:gennaroLucca a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "Gennaro" ;
    ex:lastName "Lucca" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Gennaro Lucca" ;
    ex:description "Gennaro Lucca is an Italian man from Posilippo near Naples who was employed by Augusto Barelli. He fell in love with and married Emilia Barelli against her father's wishes, eloping to Bari for the wedding and then emigrating to America. In New York, he saved Tito Castalotte from ruffians in the Bowery and was rewarded with employment at Castalotte and Zamba, becoming head of a department. In his youth, he joined the Red Circle, a Neapolitan secret society. When Gorgiano arrived in New York and reactivated the society, Gennaro was drawn back in. At a Red Circle meeting, he drew the fatal disc requiring him to murder Castalotte with dynamite. Instead, he warned Castalotte, informed the police, and fled with Emilia to London. He arranged for Emilia to hide at Mrs. Warren's house while he communicated with her through the Daily Gazette agony column and candle signals. He killed Giuseppe Gorgiano by stabbing him in the throat when Gorgiano found him at the Howe Street flats." ;
    ex:occupation "head of department at Castalotte and Zamba" ;
    ex:nationality "Italian" ;
    ex:birthPlace :posilippo ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :emiliaLucca ;
    ex:memberOf :theRedCircle ;
    ex:employedBy :castalotteAndZamba ;
    ex:knows :giuseppeGorgiano ;
    ex:knows :titoCastalotte ;
    ex:knows :augustoBarelli ;
    ex:rescued :titoCastalotte ;
    ex:killed :giuseppeGorgiano ;
    ex:initiatedBy :giuseppeGorgiano ;
    ex:fleeingFrom :giuseppeGorgiano ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :redCircleDoc .

