    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :devilsFootDoc .

:gilchrist a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Student, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:lastName "Gilchrist" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Gilchrist" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Gilchrist" ;
    ex:description "Student at the College of St. Luke's, occupying the first floor room above Soames on the same staircase. A fine figure of a man — tall, flaxen-haired, slim, lithe, and agile with a springy step, pleasant open face, and troubled blue eyes. Fine scholar and athlete: plays Rugby and cricket for the college, won his Blue for hurdles and the long jump. Son of the notorious Sir Jabez Gilchrist, who ruined himself on the turf; left very poor but hard-working and industrious. While returning from athletic practice carrying his spiked jumping shoes, he saw the exam proofs through Soames's window (being tall enough to see the central table), entered using Bannister's accidentally-left key, and began copying the proofs. When Soames returned unexpectedly via the side gate, Gilchrist fled to the bedroom, leaving gloves on the chair and clay from his shoes on the desk. Confessed after Holmes's deduction. Had already written a letter to Soames declining to sit the examination, having accepted a commission in the Rhodesian Police and planning to go to South Africa." ;
    ex:occupation "University student" ;
    ex:height "Tall, over six feet" ;
    ex:sport "Rugby, cricket, hurdles, long jump" ;
    ex:childOf :sirJabezGilchrist ;
    ex:knows :hiltonSoames ;
    ex:knows :bannisterServant ;
    ex:knows :daulatRas ;
    ex:knows :milesMcLaren ;
    ex:livesAt :gilchristsRoom ;
    ex:attendsInstitution :collegeOfStLukes ;
    ex:playsFor :stLukesRugbyTeam ;
    ex:playsFor :stLukesCricketTeam ;
    ex:confessedTo :fortescueExamTampering ;
    ex:memberOf :rhodesianPolice ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :threeStudentsDoc .

:giuseppeGorgiano a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Giuseppe" ;
    ex:lastName "Gorgiano" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Giuseppe Gorgiano" ;
    skos:altLabel "Black Gorgiano" ;
    skos:altLabel "Death" ;
    ex:description "Giuseppe Gorgiano, known as 'Black Gorgiano' and 'Death' in the south of Italy, is an enormous man from Posilippo near Naples. He is a leader of the Red Circle, a Neapolitan secret society, and is responsible for at least fifty murders. He is described as grotesque, gigantic, and terrifying with a thunderous voice and blazing eyes. He came to New York to avoid the Italian police and established a branch of the Red Circle there. He initiated Gennaro Lucca into the society in Naples and later assaulted Emilia Lucca in her home, declaring his love for her before being attacked by Gennaro. He orchestrated a plot to murder Tito Castalotte with dynamite after Castalotte refused to pay blackmail. He tracked the Luccas to London and was killed by Gennaro Lucca, who stabbed him in the throat with a knife in a flat on Howe Street. He was found dead on the floor with a knife with a white haft in his throat, a horn-handled dagger beside his right hand, and a black kid glove nearby. He was clean-shaven and swarthy-faced." ;
    ex:nationality "Italian" ;
    ex:aliasName "Black Gorgiano" ;
    ex:birthPlace :posilippo ;
    ex:memberOf :theRedCircle ;
    ex:knows :gennaroLucca ;
    ex:knows :emiliaLucca ;
    ex:killedBy :gennaroLucca ;
    ex:assaulted :emiliaLucca ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :redCircleDoc .

:gloucesterRoadOfficial a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Gloucester Road Station Official" ;
    ex:description "Unnamed very helpful official at Gloucester Road Station who walked with Holmes along the track and confirmed that the back windows of Caulfield Gardens open on the Underground line and that trains frequently halt there." ;
    ex:occupation "railway official" ;
