:godfreyStaunton a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Godfrey" ;
    ex:lastName "Staunton" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Godfrey Staunton" ;
    skos:altLabel "the crack three-quarter" ;
    ex:description "Star three-quarter for Cambridge, Blackheath, and five Internationals. An orphan and heir to his uncle Lord Mount-James, one of the richest men in England. About a year before the story, lodged in London and secretly married his landlady's daughter to preserve his inheritance from his miserly uncle. His wife fell ill with virulent consumption. Disappeared from Bentley's Hotel the night before the Varsity match after receiving a note from his father-in-law about his wife's worsening condition. Found kneeling at his dead wife's bedside in a cottage near Trumpington." ;
    ex:occupation "Rugby footballer" ;
    ex:affiliatedWith :cambridgeUniversityRugbyTeam ;
