:godfreyStauntonWife a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim ;
    ex:prefLabel "Godfrey Staunton's Wife" ;
    ex:description "Unnamed young woman, daughter of Godfrey Staunton's London landlady. Described as good, beautiful, and intelligent. Had calm pale face, wide-opened blue eyes, and golden hair. Secretly married Godfrey Staunton about a year before the story. Fell ill with virulent consumption (tuberculosis) and was kept in a lonely cottage near Trumpington under Dr. Armstrong's care. Died by the time Holmes and Watson reached the cottage. Her name is not given in the text." ;
