:henryPeters a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:prefLabel "Henry Peters" ;
    ex:firstName "Henry" ;
    ex:lastName "Peters" ;
    skos:altLabel "Holy Peters" ;
    skos:altLabel "Rev. Dr. Shlessinger" ;
    skos:altLabel "Dr. Shlessinger" ;
    skos:altLabel "Peters" ;
    ex:description "Henry Peters, known as Holy Peters, is one of the most unscrupulous rascals that Australia has ever produced. He is from Adelaide, where he was badly bitten in a saloon fight in 1889, leaving his left ear jagged or torn. His specialty is beguiling lonely ladies by playing upon their religious feelings. He posed as the Rev. Dr. Shlessinger, a missionary from South America recovering from a disease contracted in apostolic duties. He is big, clean-shaven, bald-headed, with a large red face, pendulous cheeks, and a cruel vicious mouth, with a superficial air of benevolence. He and his accomplice Annie Fraser (posing as his wife Mrs. Shlessinger) lured Lady Frances Carfax to London, held her prisoner, stole her jewellery, and attempted to bury her alive in an oversized coffin alongside the body of Rose Spender. He pawned Lady Frances's Spanish pendants at Bovington's." ;
    ex:nationality "Australian" ;
    ex:hasPhysicalFeature "jagged or torn left ear from saloon fight in Adelaide in 1889; big, clean-shaven, bald-headed, large red face, pendulous cheeks, cruel vicious mouth" ;
    ex:knows :annieFraser, :ladyFrancesCarfax, :roseSpender ;
    ex:livesAt :36PoultneySq ;
    ex:partnerOf :annieFraser ;
    ex:from :adelaide ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :disappearanceLadyFrancesCarfaxDoc .

