    ex:description "Tutor and lecturer at the College of St. Luke's. A tall, spare man of nervous and excitable temperament. One of the examiners for the Fortescue Scholarship; his subject is Greek. Discovered that someone had tampered with the examination proofs (a passage of Thucydides) that had been left on his desk while he was at tea. Engaged Holmes to investigate discreetly to avoid scandal to the college and university." ;
