:jackCroker a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Sailor, ex:Captain ;
    ex:firstName "Jack" ;
    ex:lastName "Croker" ;
    ex:title "Captain" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Captain Jack Croker" ;
    skos:altLabel "Captain Croker" ;
    skos:altLabel "Jack Croker" ;
    ex:description """A very tall young man, golden-moustached, blue-eyed, with skin burned by tropical suns and a springy step. Described as six foot three in height, active as a squirrel, dexterous with his fingers, and remarkably quick-witted. Formerly first officer of the Rock of Gibraltar, now captain of the new ship Bass Rock, sailing from Southampton. Lives at Sydenham with his people. Met Mary Fraser on her voyage from Australia in June 1895 and fell deeply in love with her. After learning from Theresa Wright of Sir Eustace's cruelty, visited Abbey Grange on the night of the murder. When Sir Eustace struck Mary with a stick, Croker seized the poker and killed him. Cut the bell-rope with a knife, tied Mary to a chair, staged a burglary by taking silver (dumped in the pond), and escaped. Summoned by Holmes's telegram to Baker Street, confessed everything, and was acquitted in Holmes's mock trial. His record in the fleet was described as magnificent - loyal, honest, and kind-hearted, though hot-headed and excitable off duty.""" ;
    ex:occupation "Ship captain" ;
    ex:physicalAppearance "Very tall, golden-moustached, blue-eyed, skin burned by tropical suns, springy step, huge frame" ;
    ex:height "Six foot three" ;
    ex:livesAt :sydenham ;
    ex:killed :eustaceBrackenstall ;
    ex:inLoveWith :maryFraser ;
    ex:captainOf :bassRock ;
    ex:firstOfficerOf :rockOfGibraltar ;
    ex:knows :maryFraser ;
    ex:knows :theresaWright ;
    ex:knows :eustaceBrackenstall ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:knows :johnWatson ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :abbeyGrangeDoc .

