:jamesDamery a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "James" ;
    ex:lastName "Damery" ;
    ex:title "Sir" ;
    ex:militaryRank "Colonel" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Sir James Damery" ;
    skos:altLabel "Colonel Sir James Damery" ;
    skos:altLabel "Colonel Damery" ;
    ex:description """Sir James Damery is a Colonel and a man of the world with a natural turn for diplomacy. He is large, bluff, and honest with a broad, clean-shaven face, gray Irish eyes, and a pleasant mellow voice. He is meticulous in his dress, wearing a lucent top-hat, dark frock-coat, pearl pin in black satin cravat, and lavender spats. He has a reputation for arranging delicate matters to be kept out of the papers, including negotiations with Sir George Lewis over the Hammerford Will case. He acts as intermediary for an unnamed illustrious client to engage Holmes in preventing Baron Gruner's marriage to Violet de Merville. He is a member of the Carlton Club with private telephone call XX.31. He provides the Ming saucer from his client's collection and ultimately takes away both the saucer and Gruner's incriminating book.""" ;
    ex:telephoneNumber "XX.31" ;
    ex:memberOf :carltonClub ;
    ex:intermediaryFor :illustriousClient ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:knows :johnWatson ;
    ex:knows :illustriousClient ;
    ex:knows :generalDeMerville ;
