:jamesDodd a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Stockbroker, ex:Soldier ;
    ex:firstName "James" ;
    ex:lastName "Dodd" ;
    ex:prefLabel "James M. Dodd" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Dodd" ;
    skos:altLabel "Jimmie" ;
    ex:description "James M. Dodd is a big, fresh, sunburned, upstanding Briton with blue eyes and a square jaw. He is a stockbroker from Throgmorton Street in London. He served in the Imperial Yeomanry, Middlesex Corps, during the Boer War, joining in January 1901. He formed a close friendship with Godfrey Emsworth during their service together. After Godfrey's mysterious disappearance following the war, Dodd visited Tuxbury Old Park to investigate and eventually engaged Sherlock Holmes to help find his friend." ;
    ex:occupation "stockbroker" ;
    ex:friendOf :godfreyEmsworth ;
