:jimBrowner a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal, ex:Steward ;
    ex:firstName "Jim" ;
    ex:lastName "Browner" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Jim Browner" ;
    skos:altLabel "James Browner" ;
    skos:altLabel "Jim" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Browner" ;
    ex:description "James Browner. Steward. Married to Mary. Formerly on South American line, transferred to Liverpool and London boats. Ship: May Day (Liverpool, Dublin, and London Steam Packet Company). Big, powerful, clean-shaven, very swarthy. Compared to Aldrige. Took temperance pledge (blue ribbon) then broke it. Impulsive, strong passions. Murdered Mary and Alec Fairbairn near New Brighton with oak stick. Cut off ears, sent them to Sarah from Belfast. Arrested at Albert Dock by Lestrade. Confession taken at Shadwell Police Station before Inspector Montgomery." ;
    ex:gender "male" ;
    ex:occupation "steward" ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :maryBrowner ;
