:johnHectorMcFarlane a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Suspect ;
    ex:firstName "John Hector" ;
    ex:lastName "McFarlane" ;
    ex:prefLabel "John Hector McFarlane" ;
    ex:description "Young solicitor, junior partner at Graham and McFarlane, 426 Gresham Buildings E.C. About 27 years old, flaxen-haired, handsome. Accused of murdering Jonas Oldacre. Visited Oldacre at Deep Dene House to discuss a will leaving Oldacre's property to him. Was followed from London Bridge Station. Stayed overnight at the Anerley Arms. Arrested by Lestrade at Baker Street. Ultimately exonerated when Oldacre found alive." ;
    ex:occupation "solicitor" ;
    ex:age "27" ;
    ex:accusedOf :oldacreFakedMurder ;
    ex:childOf :mrsMcFarlaneNorwood ;
    ex:employedBy :grahamAndMcFarlane ;
    ex:knows :jonasOldacre ;
    ex:knows :graham ;
    ex:staysAt :anerleyArms ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :norwoodBuilderDoc .

:johnMitton a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Valet ;
    ex:firstName "John" ;
    ex:lastName "Mitton" ;
    ex:prefLabel "John Mitton" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mitton" ;
    ex:description "Valet to Eduardo Lucas. Was out visiting a friend at Hammersmith on the night of the murder. Arrested as a suspect but released when his alibi was confirmed complete. Started home at an hour that should have brought him to Westminster before the crime was discovered, but explained he walked part of the way. Arrived at twelve o'clock. Appeared overwhelmed by the tragedy. Always on good terms with his master. Several of Lucas's possessions including a small case of razors found in his boxes, explained as presents. In Lucas's employment for three years. Not taken on the Continent with Lucas. Left in charge of the Godolphin Street house when Lucas visited Paris." ;
    ex:occupation "valet" ;
    ex:livesAt :16GodolphinStreet ;
    ex:employedBy :eduardoLucas ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :secondStainDoc .

:johnNeligan a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Suspect ;
    ex:firstName "John" ;
    ex:middleName "Hopley" ;
    ex:lastName "Neligan" ;
    ex:prefLabel "John Hopley Neligan" ;
    skos:altLabel "Neligan" ;
    skos:altLabel "young Neligan" ;
    ex:description "A young man of about twenty years of age, frail and thin with a black moustache which intensified the deadly pallor of his face. Son of the absconding banker of Dawson and Neligan. Was only ten when his father disappeared in 1883. Arrived at the Brambletye Hotel on the day of Peter Carey's murder on the pretence of playing golf, with a ground-floor room. Attempted twice to break into Carey's cabin to examine the Sea Unicorn's log-books for August 1883, hoping to learn his father's fate. Caught during the second attempt by Holmes, Watson, and Hopkins. His notebook with initials J.H.N. and securities listings was found blood-stained at the crime scene. Arrested by Hopkins but later released on Holmes's insistence as innocent." ;
    ex:childOf :neliganSenior, :neliganMother ;
    ex:owns :neliganNotebook ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :blackPeterDoc .

:johnScottEccles a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "John" ;
    ex:lastName "Scott Eccles" ;
    ex:prefLabel "John Scott Eccles" ;
    skos:altLabel "Scott Eccles" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Scott Eccles" ;
    ex:description "A bachelor of conventional British respectability who lives at Popham House, Lee. A Conservative, churchman, and good citizen. Met Aloysius Garcia at the table of the retired brewer Melville. Was invited to stay at Wisteria Lodge as Garcia's guest, intended as an unwitting alibi. Found the house deserted the next morning and sought Holmes's advice. Became a suspect briefly when Garcia was found murdered." ;
    ex:occupation "gentleman" ;
    ex:livesAt :pophamHouse ;
    ex:knows :aloysiusGarcia ;
    ex:knows :melville ;
