:kittyWinter a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "Kitty" ;
    ex:lastName "Winter" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Kitty Winter" ;
    skos:altLabel "Miss Kitty Winter" ;
    skos:altLabel "Miss Winter" ;
    skos:altLabel "Miss W." ;
    ex:description """Kitty Winter is a slim, flame-like young woman with a pale, intense face, youthful yet worn with sin and sorrow that leave their leprous mark upon her. She is a former mistress of Baron Gruner who was used and ruined by him. She is filled with intense hatred for Gruner and is determined to see him destroyed. She is an old mate of Shinwell Johnson. She tells Holmes about Gruner's brown leather book cataloguing the women he has ruined. She accompanies Holmes to visit Violet de Merville at 104 Berkeley Square, where she makes a passionate but unsuccessful appeal. She throws vitriol (sulphuric acid) at Baron Gruner through the window of Vernon Lodge during Holmes's burglary, horribly disfiguring him. She is charged with vitriol-throwing and receives the lowest possible sentence due to extenuating circumstances.""" ;
    ex:formerMistressOf :adelbertGruner ;
    ex:perpetratorOf :vitriolAttackOnGruner ;
    ex:knows :shinwellJohnson ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:knows :adelbertGruner ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :illustriousClientDoc .

:klopman a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:lastName "Klopman" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Klopman" ;
    ex:description "A Nihilist who attempted to murder Count Von und Zu Grafenstein. Was thwarted by Sherlock Holmes." ;
    ex:occupation "Nihilist" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :hisLastBowDoc .

:ladyEvaBrackwell a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Debutante, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Eva" ;
    ex:lastName "Brackwell" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Lady Eva Brackwell" ;
    skos:altLabel "Lady Eva" ;
    ex:description "Holmes's client, described as the most beautiful debutante of last season. She is to be married in a fortnight to the Earl of Dovercourt. Milverton possesses several imprudent letters she wrote to an impecunious young squire in the country. The letters are described as 'sprightly' but not worse than imprudent. She is not a wealthy woman; two thousand pounds would drain her resources. Holmes is commissioned to negotiate with Milverton on her behalf." ;
    ex:clientOf :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:engagedTo :earlOfDovercourt ;
    ex:blackmailedBy :charlesAugustusMilverton ;
    ex:engagedTo :colonelDorking ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :milvertonDoc .

:ladyFrancesCarfax a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim, ex:Aristocrat ;
    ex:prefLabel "Lady Frances Carfax" ;
    ex:firstName "Frances" ;
    ex:lastName "Carfax" ;
    skos:altLabel "Lady Frances" ;
    skos:altLabel "the Lady Frances" ;
    ex:description "Lady Frances Carfax is the sole survivor of the direct family of the late Earl of Rufton. The estates went in the male line, leaving her with limited means but remarkable old Spanish jewellery of silver and curiously cut diamonds. She is a beautiful woman of about forty, still handsome, who drifts from country to country and hotel to hotel. She has precise habits and writes every second week to her old governess Miss Dobney. She banks at Silvester's. She was lured to London by the criminal Holy Peters and his accomplice Annie Fraser, who held her prisoner and stole her jewellery. She was placed alive in an oversized coffin with the body of Rose Spender and nearly buried alive, but was rescued by Holmes and Watson." ;
    ex:occupation "noblewoman" ;
    ex:age "approximately 40" ;
    ex:titleOfNobility "Lady" ;
    ex:childOf :earlOfRufton ;
    ex:knows :susanDobney, :marieDevine, :philipGreen, :henryPeters, :annieFraser ;
    ex:staysAt :hotelNationalLausanne, :englischerHof ;
    ex:owns :ladyFrancesJewellery ;
    ex:kidnappedBy :henryPeters, :annieFraser ;
    ex:rescuedBy :sherlockHolmes, :johnWatson ;
    ex:banksAt :silvestersBank ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :disappearanceLadyFrancesCarfaxDoc .

:ladyHildaTrelawneyHope a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Noble, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "Hilda" ;
    ex:lastName "Hope" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Lady Hilda Trelawney Hope" ;
    skos:altLabel "Lady Hilda" ;
    ex:description "Wife of Trelawney Hope and youngest daughter of the Duke of Belminster. The most lovely woman in London with subtle, delicate charm and beautiful colouring. Tall, graceful, and intensely womanly with a queenly presence. Visited Holmes at Baker Street seeking information about the stolen document. Was being blackmailed by Eduardo Lucas with an indiscreet letter she wrote before her marriage. Stole the diplomatic letter from her husband's despatch-box using a duplicate key furnished by Lucas, and gave it to Lucas at Godolphin Street in exchange for her compromising letter. Witnessed Lucas's murder by Mme. Fournaye. Later returned to the crime scene disguised as a young woman answering a typewriting advertisement, tricked Constable MacPherson, and recovered the diplomatic letter from the hiding-place under the carpet. Holmes confronted her and she surrendered the letter, which was returned to the despatch-box." ;
    ex:livesAt :whitehallTerrace ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :trelawneyHope ;
    ex:childOf :dukeOfBelminster ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:knows :johnWatson ;
    ex:knows :eduardoLucas ;
    ex:blackmailedBy :eduardoLucas ;
    ex:stoleFrom :trelawneyHope ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :secondStainDoc .

:ladyMaynooth a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Lady Maynooth" ;
    ex:description "Mother of Ronald Adair and Hilda Adair. Wife of the Earl of Maynooth. Returned from Australia to undergo a cataract operation. Living at 427 Park Lane with her children. Discovered her son's locked room on the night of the murder." ;
    ex:parentOf :ronaldAdair ;
    ex:parentOf :hildaAdair ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :earlOfMaynooth ;
    ex:livesAt :427ParkLane ;
