    ex:description "The unnamed landlady of the furnished lodgings where Holmes and Watson stayed in the university town. Holmes mentions that 'the landlady babbled of green peas at seven-thirty', indicating dinner was served at that time." ;
    ex:occupation "Landlady" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :threeStudentsDoc .

