:leonSterndale a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal, ex:Explorer ;
    ex:firstName "Leon" ;
    ex:lastName "Sterndale" ;
    ex:title "Dr." ;
    ex:prefLabel "Dr. Leon Sterndale" ;
    skos:altLabel "Sterndale" ;
    skos:altLabel "the great lion-hunter" ;
    ex:description "A great lion-hunter and explorer, famous in both London and Africa. A man of tremendous personality with a huge body, craggy and deeply seamed face, fierce eyes, hawk-like nose, grizzled hair that nearly brushed cottage ceilings, and a beard golden at the fringes and white near the lips with nicotine stain from his perpetual cigar. On his Cornish mother's side, a cousin of the Tregennis family. Lived in a small bungalow in the lonely wood of Beauchamp Arriance amid books and maps. Had secretly loved Brenda Tregennis for years; she loved him in return. Could not marry because his estranged wife, who left him years ago, could not be divorced under English law. The vicar Roundhay was in their confidence. Obtained a specimen of devil's-foot root (Radix pedis diaboli) from the Ubangi country in West Africa. After learning Mortimer Tregennis had stolen some of the powder and used it to kill Brenda and drive the brothers mad, Sterndale returned from Plymouth, and murdered Mortimer by burning devil's-foot powder in a lamp while threatening him with a revolver. Holmes allowed Sterndale to go free to continue his work in central Africa." ;
    ex:occupation "lion-hunter, explorer" ;
    ex:livesAt :sterndaleBungalow ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :mrsSterndale ;
    ex:romanticPartnerOf :brendaTregennis ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:knows :johnWatson ;
    ex:knows :roundhay ;
    ex:knows :mortimerTregennis ;
    ex:knows :brendaTregennis ;
    ex:knows :georgeTregennis ;
    ex:knows :owenTregennis ;
    ex:owns :devilsFootRoot ;
    ex:owns :sterndaleRevolver ;
    ex:perpetratorOf :mortimerTregennisMurder ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :devilsFootDoc .

:leperHospitalSuperintendent a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Doctor ;
    ex:prefLabel "Leper Hospital Superintendent" ;
    ex:description "The superintendent of the leper hospital near Pretoria where Godfrey Emsworth stumbled after being wounded at Buffelsspruit. He is an elderly man who spoke English and was clearly in authority at the hospital. He treated Godfrey's wound and warned him of the danger of having slept in a leper's bed. He believed himself immune to the disease but would never have dared do what Godfrey had done. He put Godfrey in a private room and within a week had him moved to the general hospital at Pretoria. His name is not given in the text." ;
    ex:occupation "medical superintendent" ;
    ex:livesAt :leperHospitalPretoria ;
    ex:treated :godfreyEmsworth ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :blanchedSoldierDoc .

:leslieArmstrong a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Doctor ;
    ex:firstName "Leslie" ;
    ex:lastName "Armstrong" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Dr. Leslie Armstrong" ;
    skos:altLabel "Dr. Armstrong" ;
    ex:description "Prominent Cambridge physician, one of the heads of the university medical school and a thinker of European reputation in more than one branch of science. Has a square massive face, brooding eyes under thatched brows, and a granite moulding of an inflexible jaw. A man of deep character, alert mind, grim, ascetic, self-contained, and formidable. Initially hostile to Holmes but ultimately cooperative. An intimate friend of Godfrey Staunton who helped keep Godfrey's secret marriage hidden. Treated Godfrey's wife for consumption and made daily journeys by brougham to her cottage near Trumpington. Sent a wire to cheer Godfrey and notified the wife's father of her critical condition." ;
    ex:occupation "Physician, university lecturer, consultant, medical researcher" ;
    ex:affiliatedWith :cambridgeUniversityMedicalSchool ;
    ex:affiliatedWith :cambridgeUniversity ;
    ex:employs :johnButler ;
    ex:friendOf :godfreyStaunton ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:knows :lordMountJames ;
    ex:livesAt :leslieArmstrongHouse ;
    ex:owns :armstrongBrougham ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :missingThreeQuarterDoc .

:leslieOakshott a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Surgeon ;
    ex:firstName "Leslie" ;
    ex:lastName "Oakshott" ;
    ex:title "Sir" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Sir Leslie Oakshott" ;
    ex:description """Sir Leslie Oakshott is a famous surgeon who treats Sherlock Holmes after the attack in Regent Street. He reports no immediate danger but notes two lacerated scalp wounds and considerable bruises requiring several stitches. Morphine has been injected. He arrives in his brougham.""" ;
    ex:occupation "surgeon" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :illustriousClientDoc .

:leverton a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Detective ;
    ex:lastName "Leverton" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Mr. Leverton" ;
    ex:description "Mr. Leverton is a detective from Pinkerton's American Agency. He is described as a quiet, businesslike young man with a clean-shaven, hatchet face. He is the hero of the Long Island cave mystery. He tracked Giuseppe Gorgiano from New York to London and has been close to him for a week, waiting for an excuse to arrest him. He works with Inspector Gregson to stake out the Howe Street flats where Gorgiano is hiding." ;
    ex:occupation "detective" ;
    ex:memberOf :pinkertonAgency ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:knows :gregson ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :redCircleDoc .

:lomax a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:lastName "Lomax" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Lomax" ;
    ex:description "Lomax is the sub-librarian at the London Library in St. James's Square. He is Watson's friend and helps Watson obtain a book on Chinese pottery for his crash course in ceramics." ;
    ex:occupation "sub-librarian" ;
    ex:employedBy :londonLibraryOrg ;
    ex:knows :johnWatson ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :illustriousClientDoc .

:lopez a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:lastName "Lopez" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Lopez" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Lucas" ;
    skos:altLabel "Lucas" ;
    skos:altLabel "Signor Rulli" ;
    ex:description "Secretary and close confidant of Don Murillo. Known as Mr. Lucas while at High Gable, and as Lopez in San Pedro. Chocolate brown complexion, wily, suave, and catlike with a poisonous gentleness of speech. Undoubtedly a foreigner. Accompanied Murillo everywhere as his shadow. Crept up on Miss Burnet when she was writing the note, addressed the note to Garcia, and sealed it with his sleeve-link. Guarded Miss Burnet while Murillo killed Garcia. Escaped England with Murillo. Murdered in Madrid at the Hotel Escurial under the name Signor Rulli." ;
    ex:physicalDescription "Chocolate brown complexion, wily, suave, catlike, poisonous gentleness of speech" ;
    ex:secretaryOf :donMurillo ;
    ex:nationality "San Pedran" ;
    ex:knows :donMurillo ;
    ex:knows :missBurnet ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :wisteriaLodgeDoc .

:lordBalmoral a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:lastName "Balmoral" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Lord Balmoral" ;
    ex:description "Lost £420 playing cards against Adair and Colonel Moran in partnership at the Bagatelle club some weeks before Adair's murder." ;
    ex:knows :ronaldAdair ;
    ex:knows :colonelSebastianMoran ;
    ex:knows :godfreyMilner ;
    ex:memberOf :bagatellCardClub ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
