:lordBellinger a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:PrimeMinister, ex:Noble ;
    ex:lastName "Bellinger" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Lord Bellinger" ;
    skos:altLabel "The Premier" ;
    skos:altLabel "The Prime Minister" ;
    ex:description "Twice Premier of Britain. Austere, high-nosed, eagle-eyed, and dominant. Gaunt, ascetic face with thin blue-veined hands. Has a quick, decisive manner and quick fierce gleam of deep-set eyes before which a Cabinet has cowered. Shaggy eyebrows. Visits Holmes with Trelawney Hope about the stolen diplomatic letter. Has nerves of steel but has hardly slept since the letter's disappearance. Twinkling eyes when he suspects Holmes knows more than he reveals." ;
    ex:occupation "Prime Minister of the United Kingdom" ;
    ex:knows :trelawneyHope ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:knows :johnWatson ;
    ex:clientOf :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :secondStainDoc .

:lordCantlemere a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Nobleman ;
    ex:lastName "Cantlemere" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Lord Cantlemere" ;
    ex:description "Lord Cantlemere is a thin, austere figure with a hatchet face and drooping mid-Victorian whiskers of a glossy blackness which hardly corresponds with his rounded shoulders and feeble gait. He is an eminent peer representing the very highest interests in the case of the stolen Crown diamond. He has fifty years of official life and is described as an excellent and loyal person but rather of the old regime. He is skeptical of Holmes's abilities and was against employing him. He visits Baker Street after the recovery of the stone, and Holmes plays a practical joke on him by slipping the Mazarin Stone into his overcoat pocket." ;
    ex:title "Lord" ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :mazarinStoneDoc .

:lordFlowers a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Noble ;
    ex:lastName "Flowers" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Lord Flowers" ;
    ex:description "Mentioned only as the author of a note found in Trelawney Hope's despatch-box when it was opened." ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :secondStainDoc .

:lordHarringby a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:lastName "Harringby" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Lord Harringby" ;
    ex:description "Lives at The Dingle near Oxshott. Listed in Holmes's telegram of large house owners in the area. Not further involved in the case." ;
    ex:livesAt :theDingle ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :wisteriaLodgeDoc .

:lordMerrow a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Noble ;
