:marieDevine a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Maid ;
    ex:prefLabel "Marie Devine" ;
    ex:firstName "Marie" ;
    ex:lastName "Devine" ;
    skos:altLabel "Marie" ;
    ex:description "Marie Devine is the former maid of Lady Frances Carfax. She is a devoted creature who left her mistress's service because Lady Frances was in the care of the Shlessingers and Marie's own approaching marriage made separation inevitable. Lady Frances had shown irritability toward her in Baden and questioned her honesty. Lady Frances gave her fifty pounds as a wedding present. She lives at 11 Rue de Trajan, Montpellier, and is engaged to Jules Vibart, a head waiter at the Hotel National in Lausanne. She witnessed Philip Green seize Lady Frances's wrist violently on the promenade by the lake in Lausanne." ;
    ex:occupation "lady's maid" ;
    ex:knows :ladyFrancesCarfax, :julesVibart ;
    ex:livesAt :11RueDeTrajan ;
    ex:employedBy :ladyFrancesCarfax ;
    ex:engagedTo :julesVibart ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :disappearanceLadyFrancesCarfaxDoc .

:marthaHisLastBow a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Spy ;
    ex:firstName "Martha" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Martha" ;
    skos:altLabel "old Martha" ;
    ex:description "Von Bork's old housekeeper who was actually an agent placed by Sherlock Holmes. Described as a dear old ruddy-faced woman in a country cap, bending over her knitting with a large black cat beside her. Holmes got her the position when he first took on the Von Bork case. She intercepted Von Bork's correspondence, keeping addresses of seven letters he posted that day. Signaled Holmes by putting out her lamp when the coast was clear after Baron Von Herling's departure. Was to report to Holmes at Claridge's Hotel the next day." ;
    ex:occupation "housekeeper" ;
    ex:agentOf :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:employedBy :vonBork ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:knows :vonBork ;
    ex:owns :marthaBlackCat ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :hisLastBowDoc .

:maryBrowner a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Mary" ;
    ex:lastName "Browner" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Mary Browner" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mary Cushing" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mrs. Browner" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mrs. Jim Browner" ;
    ex:description "Youngest sister (Mary Cushing, married name Browner). Twenty-nine when married Jim Browner. Described as angel. Trusting and innocent initially. Influenced by Sarah, became suspicious and irritable. Had affair with Alec Fairbairn. Murdered by Jim Browner at sea near New Brighton. One of the victims whose ear was sent in the box." ;
    ex:gender "female" ;
    ex:siblingOf :susanCushing ;
    ex:siblingOf :sarahCushing ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :jimBrowner ;
    ex:livesAt :brownersHomeLiverpool ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :cardboardBoxDoc .

:maryFraser a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Mary" ;
    ex:lastName "Fraser" ;
    ex:title "Lady" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Lady Brackenstall" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mary Fraser" ;
    skos:altLabel "Miss Mary Fraser of Adelaide" ;
    skos:altLabel "Lady Brackenstall" ;
    ex:description """Wife of Sir Eustace Brackenstall, née Mary Fraser of Adelaide, South Australia. A blonde, golden-haired, blue-eyed woman of graceful figure and beautiful face. Brought up in the freer atmosphere of South Australia, finding English life uncongenial. Arrived in London in June 1895 on the Rock of Gibraltar, her first voyage from home. Met Sir Eustace in July 1895 and married him in January of the following year. Endured his cruelty including being struck, stabbed with a hat-pin, and having her dog set on fire. On the night of the murder, was struck across the face by Sir Eustace with a stick and received a hideous plum-coloured swelling over one eye. After Croker killed Sir Eustace, participated in the cover-up story of a burglary, being tied to a chair by Croker. Captain Croker is deeply in love with her, and she appears to reciprocate.""" ;
    ex:physicalAppearance "Blonde, golden-haired, blue-eyed, graceful figure, beautiful face" ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :eustaceBrackenstall ;
    ex:livesAt :abbeyGrange ;
    ex:bornIn :adelaide ;
    ex:knows :eustaceBrackenstall ;
    ex:knows :theresaWright ;
    ex:knows :jackCroker ;
    ex:hasParticipantIn :murderOfEustaceBrackenstall ;
    ex:hasParticipantIn :abbeyGrangeInvestigation ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :abbeyGrangeDoc .

