:milesMcLaren a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Student ;
    ex:firstName "Miles" ;
    ex:lastName "McLaren" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Miles McLaren" ;
    skos:altLabel "McLaren" ;
    ex:description "Student at the College of St. Luke's, occupying the top floor room on the same staircase. Brilliant intellect — one of the brightest in the university — but wayward, dissipated, and unprincipled. Nearly expelled over a card scandal in his first year. Has been idling all term and faces the examination with dread. About five foot six in height. Refused to open his door when Holmes and Soames visited, shouting profanity. Too short to have seen the proofs through the window." ;
    ex:height "About five foot six" ;
    ex:knows :hiltonSoames ;
    ex:livesAt :mcLarensRoom ;
    ex:attendsInstitution :collegeOfStLukes ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :threeStudentsDoc .

:milvertonAvenger a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Milverton's Avenger" ;
    ex:description "An unnamed woman who murders Charles Augustus Milverton in his study. She is described as tall, slim, and dark, with a curved nose, strong dark eyebrows, hard glittering eyes, and a straight thin-lipped mouth. She initially poses as a maid offering to sell letters compromising the Countess d'Albert, but reveals herself as a former victim whose husband — described as 'the noblest gentleman that ever lived' and a great nobleman and statesman — died of a broken heart after Milverton sent compromising letters to him. She shoots Milverton with a small revolver, emptying the barrel into his body, and grinds her heel into his upturned face. Holmes later identifies her from a photograph in a shop near Regent Circus showing a regal and stately lady in Court dress with a diamond tiara. Her identity is suppressed by Watson." ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :avengerHusband ;
    ex:blackmailedBy :charlesAugustusMilverton ;
    ex:killed :charlesAugustusMilverton ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :milvertonDoc .

:milvertonSecretary a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Milverton's Secretary" ;
    ex:description "An unnamed secretary at Appledore Towers who is devoted to Milverton's interests and never leaves the study during the day. His constant presence in the study is the reason Holmes must attempt the burglary at night. Name is not given in the text." ;
    ex:occupation "secretary" ;
    ex:worksAt :appledoreTowers ;
    ex:employedBy :charlesAugustusMilverton ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :milvertonDoc .

:minnieWarrender a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim ;
