:missPeterCarey a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:lastName "Carey" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Miss Carey" ;
    skos:altLabel "Carey's daughter" ;
    ex:description "Daughter of Captain Peter Carey, aged twenty. A pale, fair-haired girl whose eyes blazed defiantly. Told Holmes and Watson she was glad her father was dead and blessed the hand that struck him down. Her room had a window facing the cabin, and she heard a fearful yell at approximately 2am on the night of the murder but took no notice as her father often shouted when drunk." ;
    ex:age "20" ;
    ex:childOf :peterCarey, :mrsPeterCarey ;
    ex:livesAt :woodmansLee ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :blackPeterDoc .

:mmeHenriFournaye a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:lastName "Fournaye" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Mme. Henri Fournaye" ;
    skos:altLabel "Madame Fournaye" ;
    skos:altLabel "Madame Henri Fournaye" ;
    ex:description "Wife of Eduardo Lucas (known in Paris as M. Henri Fournaye). Of Creole origin. Extremely excitable nature, suffered in the past from attacks of jealousy amounting to frenzy. Occupied a small villa in the Rue Austerlitz, Paris. Returned from a journey to London on Tuesday. Murdered Eduardo Lucas at 16 Godolphin Street by stabbing him with a curved Indian dagger during a jealous frenzy after finding him with Lady Hilda. Screamed in French 'My waiting is not in vain. At last, at last I have found you with her!' Seen at Charing Cross Station on Tuesday morning with wild appearance and violent gestures. Found insane by authorities after being reported by her servants. Developed mania of a dangerous and permanent form. Unable to give any coherent account. Doctors hold out no hopes for re-establishment of reason." ;
    ex:nationality "Creole" ;
    ex:livesAt :fournayeVilla ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :henriFournaye ;
    ex:killed :eduardoLucas ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :secondStainDoc .

:monsieurMoser a ex:FictionalPerson ;
