:mortimerTregennis a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Mortimer" ;
    ex:lastName "Tregennis" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Mortimer Tregennis" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Tregennis" ;
    skos:altLabel "Tregennis" ;
    ex:description "An independent gentleman who lodged at the vicarage of Mr. Roundhay in Tredannick Wollas. A thin, dark, spectacled man with a stoop giving the impression of physical deformity. Sad-faced and introspective with small shrewd beady eyes. Former tin-miner at Redruth who retired after selling the family venture to a company. There was a family quarrel over the division of money, supposedly reconciled. He poisoned his siblings with devil's-foot root powder placed in the fire at Tredannick Wartha on the night of March 16, 1897, killing his sister Brenda and driving brothers George and Owen insane, likely motivated by desire to control the joint family property. Was subsequently murdered by Dr. Leon Sterndale in revenge, killed by the same devil's-foot poison burned in a lamp in his sitting-room at the vicarage." ;
    ex:occupation "independent gentleman, former tin-miner" ;
    ex:livesAt :tredannickWollasVicarage ;
    ex:siblingOf :brendaTregennis ;
    ex:siblingOf :georgeTregennis ;
    ex:siblingOf :owenTregennis ;
    ex:knows :roundhay ;
    ex:knows :leonSterndale ;
    ex:victimOf :mortimerTregennisMurder ;
    ex:perpetratorOf :tredannickWarthaPoisoning ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :devilsFootDoc .

