    ex:prefLabel "Mr. Harding" ;
    ex:description "The founder and owner of Harding Brothers, a retail shop near the High Street Station in Kensington. Described as a brisk, crisp little person, very dapper and quick, with a clear head and a ready tongue. Sold Napoleon busts to Horace Harker, Josiah Brown, and Mr. Sandeford. Ordered three busts from Gelder & Co. Gave Holmes Mr. Sandeford's address." ;
    ex:occupation "shopkeeper" ;
