:mrsEmsworth a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:lastName "Emsworth" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Mrs. Emsworth" ;
    ex:description "Mrs. Emsworth is the wife of Colonel Emsworth and mother of Godfrey Emsworth. She is described as a gentle little white mouse of a woman. She invited James Dodd to stay at Tuxbury Old Park and eagerly questioned him about her son at dinner. She fainted upon hearing Sir James Saunders's diagnosis that Godfrey's condition was ichthyosis rather than leprosy." ;
    ex:parentOf :godfreyEmsworth ;
