    ex:prefLabel "Mrs. Warren" ;
    ex:description "Mrs. Warren is a landlady who consults Sherlock Holmes about a mysterious lodger at her house in Great Orme Street, near the British Museum. She is frightened because the lodger has remained hidden in his rooms for ten days, never showing his face, communicating only through printed slips of paper. She previously had a lodger named Fairdale Hobbs whose affair was arranged by Holmes. She is married to Mr. Warren and employs a servant girl." ;
    ex:occupation "landlady" ;
