:mycroftHolmes a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:GovernmentOfficial ;
    ex:firstName "Mycroft" ;
    ex:lastName "Holmes" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Mycroft Holmes" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mycroft" ;
    ex:description "Sherlock Holmes's elder brother, seven years his senior. Corpulent, with massive face and peculiarly light watery gray eyes. Greater powers of observation and deduction than Sherlock but lacks ambition and energy. Has extraordinary faculty for figures, audits government books. Lodges in Pall Mall, walks to Whitehall daily. Co-founder of the Diogenes Club.  Described as occasionally being the British government itself — the central exchange and clearinghouse for all government departments. Draws £450/year, remains a subordinate with no ambitions for honour or title, yet the most indispensable man in the country. Has the tidiest and most orderly brain with the greatest capacity for storing facts of any man living. His regular cycle is Pall Mall lodgings, Diogenes Club, Whitehall. Visited Baker Street (extremely rare) over the Cadogan West affair. Provided list of foreign agents. Participated in stakeout at Caulfield Gardens but indignantly declined to climb railings. The Prime Minister was upset; the Admiralty buzzing; the Cabinet anxious." ;
    ex:occupation "Government auditor" ;
    ex:gender "male" ;
    ex:eyeColor "light, watery gray" ;
    ex:physicalDescription "Much larger and stouter than Sherlock, absolutely corpulent. Massive face with sharpness of expression. Broad, fat hands. Peculiarly light watery gray eyes with far-away introspective look." ;
    ex:brotherOf :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:foundedOrg :diogenesClub ;
    ex:memberOf :diogenesClub ;
    ex:grandchildOf :holmesGrandmother ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes , :johnWatson , :mrMelas ;
    ex:knows :mrsHudson ;
    ex:livesAt :mycroftLodgings , :pallMall ;
    ex:owns :mycroftSnuffBox , :mycroftPocketBook , :mycroftHandkerchief ;
    ex:worksAt :whitehall ;
    ex:salary "£450 per year" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :emptyHouseDoc ;
    dc:source :greekInterpreterDoc ;
    dc:source :brucePartingtonPlansDoc .

