:neliganSenior a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim, ex:Banker ;
    ex:lastName "Neligan" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Mr. Neligan Senior" ;
    skos:altLabel "Neligan's father" ;
    ex:description "Partner in the West-country banking firm of Dawson and Neligan. When the firm failed for a million pounds in 1883, ruining half the county families of Cornwall, he took the securities believing he could realize them and pay all creditors in full. Sailed in his yacht toward Norway just before the arrest warrant was issued, bidding farewell to his wife and leaving a list of securities. His yacht was blown north by southerly gales and picked up by the Sea Unicorn commanded by Peter Carey. His name was never mentioned aboard ship. On the second night aboard, Carey threw him overboard in the middle watch of a dark night, two days before sighting the Shetland lights. His son later discovered securities reappearing on the London market, traced to Peter Carey. Name not given in text; referred to only as Neligan or Neligan's father." ;
    ex:occupation "banker" ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :neliganMother ;
    ex:parentOf :johnNeligan ;
    ex:owns :neliganYacht, :neliganTinBox ;
    ex:killedBy :peterCarey ;
    ex:partnerIn :dawsonAndNeligan ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :blackPeterDoc .

