:patrickCairns a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal, ex:Sailor ;
    ex:firstName "Patrick" ;
    ex:lastName "Cairns" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Patrick Cairns" ;
    skos:altLabel "Cairns" ;
    ex:description "A man of remarkable and fierce appearance with a bulldog face framed in a tangle of hair and beard, two bold dark eyes gleaming behind thick tufted overhung eyebrows. A harpooner with twenty-six voyages to his credit, based in Dundee, earning eight pounds a month. Was spare harpooner on the Sea Unicorn in 1883 under Captain Peter Carey. Witnessed Carey murder the landsman (Neligan Senior) by throwing him overboard. Years later found Carey at Woodman's Lee and attempted blackmail. On the first visit Carey was reasonable. On the second visit (the night of the murder), Carey was drunk and attacked Cairns with a clasp-knife. Cairns seized a harpoon from the wall and drove it through Carey in self-defense. Took the tin box of securities from the shelf but left his tobacco pouch behind. Heard someone (Neligan) enter the cabin as he fled. Walked ten miles to Tunbridge Wells and took a train to London. Found the box contained only papers he dared not sell. Applied for harpooner work through shipping agents and was lured to Baker Street by Holmes's fake Arctic expedition advertisement under Captain Basil. Captured and handcuffed by Holmes." ;
    ex:occupation "harpooner" ;
    ex:owns :cairnsTobaccoPouch ;
    ex:crewOf :seaUnicorn ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :blackPeterDoc .

