:peterCarey a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "Peter" ;
    ex:lastName "Carey" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Captain Peter Carey" ;
    skos:altLabel "Black Peter" ;
    skos:altLabel "Peter Carey" ;
    skos:altLabel "Captain Carey" ;
    ex:description "Born in 1845, a most daring and successful seal and whale fisher. In 1883 commanded the steam sealer Sea Unicorn of Dundee. Retired in 1884 after several successful voyages. Known as Black Peter on account of his swarthy features, huge brindled beard, and violent temperament. A strict Puritan in ordinary life but an intermittent drunkard who became a perfect fiend when drinking. Known to drive his wife and daughter out of doors at night and flog them through the park. Assaulted the local vicar. Bought Woodman's Lee near Forest Row in Sussex where he lived for six years. Built a wooden outhouse he called 'the cabin' where he slept every night. In August 1883 murdered a landsman (Neligan Senior) aboard the Sea Unicorn by throwing him overboard. Murdered at approximately 2am on a Wednesday in early July 1895 by Patrick Cairns, who harpooned him through the breast in self-defense after Carey attacked with a clasp-knife." ;
    ex:occupation "seal and whale fisher, ship captain" ;
    ex:birthYear "1845" ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :mrsPeterCarey ;
    ex:parentOf :missPeterCarey ;
    ex:livesAt :woodmansLee ;
    ex:owns :peterCareyCabin, :careySheathKnife, :careySeaChest ;
    ex:killedBy :patrickCairns ;
    ex:commands :seaUnicorn ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :blackPeterDoc .

:peterSteiler a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Peter" ;
    ex:lastName "Steiler" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Peter Steiler the Elder" ;
    skos:altLabel "Steiler" ;
    skos:altLabel "Old Steiler" ;
    skos:altLabel "Peter Steiler the elder" ;
    ex:description "Landlord of the Englischer Hof hotel in Meiringen. An intelligent man who spoke excellent English, having served for three years as waiter at the Grosvenor Hotel in London. The forged letter about the sick Englishwoman bore his hotel's mark, and he confirmed he had not written it — noting it must have been written by the tall Englishman who came in after Holmes and Watson left." ;
    ex:occupation "hotel landlord, former waiter" ;
    ex:owns :englischerHof ;
    ex:livesAt :meiringen ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :finalProblemDoc .

:peterTheGroom a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim, ex:Groom ;
    ex:firstName "Peter" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Peter the groom" ;
    skos:altLabel "Peter" ;
    skos:altLabel "the little ostler" ;
    ex:description "A young fellow about seventeen years old, dressed like an ostler with leather cords and gaiters. He drove Violet's dog-cart. Was pulled off and clubbed by the attackers during the abduction, receiving a terrible cut on his head. Found insensible but alive; the wound had not penetrated the bone. Was able to keep pace with the county constabulary later." ;
    ex:occupation "groom/ostler" ;
    ex:age "approximately 17" ;
    ex:gender "male" ;
    ex:employedBy :bobCarruthers ;
    ex:hasParticipatedIn :abductionOfVioletSmith ;
    ex:hasParticipatedIn :assaultOnPeter ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :solitaryCyclistDoc .

:philipGreen a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Hon. Philip Green" ;
    ex:firstName "Philip" ;
    ex:lastName "Green" ;
    skos:altLabel "Philip Green" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Green" ;
    ex:description "The Honourable Philip Green is the son of the famous Admiral Green who commanded the Sea of Azof fleet in the Crimean War. He is a huge, swarthy man with a bristling black beard, who looks more at home in a farmer's inn than a fashionable hotel. He loved Lady Frances Carfax but was a wild youngster whose behaviour caused her to reject him. He went to South Africa and made his money at Barberton. He attempted to reconcile with Lady Frances at Lausanne, but she fled. He pursued her to Baden and then to Montpellier. He attacked Watson in Montpellier when accused of harming Lady Frances. Holmes enlisted Green to watch Bovington's pawnshop. Green followed Mrs. Peters to 36 Poultney Square and witnessed the coffin delivery. His London address is the Langham Hotel." ;
    ex:hasPhysicalFeature "huge, swarthy, bristling black beard, sunburned" ;
    ex:honorific "Hon." ;
    ex:childOf :admiralGreen ;
    ex:knows :ladyFrancesCarfax, :sherlockHolmes, :johnWatson, :susanDobney ;
    ex:staysAt :langhamHotel ;
    ex:loves :ladyFrancesCarfax ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :disappearanceLadyFrancesCarfaxDoc .

:pietroVenucci a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Pietro" ;
    ex:lastName "Venucci" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Pietro Venucci" ;
    ex:description "A man from Naples and one of the greatest cut-throats in London. Connected to the Mafia. Brother of Lucretia Venucci, the maid of the Princess of Colonna. Tall, sunburned, very powerful, not more than thirty years old, poorly dressed. Carried a horn-handled clasp knife, an apple, string, a shilling map of London, a Catholic emblem round his neck, and a photograph of Beppo. Found murdered on the doorstep of 131 Pitt Street, Kensington, with a great gash in his throat. Was tracking Beppo, possibly because Beppo was responsible for the loss of the pearl, and was killed in the scuffle." ;
    ex:nationality "Italian" ;
    ex:siblingOf :lucretiaVenucci ;
    ex:connectedTo :theMafia ;
    ex:killedBy :beppo ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :sixNapoleonsDoc .

:plainClothesManStation a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Constable ;
    ex:prefLabel "Plain-clothes man at Esher station" ;
