:sirJamesSaunders a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Dermatologist ;
    ex:firstName "James" ;
    ex:lastName "Saunders" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Sir James Saunders" ;
    ex:description "Sir James Saunders is an eminent dermatologist whom Holmes brought to examine Godfrey Emsworth. He is described as a grave and taciturn gentleman of iron-gray aspect with austere, sphinx-like features. Holmes had once done him a professional service, and he agreed to advise as a friend rather than a specialist. He diagnosed Godfrey's condition as pseudo-leprosy or ichthyosis, a scale-like skin affection that is unsightly and obstinate but possibly curable and certainly noninfective. He speculated that the psychological apprehension of leprosy may have produced a physical effect simulating the feared disease." ;
    ex:occupation "dermatologist" ;
    ex:honorificPrefix "Sir" ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:knows :godfreyEmsworth ;
    ex:knows :colonelEmsworth ;
    ex:knows :mrKent ;
    ex:diagnosed :godfreyEmsworth ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :blanchedSoldierDoc .

:sirJamesWalter a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:GovernmentOfficial ;
    ex:firstName "James" ;
    ex:lastName "Walter" ;
    ex:title "Sir" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Sir James Walter" ;
    skos:altLabel "Sir James" ;
    ex:description "Famous government expert and head of the Submarine Department at Woolwich Arsenal. His decorations and sub-titles fill two lines of a book of reference. Grown gray in the service. A gentleman and favoured guest in the most exalted houses. Patriotism beyond suspicion. One of two persons with a key to the safe containing the Bruce-Partington plans; kept all three keys (outer door, office, safe) on the same ring. Left for London about 3pm Monday, visited Admiral Sinclair at Barclay Square the whole evening. Died the morning after the theft was discovered, from a broken heart over the scandal. A man of very sensitive honour who could not survive such an affair. His brother Colonel Valentine Walter testified to his departure from Woolwich." ;
    ex:occupation "head of Submarine Department" ;
    ex:livesAt :sirJamesWalterHouse ;
    ex:employedBy :woolwichArsenalOrg ;
    ex:siblingOf :colonelValentineWalter ;
    ex:knows :colonelValentineWalter ;
    ex:knows :sidneyJohnson ;
    ex:knows :admiralSinclair ;
    ex:headOf :submarineDepartment ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :brucePartingtonPlansDoc .

