:stimsonShopWoman a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Stimson's Shop Woman" ;
    skos:altLabel "undertaker's wife" ;
    ex:description "An unnamed woman who works behind the counter at Stimson and Co., the undertaker's shop on Kennington Road. She told Philip Green the coffin was late because it 'took longer, being out of the ordinary.' She also confirmed to Watson that the Poultney Square funeral was at eight o'clock in the morning. Her remark about the coffin being out of the ordinary was the key clue that led Holmes to realize the coffin was specially made to hold two bodies." ;
    ex:occupation "undertaker's assistant" ;
    ex:worksAt :stimsonAndCo ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :disappearanceLadyFrancesCarfaxDoc .

:straubenzee a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Craftsman ;
    ex:lastName "Straubenzee" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Straubenzee" ;
    ex:description "Straubenzee is a craftsman who made the air-gun used in the Mazarin Stone case. He has a workshop in the Minories in London. Holmes followed Count Sylvius to his workshop. Holmes describes Straubenzee's air-gun as a very pretty bit of work." ;
    ex:occupation "gunsmith" ;
    ex:worksAt :straubenzeeWorkshop ;
    ex:created :mazarinAirGun ;
    ex:knows :countNegrettoSylvius ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :mazarinStoneDoc .

:sultanOfTurkey a ex:RealPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Sultan of Turkey" ;
    ex:description "The Sultan of Turkey had given Holmes a commission which called for immediate action in January 1903, as political consequences of the gravest kind might arise from its neglect. This commission delayed Holmes's ability to accompany Dodd to Tuxbury Old Park." ;
    ex:occupation "sultan" ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
