:susanTarlton a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:DomesticServant ;
    ex:firstName "Susan" ;
    ex:lastName "Tarlton" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Susan Tarlton" ;
    skos:altLabel "Susan" ;
    ex:description "Maid at Yoxley Old Place. Has been with Professor Coram since his arrival. Key witness to the murder of Willoughby Smith. Was hanging curtains in upstairs front bedroom when she heard Smith pass along the passage and descend to the study. Heard a wild, hoarse scream and a heavy thud. Found Smith on the floor with blood pouring from his neck. Heard his dying words: 'The Professor—it was she.' Confirmed no one could have escaped through the passage door after the cry. Described by Professor Coram as a 'country girl.'" ;
    ex:occupation "maid" ;
    ex:livesAt :yoxleyOldPlace ;
    ex:employedBy :professorCoram ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :goldenPinceNezDoc .

:swissMessengerReichenbach a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:prefLabel "Swiss Messenger at Reichenbach" ;
    skos:altLabel "Swiss lad" ;
    skos:altLabel "young Swiss messenger" ;
    ex:description "A young Swiss lad who came running along the path at Reichenbach Falls with a forged letter. Was to remain with Holmes as guide and companion while Watson returned to Meiringen. Never found again; almost certainly one of Moriarty's agents. The text states there can be no doubt he was 'one of the numerous agents whom Moriarty kept in his employ.'" ;
    ex:employedBy :professorMoriarty ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :finalProblemDoc .

:tangeyDaughter a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Tangey's Eldest Daughter" ;
    ex:description "The eldest daughter of the commissionaire Tangey and Mrs. Tangey. A young woman who opened the door at 16 Ivy Lane when Forbes and Phelps arrived. She told her mother that two men were waiting to see her, inadvertently allowing Mrs. Tangey to run to the back kitchen. Her name is not given in the text." ;
    ex:childOf :tangey ;
    ex:childOf :mrsTangey ;
    ex:livesAt :16IvyLane ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :navalTreatyDoc .

:monsieurDubugue a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Detective ;
    ex:lastName "Dubugue" ;
    ex:title "Monsieur" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Monsieur Dubugue" ;
    ex:description "A member of the Paris police who was involved in the Adventure of the Second Stain case. He wasted his energies upon what proved to be side-issues. Holmes demonstrated the true facts of the case to him." ;
    ex:occupation "police detective" ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:livesAt :paris ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :navalTreatyDoc .

:mrsTangey a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Charwoman ;
    ex:lastName "Tangey" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Mrs. Tangey" ;
    skos:altLabel "the commissionaire's wife" ;
    ex:description "Wife of Tangey the commissionaire. A large, coarse-faced, elderly woman who wears an apron. Works as a charwoman at the Foreign Office. On the night of the theft, she answered the bell when Phelps rang for coffee, as her husband was tired. She hurried away from the building and was the only person seen by the policeman on Charles Street (described as a tall elderly woman with a Paisley shawl). At her home at 16 Ivy Lane, she ran to the back kitchen when she learned men were waiting - claimed she had money there to pay off brokers. Taken to Scotland Yard and searched by a female searcher, no papers found. She drinks and was watched by a female police agent who could get nothing from her even when she was drunk. Forbes considers her 'a bad lot'." ;
    ex:occupation "charwoman" ;
    ex:employedBy :foreignOfficeOrg ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :tangey ;
    ex:knows :tangey ;
    ex:knows :percyPhelps ;
    ex:livesAt :16IvyLane ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :navalTreatyDoc .

:tangey a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Commissionaire ;
    ex:lastName "Tangey" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Tangey" ;
    skos:altLabel "the commissionaire" ;
    ex:description "The commissionaire at the Foreign Office. An old soldier who served in the Coldstream Guards and left with a good character. He remains all night in a small lodge at the foot of the stairs and makes coffee on a spirit-lamp for officials working overtime. On the night of the theft, he fell asleep while boiling the kettle. He was awakened by the bell ringing from Phelps's room and followed Phelps upstairs. He rushed to Charles Street with Phelps and tried to lead the search away from his wife's direction. Lives at 16 Ivy Lane, Brixton. Shadowed by police for nine weeks with nothing found against him." ;
    ex:occupation "commissionaire" ;
    ex:employedBy :foreignOfficeOrg ;
    ex:formerMemberOf :coldstreamGuards ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :mrsTangey ;
    ex:knows :percyPhelps ;
    ex:knows :mrsTangey ;
    ex:livesAt :16IvyLane ;
    ex:worksAt :commissionaireLodge ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :navalTreatyDoc .

:josephHarrison a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "Joseph" ;
    ex:lastName "Harrison" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Joseph Harrison" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Joseph Harrison" ;
    skos:altLabel "Master Joseph" ;
    ex:description "Annie Harrison's brother. A rather stout man with ruddy cheeks, merry eyes, and a plump and mischievous appearance, looking nearer forty than thirty. Wears a locket with J H monogram. His father is an iron-master in Northumberland. He is the thief who stole the naval treaty from the Foreign Office. He entered via the Charles Street door, found the treaty on Phelps's desk, and hid it under a floorboard in the sick-room at Briarbrae (covering a T-joint for gas pipes). He had lost heavily in stock market dabbling and planned to sell the treaty to the French embassy. He was an absolutely selfish man who did not let his sister's happiness or Phelps's reputation hold his hand. He attempted to retrieve the hidden treaty twice - once scared off by Phelps, then caught by Holmes. He attacked Holmes with a long-bladed knife, cutting him over the knuckles, before being subdued." ;
    ex:childOf :harrisonFather ;
    ex:hasWeapon :josephKnife ;
    ex:knows :percyPhelps ;
    ex:knows :annieHarrison ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:knows :johnWatson ;
    ex:livesAt :briarbrae ;
    ex:owns :harrisonLocket ;
    ex:siblingOf :annieHarrison ;
    ex:stole :navalTreaty ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :navalTreatyDoc .

:lordHoldhurst a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Politician ;
    ex:lastName "Holdhurst" ;
    ex:title "Lord" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Lord Holdhurst" ;
    ex:description "Percy Phelps's uncle (his mother's brother). A great conservative politician who became foreign minister in the current administration, described as a cabinet minister and 'future premier of England'. Physically slight and tall with sharp features, a thoughtful face, and curling hair prematurely tinged with gray. Represents a nobleman who is in truth noble, with old-fashioned courtesy. Despite his position, he is far from rich with many calls on his resources - Holmes observed his boots had been re-soled. His chambers are in Downing Street. He gave Phelps the secret naval treaty to copy. After the theft, he wrote Phelps a letter that was cold but not harsh, saying no steps about dismissal would be taken until Phelps's health was restored." ;
    ex:occupation "foreign minister, cabinet minister" ;
    ex:commissions :percyPhelps ;
    ex:knows :percyPhelps ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:knows :johnWatson ;
    ex:livesAt :downingStreet ;
    ex:memberOf :britishCabinet ;
    ex:uncleOf :percyPhelps ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :navalTreatyDoc .

:percyPhelps a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim, ex:Diplomat ;
    ex:firstName "Percy" ;
    ex:lastName "Phelps" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Percy Phelps" ;
    skos:altLabel "Tadpole Phelps" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Phelps" ;
    skos:altLabel "Tadpole" ;
    ex:description "Watson's old school-fellow, nicknamed 'Tadpole' at school. A very brilliant boy who carried away every prize at school and won a scholarship to Cambridge. His mother's brother is Lord Holdhurst, the conservative politician and foreign minister. Through his uncle's influence, Phelps obtained a position of trust at the Foreign Office, where he was given the secret naval treaty to copy. The treaty was stolen while he went downstairs for coffee, leading to nine weeks of brain-fever. He convalesced at Briarbrae in Woking, nursed by his fiancée Annie Harrison. Described as young, very pale and worn, lying on a sofa. A nervous, sensitive person by nature. Holmes recovered the treaty and presented it to him at breakfast at 221B Baker Street." ;
    ex:nickname "Tadpole" ;
    ex:occupation "Foreign Office clerk" ;
    ex:attendedSchoolWith :johnWatson ;
    ex:educatedAt :cambridgeUniversity ;
    ex:employedBy :foreignOfficeOrg ;
    ex:engagedTo :annieHarrison ;
    ex:knows :johnWatson ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:knows :annieHarrison ;
    ex:knows :josephHarrison ;
    ex:knows :lordHoldhurst ;
    ex:knows :forbes ;
    ex:knows :drFerrier ;
    ex:knows :charlesGorot ;
    ex:livesAt :briarbrae ;
    ex:nephewOf :lordHoldhurst ;
    ex:nursedBy :annieHarrison ;
    ex:nursedBy :hiredNurseNT ;
    ex:treatedBy :drFerrier ;
    ex:victimOf :theftOfNavalTreaty ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :navalTreatyDoc .

