:barclayCoachman a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Servant ;
    ex:prefLabel "Barclay Household Coachman" ;
    ex:description "Unnamed coachman serving the Barclay household at Lachine. Heard Mrs. Barclay chatting with the Colonel in a friendly fashion before she left for the Guild meeting. Later, after hearing screams, rushed to the morning-room door and tried to force it. Ran through the hall door and around to the lawn, entered through the open French window. Found Mrs. Barclay insensible on a couch and Colonel Barclay dead on the floor. Could not find the missing key. Went out through the window again to obtain help from a policeman and medical man." ;
    ex:occupation "Coachman" ;
    ex:employedBy :jamesBarclay ;
    ex:worksAt :lachine ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :crookedManDoc .

