:blessington a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal, ex:Informer, ex:Victim ;
    ex:lastName "Blessington" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Mr. Blessington" ;
    skos:altLabel "Sutton" ;
    skos:altLabel "Blessington" ;
    ex:description "A singular-looking, very fat man whose skin hung about his face in loose pouches like a bloodhound's cheeks, with sickly color and thin sandy hair. His real name was Sutton, and he was the worst member of the Worthingdon bank gang who robbed the bank in 1875. He turned informer, leading to Cartwright's hanging and fifteen-year sentences for Biddle, Hayward, and Moffat. He assumed the identity of Blessington and lived as a resident patient at 403 Brook Street, funding Dr. Trevelyan's practice from his ill-gotten gains. He kept all his money in a black strong-box, distrusting bankers. He was murdered by his former associates who hanged him in his room after a mock trial, in revenge for his betrayal." ;
    ex:alias "Sutton" ;
    ex:livesAt :403BrookStreet ;
    ex:owns :blessingtonStrongbox ;
    ex:owns :blessingtonPistol ;
    ex:owns :blessingtonCigarCase ;
    ex:owns :blessingtonCigarHolder ;
    ex:finances :percyTrevelyan ;
