:missMorrison a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:lastName "Morrison" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Miss Morrison" ;
    skos:altLabel "Miss M." ;
    ex:description "Young lady living in the next villa to Lachine in Aldershot. Friend of Mrs. Barclay. Described as a little ethereal slip of a girl with timid eyes and blond hair, but shrewd and possessing common-sense. Accompanied Mrs. Barclay to the Guild of St. George meeting on Monday evening. On the walk home through Hudson Street, witnessed Mrs. Barclay's encounter with Henry Wood. Initially denied knowledge of what caused Mrs. Barclay's ill-humor. Later provided a full statement to Holmes after he explained the danger Mrs. Barclay faced." ;
    ex:livesAt :aldershot ;
