:percyTrevelyan a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Doctor ;
    ex:firstName "Percy" ;
    ex:lastName "Trevelyan" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Dr. Percy Trevelyan" ;
    skos:altLabel "Dr. Trevelyan" ;
    skos:altLabel "Percy Trevelyan" ;
    skos:altLabel "P.T." ;
    ex:description "A pale, taper-faced man with sandy whiskers, aged about thirty-three or thirty-four, with a haggard expression and unhealthy hue. A specialist in nervous diseases who studied at London University and held a minor position at King's College Hospital. He won the Bruce Pinkerton prize and medal for his monograph on nervous lesions, and was an authority on catalepsy. His practice at 403 Brook Street was funded by Mr. Blessington, to whom he paid three-quarters of his earnings. He consulted Holmes when mysterious events at his practice led to Blessington's murder." ;
    ex:occupation "specialist in nervous diseases" ;
    ex:livesAt :403BrookStreet ;
    ex:workedAt :kingsCollegeHospital ;
    ex:educatedAt :londonUniversity ;
    ex:financedBy :blessington ;
