:theresaWright a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Nurse, ex:Servant ;
    ex:firstName "Theresa" ;
    ex:lastName "Wright" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Theresa Wright" ;
    skos:altLabel "Theresa" ;
    ex:description """Lady Brackenstall's personal maid and nurse. A tall, austere, gaunt Australian woman. Taciturn, suspicious, and ungracious in manner. Nursed Mary Fraser as a baby and has been with her all her life. Came with Mary from Australia to England eighteen months before the story. Devoted to her mistress and hateful of Sir Eustace, who once threw a decanter at her. After Croker killed Sir Eustace, Theresa devised the burglary cover story, coaching Lady Brackenstall while Croker staged the scene. Met Croker by chance in a country lane at Sydenham and told him of Lady Brackenstall's mistreatment.""" ;
    ex:occupation "Lady's maid and nurse" ;
    ex:physicalAppearance "Tall, austere, gaunt" ;
