:victorSavage a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Victor" ;
    ex:lastName "Savage" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Victor Savage" ;
    skos:altLabel "Poor Victor" ;
    ex:description "Victor Savage is the nephew of Culverton Smith. He was described as a strong, hearty young fellow who died horribly on the fourth day after contracting an out-of-the-way Asiatic disease in the heart of London. His death was actually murder by his uncle Culverton Smith, who used his knowledge of tropical diseases to kill him. Victor stood between Smith and a reversion (inheritance), providing the motive for the murder. Holmes had suspicions of foul play in Savage's death, which led Smith to attempt to murder Holmes as well." ;
    ex:nephewOf :culvertonSmith ;
    ex:participatedIn :murderOfVictorSavage ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :dyingDetectiveDoc .

