:violetDeMerville a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Violet" ;
    ex:lastName "de Merville" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Violet de Merville" ;
    skos:altLabel "Miss Violet de Merville" ;
    skos:altLabel "Miss de Merville" ;
    ex:description """Violet de Merville is the young, rich, beautiful, and accomplished daughter of General de Merville. She is described as having an ethereal, other-world beauty with a pale, demure, self-contained appearance, likened to a snow image on a mountain and the faces in pictures of old masters. She met Baron Gruner on a Mediterranean yachting voyage and is completely and obsessively in love with him, refusing to hear any word against him. She lives at 104 Berkeley Square with her father. She is aware of three passages in her fiancé's past involving women but believes his account of them. She coldly dismisses both Holmes's arguments and Kitty Winter's passionate testimony. The marriage is ultimately cancelled after the incriminating book is shown to her or her father.""" ;
    ex:engagedTo :adelbertGruner ;
    ex:childOf :generalDeMerville ;
    ex:livesAt :104BerkeleySquare ;
    ex:knows :adelbertGruner ;
    ex:knows :generalDeMerville ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :illustriousClientDoc .

:violetHunter a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Client ;
    ex:firstName "Violet" ;
    ex:lastName "Hunter" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Violet Hunter" ;
    skos:altLabel "Miss Hunter" ;
    ex:description """Violet Hunter is a young governess who consults Sherlock Holmes about a suspicious job offer. She is plainly but neatly dressed, with a bright, quick face, freckled like a plover's egg, and with the brisk manner of a woman who has had her own way to make in the world. She has luxuriant chestnut hair of a rather peculiar tint. Having no parents or relations, she served five years as governess to Colonel Spence Munro's family before being left without a situation. Through Westaway's agency she met Jephro Rucastle, who offered her 120 pounds a year with peculiar conditions: cutting her hair, wearing an electric-blue dress, and sitting in a window. She accepted and discovered she was impersonating the imprisoned Alice Rucastle. She bravely locked Mrs. Toller in the cellar to help Holmes investigate. She later became the head of a private school at Walsall with considerable success.""" ;
    ex:occupation "governess, school headmistress" ;
    ex:clientOf :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:employedBy :jephroRucastle, :colonelSpenceMunro ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes, :johnWatson, :jephroRucastle, :mrsRucastle, :missStoper, :mrsTollerCB, :tollerCB, :edwardRucastle ;
    ex:hasParticipatedIn :copperBeechesInvestigation ;
    ex:livesAt :copperBeeches, :montaguePlace ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :copperBeechesDoc .

:violetSmith a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim, ex:Musician ;
    ex:firstName "Violet" ;
    ex:lastName "Smith" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Violet Smith" ;
    skos:altLabel "Miss Violet Smith" ;
    skos:altLabel "Miss Smith" ;
    skos:altLabel "the solitary cyclist" ;
    ex:description "Young, beautiful, tall, graceful, queenly woman. Daughter of James Smith, the orchestra conductor at the old Imperial Theatre. Music teacher employed by Bob Carruthers at Chiltern Grange at £100 per year to teach his daughter. An ardent bicyclist who cycled weekly between Chiltern Grange and Farnham Station. Engaged to Cyril Morton. Followed by a mysterious cyclist (later revealed to be Carruthers in disguise). Abducted and forced into marriage with Jack Woodley by the unfrocked clergyman Williamson. The marriage was later declared invalid. She inherited a large fortune from her uncle Ralph Smith and married Cyril Morton, becoming wife of the senior partner of Morton & Kennedy, Westminster electricians." ;
    ex:occupation "music teacher" ;
