:vonBork a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Spy ;
    ex:lastName "Von Bork" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Von Bork" ;
    skos:altLabel "the master spy" ;
    ex:description "A German master spy who spent four years in England posing as a hard-drinking, hard-riding sportsman and country squire. One of the Kaiser's most devoted agents, described as having a sunburned aquiline face, keen and handsome. Strong and self-contained. Maintained a country house on the English coast near Harwich perched on a great chalk cliff, with an oak-panelled study containing a brass-bound safe with a double combination lock (word: August, figures: 1914). The safe held pigeon-holes of intelligence labeled Fords, Harbour-defences, Aeroplanes, Ireland, Egypt, Portsmouth forts, The Channel, Rosythe, Naval Signals, and others. His wife and household left for Flushing the day before. His cousin Heinrich was the Imperial Envoy during the Irene Adler affair. His mother's elder brother was Count Von und Zu Grafenstein. Captured by Holmes via chloroform on the night of August 2, 1914, bound with straps, and taken to Scotland Yard." ;
    ex:occupation "spy" ;
    ex:capturedBy :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:cousinOf :heinrichVonBork ;
    ex:hasAgent :jackJames ;
    ex:hasAgent :hollisAgent ;
