:arthurHolder a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Arthur" ;
    ex:lastName "Holder" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Arthur Holder" ;
    ex:description "Son of Alexander Holder. Wild and wayward, a gambler who squandered money on cards and horse racing. Member of an aristocratic club where he fell under the influence of Sir George Burnwell. Deeply in love with his cousin Mary Holder, having proposed twice and been refused both times. On the night of the theft, saw Mary pass the coronet through the window to Burnwell. Pursued Burnwell into the stable lane, struggled with him over the coronet, struck Burnwell cutting him over the eye. Retrieved the coronet (minus the corner Burnwell had broken off) and was attempting to straighten it when his father discovered him. Refused to explain to protect Mary's secret. Was arrested and taken to a cell. Later vindicated when Holmes uncovered the truth." ;
    ex:childOf :alexanderHolder ;
    ex:cousinOf :maryHolder ;
    ex:knows :sirGeorgeBurnwell ;
    ex:livesAt :fairbank ;
    ex:accusedOf :berylCoronetTheft ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :berylCoronetDoc .

:arthurPinnerBeddington a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal, ex:Forger, ex:Cracksman ;
    ex:lastName "Beddington" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Arthur Pinner (Beddington)" ;
    skos:altLabel "Arthur Pinner" ;
    skos:altLabel "Harry Pinner" ;
    skos:altLabel "Beddington" ;
    ex:description "One of the two Beddington brothers, famous forgers and cracksmen who had recently emerged from five years of penal servitude. He posed as both Arthur Pinner (a financial agent in London) and Harry Pinner (managing director in Birmingham) to recruit Hall Pycroft away from Mawson & Williams. As Arthur Pinner: middle-sized, dark-haired, dark-eyed, black-bearded man with a brisk manner. As Harry Pinner: clean-shaven with lighter hair. Identified as the same person by a distinctive gold-stuffed second tooth on the left-hand side. Upon reading in the Evening Standard that his brother had been arrested for robbery and murder at Mawson's, he attempted suicide by hanging himself with his own braces from a hook behind a door. He was rescued by Watson, Holmes, and Pycroft." ;
    ex:occupation "forger and cracksman" ;
    ex:alias "Arthur Pinner, Financial Agent" ;
    ex:alias "Harry Pinner" ;
    ex:siblingOf :beddingtonBrother2 ;
    ex:impersonates :hallPycroft ;
    ex:locatedIn :126bCorporationStreet ;
    ex:memberOf :francoMidlandHardwareCompany ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :stockBrokersClerkDoc .

:athelneyJones a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Detective ;
    ex:firstName "Athelney" ;
    ex:lastName "Jones" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Athelney Jones" ;
    skos:altLabel "Inspector Jones" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Athelney Jones" ;
    ex:description "Athelney Jones is a Scotland Yard detective. Initially arrested Thaddeus Sholto, McMurdo, Mrs Bernstone, and Lal Rao for Bartholomew's murder. Had to release them all. Previously involved in Bishopgate jewel case where Holmes set them on right track. Worked with Holmes on Thames chase. Sociable in hours of relaxation. Took credit for capture of Jonathan Small." ;
    ex:occupation "police detective" ;
    ex:gender "male" ;
    ex:physicalDescription "Very stout, portly, red-faced, burly, plethoric, small twinkling eyes in swollen puffy pouches, husky voice" ;
    ex:investigatesCase :investigationSignOfFour ;
    ex:knows :johnWatson ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:memberOf :scotlandYard ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
