:beddingtonBrother2 a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal, ex:Forger, ex:Cracksman ;
    ex:lastName "Beddington" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Beddington (arrested at Mawson's)" ;
    skos:altLabel "Beddington the forger" ;
    ex:description "One of the two Beddington brothers, famous forgers and cracksmen recently out of five years penal servitude. He impersonated Hall Pycroft at Mawson & Williams, using a forged specimen of Pycroft's handwriting to secure the position. He obtained moulds of various locks and thorough knowledge of the strong room and safes. On Saturday, he entered the building pretending he had left something behind, murdered the armed watchman with a poker blow from behind, stuffed the body into the largest safe, and stole nearly a hundred thousand pounds worth of American railway bonds and scrip. He was spotted leaving with a carpet bag by Sergeant Tuson at twenty minutes past one, and after desperate resistance was arrested with the aid of Constable Pollack." ;
    ex:occupation "forger and cracksman" ;
    ex:siblingOf :arthurPinnerBeddington ;
    ex:impersonates :hallPycroft ;
    ex:employedBy :mawsonAndWilliams ;
    ex:arrestedBy :sergeantTuson ;
    ex:participatesIn :robberyAtMawsons ;
    ex:participatesIn :murderOfMawsonsWatchman ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :stockBrokersClerkDoc .

:beddoes a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Convict ;
    ex:lastName "Beddoes" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Beddoes" ;
    ex:description "A former convict who, like James Armitage (Mr. Trevor), returned to England as a rich colonial after the Gloria Scott affair and assumed a new identity. Lived in Hampshire near Fordingbridge with shooting preserves. Was blackmailed by Hudson the sailor. Sent the coded cipher letter to Trevor warning 'The game is up. Hudson has told all. Fly for your life.' The sporting cipher filler words (head-keeper, hen-pheasant, fly-paper) suggest he was an ardent sportsman. Holmes believed Beddoes, pushed to desperation and believing himself betrayed, killed Hudson and fled the country with as much money as possible. Neither Beddoes nor Hudson was ever heard from again." ;
    ex:occupation "Landowner with shooting preserves" ;
    ex:knows :jamesArmitage ;
    ex:knows :hudsonSailor ;
    ex:livesAt :hampshire ;
    ex:survivorOf :gloriaScottExplosion ;
    ex:blackmailedBy :hudsonSailor ;
    ex:wroteDocument :codedLetter ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :gloriaScottDoc .

:berylCoronetClient a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Illustrious Client of the Beryl Coronet" ;
    ex:description "An unnamed person of the highest social rank in England, whose name is described as a household word all over the earth, one of the highest, noblest, most exalted names in England. Visited Alexander Holder at his bank to borrow £50,000, leaving the beryl coronet as security. Expected repayment by the following Monday. The text deliberately withholds his identity. His name is not given in the text." ;
    ex:occupation "unnamed illustrious personage" ;
    ex:owns :berylCoronet ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :berylCoronetDoc .

:berylCoronetInspector a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:PoliceOfficer ;
    ex:prefLabel "Inspector in the Beryl Coronet Case" ;
    ex:description "An unnamed police inspector who responded to Alexander Holder's summons after discovering Arthur with the damaged coronet. Arrested Arthur Holder. Suggested that Holder consult Sherlock Holmes. The police openly confessed they could make nothing of the case. His name is not given in the text." ;
    ex:occupation "police inspector" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :berylCoronetDoc .

:berylCoronetReceiver a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Fence ;
    ex:prefLabel "Receiver of the Stolen Beryls" ;
    ex:description "An unnamed fence (receiver of stolen goods) who purchased the three stolen beryls from Sir George Burnwell for £600 each. Holmes obtained the receiver's address from Burnwell and bought back the stones at £1,000 apiece after much chaffering. His name is not given in the text." ;
    ex:occupation "fence (receiver of stolen goods)" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :berylCoronetDoc .

:berylStapleton a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Beryl" ;
    ex:lastName "Stapleton" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Beryl Stapleton" ;
    skos:altLabel "Beryl Garcia" ;
    skos:altLabel "Beryl" ;
    skos:altLabel "Miss Stapleton" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mrs. Stapleton" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mrs. Vandeleur" ;
    ex:description "Born Beryl Garcia, one of the beauties of Costa Rica. Wife of Jack Stapleton (Rodger Baskerville Jr./Vandeleur), forced to pose as his sister. Darker than any brunette Watson had seen in England, slim, elegant, and tall, with a proud finely-cut face, sensitive mouth, and beautiful dark eager eyes. Spoke with a curious lisp. Warned Watson (mistaking him for Sir Henry) to leave the moor. Again and again tried to warn Sir Henry. Stapleton was jealous and controlling; she was physically abused (arms mottled with bruises). On the night of the final ambush, Stapleton tied her up to prevent her warning Sir Henry. After rescue, she revealed the hound's hiding place on the island in the mire. Guided the search party into the mire the following day." ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :jackStapleton ;
    ex:knows :charlesBaskerville ;
    ex:knows :henryBaskerville ;
    ex:knows :jamesMortimer ;
    ex:knows :johnWatson ;
    ex:livesAt :merripitHouse ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :houndOfTheBaskervillesDoc .

:bill a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Bill" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Bill" ;
    ex:description "Bill is a small boy who works for Breckinridge at his stall in Covent Garden Market. He brought the account books when asked." ;
    ex:employedBy :breckinridge ;
    ex:worksAt :coventGardenMarket ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :blueCarbuncleDoc .

:billy a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Servant ;
    ex:prefLabel "Billy" ;
    skos:altLabel "Billy the page" ;
    ex:description "Page boy at 221B Baker Street who delivers mail and announces visitors. In The Valley of Fear, delivers Porlock's cipher message to Holmes. In the Mazarin Stone case, Billy plays a significant role: he is described as a young but very wise and tactful page who helped fill the gap of loneliness around Holmes. He manages the wax dummy of Holmes in the bow window, shows visitors in and out, and fetches Sam Merton from the street on Holmes's instructions. In the Mazarin Stone case, Billy is described as young but very wise and tactful, helping to fill up the gap of loneliness surrounding Holmes. He shows Watson the wax dummy, announces Count Sylvius, fetches Sam Merton from the street, and shows Lord Cantlemere out at the end. Opens the door at 221B Baker Street to announce visitors during the Thor Bridge case." ;
    ex:occupation "Page boy" ;
    ex:employedBy :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:worksAt :221bBakerStreet ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :valleyOfFearDoc ;
    dc:source :mazarinStoneDoc  ;
    dc:source :thorBridgeDoc .

:billyJames a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Billy" ;
    ex:lastName "James" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Little Billy James" ;
    ex:description "Young murder victim mentioned by Jacob Shafter as killed by the Scowrers." ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :valleyOfFearDoc .

:boscombeValleyCoroner a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Boscombe Valley Coroner" ;
    skos:altLabel "the Coroner" ;
    ex:description "Unnamed coroner who conducted the inquest into Charles McCarthy's death on the Tuesday after the murder. Questioned James McCarthy about the dying words, the quarrel, and the 'Cooee' cry. Made severe concluding remarks against James McCarthy. His name is not given in the text." ;
    ex:occupation "coroner" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :boscombeValleyMysteryDoc .

:boscombeValleyInspector a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Boscombe Valley Inspector" ;
    skos:altLabel "the inspector of constabulary" ;
    ex:description "Unnamed inspector of constabulary who informed James McCarthy that he was under arrest after James returned to Hatherley Farm. James remarked he was not surprised and that it was no more than his deserts. His name is not given in the text." ;
    ex:occupation "inspector of constabulary" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :boscombeValleyMysteryDoc .

:boscombeValleySurgeon a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Doctor ;
    ex:prefLabel "Boscombe Valley Surgeon" ;
    ex:description "Unnamed surgeon who gave a deposition at the inquest stating that the posterior third of the left parietal bone and the left half of the occipital bone had been shattered by a heavy blow from a blunt weapon. His name is not given in the text." ;
    ex:occupation "surgeon" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :boscombeValleyMysteryDoc .

:bossMcGinty a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "Jack" ;
    ex:lastName "McGinty" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Boss McGinty" ;
    skos:altLabel "Black Jack McGinty" ;
    skos:altLabel "Bodymaster McGinty" ;
    skos:altLabel "Councillor McGinty" ;
    ex:description "Bodymaster of Lodge 341, Vermissa Valley. Black-maned giant, bearded to the cheek-bones, with shock of raven hair, swarthy complexion, and dead black eyes with a slight squint. Also a municipal councillor and commissioner of roads. Runs the Union House saloon. Rules the valley through terror and corruption. Met his fate on the scaffold after Edwards's testimony." ;
    ex:occupation "Saloon-keeper; municipal councillor; commissioner of roads; Bodymaster of Lodge 341" ;
    ex:knows :johnDouglas, :tedBaldwin, :mikeScanlan ;
    ex:leaderOf :lodge341 ;
    ex:memberOf :eminentOrderOfFreemen, :lodge341 ;
    ex:owns :unionHouse ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :valleyOfFearDoc .

:boyInButtons a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Servant ;
    ex:prefLabel "Boy in Buttons" ;
    skos:altLabel "the boy in buttons" ;
    ex:description "The boy in buttons is the page boy at 221B Baker Street who announces Miss Mary Sutherland's arrival. Described as a small black figure. His name is not given in the text." ;
    ex:occupation "page boy" ;
    ex:worksAt :221bBakerStreet ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :caseOfIdentityDoc .

:breckinridge a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:lastName "Breckinridge" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Breckinridge" ;
    ex:description "Breckinridge is a salesman and proprietor of one of the largest stalls at Covent Garden Market. He is described as horsey-looking with a sharp face and trim side-whiskers, and carries a copy of the Sporting Times ('Pink Un'). He has a quick temper and was pestered by multiple people inquiring about the geese. He employs a boy named Bill. He supplied 24 geese from Mrs. Oakshott to Mr. Windigate of the Alpha Inn." ;
    ex:occupation "poultry salesman" ;
    ex:employs :bill ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes, :jamesRyder ;
    ex:suppliedBy :mrsOakshott ;
    ex:suppliesTo :windigate ;
