:duncanRoss a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "Duncan" ;
    ex:lastName "Ross" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Duncan Ross" ;
    skos:altLabel "Archie" ;
    skos:altLabel "William Morris" ;
    ex:description "Duncan Ross is John Clay's accomplice. A small man with very red hair. Ran the Red-headed League office at 7 Pope's Court, Fleet Street under the name Duncan Ross. Also used the alias William Morris, claiming to be a solicitor. The landlord at Pope's Court knew him as William Morris. During the tunnel emergence, Clay calls him 'Archie.' He escaped down the tunnel when Holmes sprang on Clay, though Jones clutched at his coat-tails. Three men were posted at the front door to intercept him. His real first name may be Archie; Duncan Ross and William Morris are both aliases." ;
    ex:alias "Archie" ;
    ex:alias "William Morris" ;
    ex:hairColor "very red" ;
    ex:physicalDescription "Small man with a head even redder than Wilson's. Pale face, shock of very red hair. Lithe and small." ;
    ex:accompliceOf :johnClay ;
    ex:knows :jabezWilson ;
    ex:knows :johnClay ;
