:edithBaxter a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Servant ;
    ex:firstName "Edith" ;
    ex:lastName "Baxter" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Edith Baxter" ;
    ex:description "Maid-servant at John Straker's household at King's Pyland. Carried supper (curried mutton) down to the stables for the night guard, Ned Hunter. Carried a lantern as the path ran across the open moor. Was accosted by Fitzroy Simpson who tried to bribe her with a new dress to deliver a paper to the stable-boy. Frightened by his manner, she ran to the stable window. Noticed the corner of a paper packet in Simpson's hand. Recognized Simpson's red and black silk cravat as having been worn by the stranger. Sworn testimony about the encounter." ;
    ex:occupation "maid-servant" ;
    ex:employedBy :johnStraker ;
    ex:worksAt :strakerVilla ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :silverBlazeDoc .

