:effieMunro a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Effie" ;
    ex:lastName "Munro" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Effie Munro" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mrs. Grant Munro" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mrs. Hebron" ;
    skos:altLabel "Effie" ;
    ex:description "Wife of Grant Munro, previously married to John Hebron of Atlanta as Mrs. Hebron. Went to America as a young woman and married Hebron, a lawyer of African descent. Had one daughter, Lucy. After Hebron died of yellow fever in Atlanta, she returned to England with approximately four thousand five hundred pounds capital. Lived with a maiden aunt at Pinner, Middlesex for six months before meeting and quickly marrying Grant Munro. Told Munro that both her first husband and child died of yellow fever, but her daughter Lucy had actually survived and was left in the care of a Scottish nurse in America. After three years of marriage to Munro, she secretly brought Lucy to England, installing her in a cottage near Norbury with the nurse, having the child wear a mask and gloves to conceal her appearance. Described as nervous and highly strung. Made over all her property to Munro on marriage. Her secret was discovered when Munro forced his way into the cottage with Holmes and Watson." ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :grantMunro ;
    ex:livesAt :grantMunroVilla ;
    ex:parentOf :lucyHebron ;
    ex:formerSpouse :johnHebron ;
    ex:owns :hebronSilverLocket ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :yellowFaceDoc .

:effiesMaidenAunt a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Effie's Maiden Aunt" ;
    ex:description "Unnamed maiden aunt living at Pinner in Middlesex. Effie came to live with her after returning from America following John Hebron's death. Effie lived with her for six months before meeting Grant Munro. Mentioned only briefly in Munro's account." ;
    ex:livesAt :pinner ;
    ex:auntOf :effieMunro ;
