:eliasOpenshaw a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:MilitaryOfficer, ex:Planter, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "Elias" ;
    ex:lastName "Openshaw" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Colonel Elias Openshaw" ;
    skos:altLabel "Colonel Openshaw" ;
    skos:altLabel "Uncle Elias" ;
    ex:description "John Openshaw's uncle. Emigrated to America as a young man and became a planter in Florida. During the American Civil War he fought in Jackson's army and afterwards under Hood, rising to the rank of colonel. Was a member of the Ku Klux Klan. After the war, returned to his plantation for three or four years. About 1869 or 1870, returned to Europe with a considerable fortune and took a small estate in Sussex near Horsham. His reason for leaving America was stated as his aversion to the negroes and his dislike of the Republican policy of extending the franchise. Was a singular man: fierce, quick-tempered, foul-mouthed, and reclusive. Drank heavily (brandy) and smoked. Had a locked lumber-room in the attic containing a brass box marked 'K.K.K.' with letters, memoranda, receipts, and a register related to Klan activities. In March 1883 received five orange pips from Pondicherry with 'K.K.K.' inscription. Burned the papers and made his will, leaving the estate to his brother Joseph. Found dead face-downward in a garden pool on May 2, 1883. The jury returned a verdict of suicide, but John suspected foul play." ;
    ex:occupation "planter" ;
    ex:causeOfDeath "Found face-downward in a green-scummed pool at the foot of the garden; verdict of suicide, suspected murder by KKK agents" ;
    ex:rank "Colonel" ;
    ex:title "Colonel" ;
    ex:arrivedFrom :florida ;
    ex:childOf :openshawGrandfather ;
    ex:isVictimOf :deathOfEliasOpenshaw ;
    ex:livesAt :openshawEstate ;
    ex:memberOf :kuKluxKlan ;
    ex:siblingOf :josephOpenshaw ;
    ex:uncleOf :johnOpenshaw ;
    ex:willed :josephOpenshaw ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :fiveOrangePipsDoc .

