:elise a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Elise" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Elise" ;
    skos:altLabel "the woman" ;
    skos:altLabel "the beautiful woman" ;
    ex:description "A woman residing at Dr. Becher's house with Colonel Lysander Stark. She spoke broken English and communicated with Stark in a foreign tongue (implied German). She was pretty with a dark, rich dress. She twice tried to warn Hatherley to leave and ultimately saved his life by opening a secret panel in the hydraulic press chamber. She called Stark 'Fritz' and begged him to remember his promise 'after the last time' not to harm Hatherley. She threw her arms around Stark to restrain him as Hatherley escaped. She later helped carry the unconscious Hatherley to safety near the road (evidenced by small footprints). She fled with the gang before police arrived. Holmes described her as 'the beautiful woman.'" ;
    ex:nationality "likely German" ;
    ex:hasPhysicalDescription "Pretty woman with dark, rich dress; spoke broken English and a foreign tongue; remarkably small feet." ;
    ex:livesAt :becherHouse ;
    ex:knows :lysanderStark ;
    ex:knows :mrFerguson ;
    ex:knows :victorHatherley ;
    ex:rescued :victorHatherley ;
    ex:memberOf :starkCounterfeitingGang ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :engineersThumbDoc .

