:eyfordPlainClothesMan a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:PoliceOfficer ;
    ex:prefLabel "Eyford Plain-Clothes Man" ;
    skos:altLabel "the plain-clothes man" ;
    ex:description "A plain-clothes police officer who accompanied Holmes, Watson, Bradstreet, and Hatherley on the train to Eyford. He suggested the criminals' base was to the west, noting 'several quiet little villages up there.'" ;
    ex:occupation "police officer (plain-clothes)" ;
    ex:knows :inspectorBradstreet ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :engineersThumbDoc .

:eyfordPorter a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Eyford Station Porter" ;
    skos:altLabel "the sleepy porter" ;
    ex:description "A porter at Eyford Station who was on duty when Hatherley arrived late at night. He was the only person on the platform, carrying a lantern. The same porter was on duty the next morning when Hatherley returned wounded. He had never heard of Colonel Lysander Stark and had not observed a carriage waiting the night before." ;
    ex:occupation "railway porter" ;
    ex:worksAt :eyfordStation ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :engineersThumbDoc .

:eyfordStationMaster a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:StationMaster ;
    ex:prefLabel "Eyford Station-Master" ;
    skos:altLabel "the station-master" ;
    ex:description "The station-master at Eyford Station who reported that Dr. Becher's house was on fire. He described Dr. Becher as an Englishman with a well-lined waistcoat and mentioned that Becher had a thin foreign gentleman staying with him as a patient. He laughed heartily when asked if Becher was a thin German." ;
    ex:occupation "station-master" ;
    ex:worksAt :eyfordStation ;
    ex:knows :drBecher ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :engineersThumbDoc .

:wombwell a ex:RealPerson, ex:Showman ;
    ex:lastName "Wombwell" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Wombwell" ;
    ex:description "Wombwell is a real historical showman mentioned as a rival of Ronder and one of the greatest showmen of his day." ;
    ex:occupation "showman" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :veiledLodgerDoc .

:yeggman a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:prefLabel "The Yeggman" ;
    ex:description "The Yeggman is mentioned in Holmes's index volume in connection with Vanderbilt. A yeggman is slang for a burglar or safe-cracker. No further details are given in the text." ;
    ex:associatedWith :vanderbilt ;
    ex:occupation "yeggman (burglar)" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :sussexVampireDoc .

:youngPerkins a ex:FictionalPerson , ex:Victim ;
    ex:lastName "Perkins" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Young Perkins" ;
    skos:altLabel "Perkins" ;
    ex:description "A young man who was killed outside the Holborn Bar. Steve Dixie is implicated in his death. Holmes uses knowledge of this killing as leverage over Dixie." ;
    ex:victimOf :killingOfPerkins ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :threeGablesDoc .

:ezekiahHopkins a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Ezekiah" ;
    ex:lastName "Hopkins" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Ezekiah Hopkins" ;
    ex:description "Ezekiah Hopkins is a fictitious American millionaire from Lebanon, Pennsylvania, U.S.A. Allegedly red-headed, with great sympathy for all red-headed men. Supposedly left his enormous fortune in the hands of trustees for the Red-headed League. Started from London when young. Entirely invented as part of John Clay's scheme." ;
    ex:hairColor "red" ;
    ex:livesAt :lebanonPennsylvania ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :redHeadedLeagueDoc .

:fitzroySimpson a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Suspect ;
    ex:firstName "Fitzroy" ;
    ex:lastName "Simpson" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Fitzroy Simpson" ;
    skos:altLabel "Simpson" ;
    ex:description "Man of excellent birth and education who had squandered a fortune upon the turf and lived by doing quiet, genteel bookmaking in the sporting clubs of London. Person of gentlemanly bearing, dressed in a gray suit of tweeds with a cloth cap and gaiters. Extremely pale face and nervous manner, age over thirty. Had registered bets of five thousand pounds against Silver Blaze. Came to Dartmoor hoping to get information about the King's Pyland horses and Desborough. Attempted to bribe Edith Baxter and Ned Hunter for racing tips. His red and black silk cravat was found in the dead man's hand. Carried a Penang-lawyer stick weighted with lead. Had twice lodged at Tavistock in the summer so was not a stranger to the district. Arrested by Inspector Gregory on circumstantial evidence. Volunteered a statement. Turned very pale when confronted with his cravat. His wet clothing showed he had been out in the storm. No wound on his person. Ultimately exonerated by Holmes who deduced Straker was the real criminal." ;
    ex:occupation "bookmaker" ;
    ex:owns :penangLawyerStick, :simpsonCravat, :simpsonBettingBook ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :silverBlazeDoc .

:floraMillar a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Danseuse ;
    ex:firstName "Flora" ;
    ex:lastName "Millar" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Flora Millar" ;
    skos:altLabel "Miss Flora Millar" ;
    ex:description "Formerly a danseuse at the Allegro. Had known Lord St. Simon for some years on a 'very friendly footing.' Described as hot-headed and devotedly attached to St. Simon. Wrote dreadful letters when she heard of his marriage. Caused a disturbance at the Doran house after the wedding, trying to force her way in and uttering abusive expressions towards the bride and even threatening her. Ejected by butler and footman. Later arrested on suspicion of involvement in the bride's disappearance. Was seen walking with Hatty Doran in Hyde Park, though Hatty's account suggests the encounter was incidental - Flora talked to her about St. Simon having secrets before marriage." ;
    ex:occupation "Danseuse" ;
    ex:formerPartnerOf :lordRobertStSimon ;
    ex:worksAt :allegro ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :nobleBachelorDoc .

:fordham a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Lawyer ;
    ex:lastName "Fordham" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Fordham" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Fordham" ;
    ex:description "A lawyer in Horsham. Called upon by Colonel Elias Openshaw in March 1883 to witness his will after receiving the threatening letter with orange pips." ;
    ex:occupation "lawyer" ;
    ex:worksAt :horsham ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :fiveOrangePipsDoc .

:foremanBlaker a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim ;
    ex:lastName "Blaker" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Foreman Blaker" ;
    skos:altLabel "Blaker" ;
    ex:description "Foreman who turned off three lodge members, earning a long-owed grudge from Baldwin." ;
    ex:occupation "Foreman" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :valleyOfFearDoc .

:francisHayMoulton a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Francis" ;
    ex:lastName "Moulton" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Francis Hay Moulton" ;
    skos:altLabel "Frank Moulton" ;
    skos:altLabel "Frank" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Moulton" ;
    skos:altLabel "Francis H. Moulton" ;
    skos:altLabel "F.H.M." ;
    ex:description "An American gentleman. Small, wiry, sunburnt man, clean-shaven, with a sharp face and alert manner. Met Hatty Doran in 1884 at McQuire's camp near the Rockies and they became engaged. When Aloysius Doran struck gold and refused the engagement, Frank followed Hatty to San Francisco and they secretly married with a clergyman. Frank went to seek his fortune, prospecting in Montana, Arizona, and New Mexico. Reported killed in an Apache Indian attack on a miners' camp, but was actually taken prisoner. Escaped, came to San Francisco, found Hatty had gone to England, followed her there. Saw announcement of the St. Simon wedding in a paper and attended the ceremony at St. George's Hanover Square. Passed a note to Hatty via the bouquet drop. After she fled the wedding breakfast, they went to lodgings at 226 Gordon Square. Had previously stayed at a select hotel on Northumberland Avenue. Holmes found them and persuaded them to make their situation public." ;
    ex:occupation "Prospector, miner" ;
    ex:nationality "American" ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :hattyDoran ;
    ex:knows :aliceMaid ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:knows :johnWatson ;
    ex:knows :lordRobertStSimon ;
    ex:livesAt :226GordonSquare ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :nobleBachelorDoc .

:francisProsper a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Greengrocer ;
    ex:firstName "Francis" ;
    ex:lastName "Prosper" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Francis Prosper" ;
    ex:description "A greengrocer who delivers vegetables to the Holder household at Fairbank. Has a wooden leg. Is the sweetheart of Lucy Parr. Was standing to the left of the kitchen door on the night of the theft, farther up the path than necessary. Holmes deduced his wooden leg from the round impressions in the snow." ;
    ex:occupation "greengrocer" ;
    ex:romanticPartnerOf :lucyParr ;
    ex:physicalDescription "has a wooden leg" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :berylCoronetDoc .

:francoisLeVillard a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Detective ;
    ex:firstName "Francois" ;
    ex:lastName "Le Villard" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Francois Le Villard" ;
    ex:description "Francois Le Villard is a French detective who has recently come to the front in the French detective service. Consulted Holmes about a will case. Has Celtic power of quick intuition but deficient in wide range of exact knowledge. Translating Holmes's small works into French. Wrote admiratory letter to Holmes." ;
    ex:occupation "detective" ;
    ex:gender "male" ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:memberOf :frenchDetectiveService ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :signOfTheFourDoc .

:frankland a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Frankland" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Frankland" ;
    skos:altLabel "Frankland of Lafter Hall" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Frankland" ;
    ex:description "Elderly man living at Lafter Hall near Grimpen. Father of Laura Lyons, though estranged from her. An amateur astronomer and litigious busybody who brings lawsuits for the pleasure of litigation, fighting for public rights of way and closing paths alternately. Has a powerful telescope mounted on the roof of his house. Threatened to prosecute Dr. Mortimer for opening a grave (the Neolithic skull at Long Down). His effigy was burned by locals. Inadvertently helped Watson locate Holmes by spotting the boy carrying food on the moor through his telescope. Gray-whiskered old man." ;
    ex:knows :charlesBaskerville ;
    ex:knows :jamesMortimer ;
    ex:knows :johnWatson ;
    ex:livesAt :lafterHall ;
    ex:owns :franklandsTelescopeObj ;
    ex:parentOf :lauraLyons ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :houndOfTheBaskervillesDoc .

:fraser a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:lastName "Fraser" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Fraser" ;
    ex:description "Consumptive tutor who met Vandeleur (Stapleton) on the voyage home to England. His teaching ability helped make St. Oliver's school a success. Died, after which the school declined." ;
    ex:occupation "tutor" ;
    ex:knows :jackStapleton ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :houndOfTheBaskervillesDoc .

:fredPorlock a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Informant ;
    ex:lastName "Porlock" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Fred Porlock" ;
    skos:altLabel "Porlock" ;
    ex:description "Pseudonymous informant who is a minor agent in Moriarty's criminal organization. Sends Holmes a cipher warning about danger to Douglas at Birlstone but then sends a second letter withdrawing due to fear of Moriarty's suspicion. His letters are posted from Camberwell." ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes, :professorMoriarty ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :valleyOfFearDoc .

