:grantMunro a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Grant" ;
    ex:lastName "Munro" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Grant Munro" ;
    skos:altLabel "Jack" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Grant Munro" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Munro" ;
    ex:description "Client of Sherlock Holmes in the Yellow Face case. A tall young man appearing about thirty but actually older, well but quietly dressed in a dark-gray suit with a brown wide-awake hat. A hop merchant with an income of seven or eight hundred pounds per year. Left-handed, muscular, with excellent teeth and careless habits. Smokes Grosvenor mixture tobacco in an old brier pipe. Married to Effie (formerly Mrs. Hebron) for three years, living in an eighty-pound-a-year villa at Norbury. A reserved, self-contained man with a dash of pride. Consulted Holmes about his wife's mysterious behavior involving a nearby cottage. At the climax, upon discovering his wife's mixed-race child from her first marriage, he responded nobly by lifting and kissing the child and taking his wife's hand." ;
    ex:occupation "hop merchant" ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :effieMunro ;
    ex:livesAt :grantMunroVilla ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes, :johnWatson ;
    ex:owns :grantMunroPipe, :grantMunroHat ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :yellowFaceDoc .

:grimesByRoylott a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal, ex:Doctor, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Grimesby" ;
    ex:lastName "Roylott" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Dr. Grimesby Roylott" ;
    skos:altLabel "Dr. Roylott" ;
    ex:description "Dr. Grimesby Roylott is the last survivor of the Roylotts of Stoke Moran, one of the oldest Saxon families in England. He is the stepfather of Helen and Julia Stoner, having married their mother Mrs. Stoner (the young widow of Major-General Stoner of the Bengal Artillery) while in India. He took a medical degree funded by a relative's advance and established a large practice in Calcutta. In a fit of anger over robberies, he beat his native butler to death and narrowly escaped a capital sentence, serving a long term of imprisonment. After returning to England and his wife's death in a railway accident near Crewe, he took his stepdaughters to live at Stoke Moran. He became violent and quarrelsome, the terror of the village, hurling the local blacksmith over a parapet. A man of immense strength, he bent a steel poker at 221B Baker Street. He had hereditary violence of temper intensified by long residence in the tropics. He kept Indian animals—a cheetah, baboon, and a swamp adder—sent by a correspondent. He murdered Julia Stoner by training the swamp adder to travel through a ventilator and down a dummy bell-rope to her bed. He was killed by the same snake when Holmes struck it back through the ventilator. Found dead in his room, the snake coiled around his brow—the 'speckled band.' He stood to lose 250 pounds per daughter's marriage from his wife's estate. He is described as very tall, with a large sun-burned face seared with wrinkles, deep-set bile-shot eyes, and a high thin fleshless nose." ;
    ex:occupation "Doctor of medicine" ;
    ex:causeOfDeath "Bitten by his own swamp adder" ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :mrsStoner ;
    ex:knows :helenStoner ;
    ex:knows :johnWatson ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:livesAt :stokeMoranManorHouse ;
    ex:memberOf :roylottFamily ;
    ex:owns :dogWhip ;
    ex:owns :roylottBaboon ;
    ex:owns :roylottCheetah ;
    ex:owns :roylottIronSafe ;
    ex:owns :swampAdder ;
    ex:stepparentOf :helenStoner ;
    ex:stepparentOf :juliaStoner ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :speckledBandDoc .

:grimpenPostmaster a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Grimpen postmaster" ;
    skos:altLabel "the village grocer" ;
    ex:description "Postmaster and village grocer of Grimpen. Father of James. Had a clear recollection of delivering Holmes's test telegram to Mr. Barrymore." ;
    ex:occupation "postmaster, grocer" ;
    ex:livesAt :grimpen ;
    ex:parentOf :grimpenPostmasterBoy ;
