:helenStoner a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Helen" ;
    ex:lastName "Stoner" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Helen Stoner" ;
    skos:altLabel "Miss Roylott" ;
    skos:altLabel "Miss Stoner" ;
    ex:description "Helen Stoner is a young woman of about thirty living with her stepfather Dr. Grimesby Roylott at Stoke Moran Manor House on the western border of Surrey. She is the twin sister of the late Julia Stoner and daughter of the late Mrs. Stoner and the late Major-General Stoner of the Bengal Artillery. Her hair is prematurely grey and her expression weary and haggard. She consulted Holmes in April 1883 about her sister's mysterious death two years earlier and the recent recurrence of the same nocturnal whistle now that she has been moved into Julia's room. She is engaged to Percy Armitage, second son of Mr. Armitage of Crane Water near Reading. She learned of Holmes through Mrs. Farintosh. She was taken to her aunt Miss Honoria Westphail at Harrow after the resolution of the case. Roylott had left bruise marks on her wrist." ;
    ex:childOf :majorGeneralStoner ;
    ex:childOf :mrsStoner ;
    ex:engagedTo :percyArmitage ;
    ex:knows :johnWatson ;
    ex:knows :mrsFarintosh ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:livesAt :stokeMoranManorHouse ;
    ex:nieceOf :honoriaWestphail ;
    ex:stepchildOf :grimesByRoylott ;
    ex:twinOf :juliaStoner ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :speckledBandDoc .

:henryBaker a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Henry" ;
    ex:lastName "Baker" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Henry Baker" ;
    ex:description "Henry Baker is a large man with rounded shoulders, a massive head, and a broad intelligent face sloping down to a pointed beard of grizzled brown. He has a touch of red in his nose and cheeks with a slight tremor of his hand, suggesting a drinking habit. He wears a rusty black frock-coat and presents as a man of learning and letters who has fallen upon hard times. He frequents the Alpha Inn near the British Museum and spends his days in the Museum itself. He was a member of Windigate's goose club. On Christmas morning, he was accosted by roughs on Tottenham Court Road and fled, leaving his hat and goose. He was entirely innocent of any involvement with the blue carbuncle." ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :mrsHenryBaker ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes, :johnWatson ;
    ex:memberOf :alphaInnGooseClub ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :blueCarbuncleDoc .

:henryBaskerville a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Henry" ;
    ex:lastName "Baskerville" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Sir Henry Baskerville" ;
    skos:altLabel "Henry Baskerville" ;
    skos:altLabel "Sir Henry" ;
    ex:description "Nephew of Sir Charles Baskerville, son of the middle Baskerville brother. About thirty years of age, small, alert, dark-eyed, sturdily built with thick black eyebrows and a pugnacious face. Had been farming in Canada. Last of the Baskervilles. Inherited the estate worth close to a million pounds. Arrived at Southampton and stayed at Northumberland Hotel in London. Received warning letter about the moor. Had boots stolen (one new brown, one old black). Traveled to Baskerville Hall accompanied by Watson. Fell in love with Beryl Stapleton. Attacked by the hound on the moor path from Merripit House but survived. Suffered shattered nerves and traveled round the world with Dr. Mortimer to recover." ;
    ex:childOf :henryBaskFather ;
    ex:knows :berylStapleton ;
    ex:knows :elizaBarrymore ;
    ex:knows :jackStapleton ;
    ex:knows :jamesMortimer ;
    ex:knows :johnBarrymore ;
    ex:knows :johnWatson ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:livesAt :baskervilleHall ;
    ex:memberOf :baskervilleFamily ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :houndOfTheBaskervillesDoc .

:henryBaskFather a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:lastName "Baskerville" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Henry's father" ;
    ex:description "Middle brother of the three Baskerville brothers (elder being Sir Charles, youngest being Rodger). Died when Henry was in his teens. Lived in a little cottage on the South Coast. His name is not given in the text." ;
    ex:memberOf :baskervilleFamily ;
    ex:parentOf :henryBaskerville ;
    ex:siblingOf :charlesBaskerville ;
    ex:siblingOf :rodgerBaskerville ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :houndOfTheBaskervillesDoc .

