:jackStapleton a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "Jack" ;
    ex:lastName "Stapleton" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Jack Stapleton" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Stapleton" ;
    skos:altLabel "Rodger Baskerville Jr." ;
    skos:altLabel "Stapleton" ;
    skos:altLabel "Vandeleur" ;
    skos:altLabel "the naturalist" ;
    ex:description "True name Rodger Baskerville, son of Rodger Baskerville (the youngest of the three Baskerville brothers). Alias Vandeleur, then Stapleton. Married Beryl Garcia of Costa Rica but presented her as his sister. Small, slim, clean-shaven, prim-faced, flaxen-haired and lean-jawed, between thirty and forty. Naturalist devoted to entomology and botany. Recognized authority on Lepidoptera; the name Vandeleur permanently attached to a moth he described. Previously ran St. Oliver's private school in east Yorkshire which failed after an epidemic killed three boys. Cultivated friendship with Sir Charles to plot his murder using a hound trained with luminous paste. Used Laura Lyons to lure Sir Charles to the moor-gate. Bought the hound from Ross and Mangles in Fulham Road and hid it on an island in Grimpen Mire. After the ambush at Merripit House failed, fled into the Grimpen Mire and is presumed dead." ;
    ex:occupation "naturalist, former schoolmaster" ;
    ex:childOf :rodgerBaskerville ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :berylStapleton ;
    ex:knows :charlesBaskerville ;
    ex:knows :henryBaskerville ;
    ex:knows :jamesMortimer ;
    ex:knows :johnWatson ;
    ex:knows :lauraLyons ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:livesAt :merripitHouse ;
    ex:memberOf :baskervilleFamily ;
    ex:owns :theHound ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :houndOfTheBaskervillesDoc .

:jacobShafter a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Jacob" ;
    ex:lastName "Shafter" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Jacob Shafter" ;
    skos:altLabel "Old Shafter" ;
    skos:altLabel "Old man Shafter" ;
    ex:description "Heavy, elderly German man who runs a boarding house on Sheridan Street, Vermissa. Father of Ettie. Honest man who despises the Scowrers. Banishes McMurdo from the house when he learns McMurdo is a Freeman. Later witness at Edwards and Ettie's wedding in Chicago." ;
    ex:occupation "Boarding house owner" ;
    ex:livesAt :sheridanStreet ;
    ex:parentOf :ettieShafter ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :valleyOfFearDoc .

:jaInitials a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "J.A." ;
    ex:description "An unidentified person whose initials 'J.A.' were tattooed on old Mr. Trevor's (James Armitage's) arm at the bend of the elbow. Trevor had attempted to obliterate the tattoo. When Holmes deduced the initials and their significance, Trevor fainted. Trevor later referred to 'the ghosts of our old lovers' in connection with the initials. The identity of J.A. is never revealed; it is possible the initials represent James Armitage's own name from before his conviction, tattooed as a personal mark." ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :gloriaScottDoc .

:jamesArmitage a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Convict, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "James" ;
    ex:lastName "Armitage" ;
    ex:prefLabel "James Armitage" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Trevor" ;
    skos:altLabel "old Trevor" ;
    skos:altLabel "Trevor senior" ;
    skos:altLabel "Justice of the Peace Trevor" ;
    ex:description "Real name James Armitage; lived under the assumed name Trevor as a Justice of the Peace and landed proprietor at Donnithorpe, Norfolk. A widower with one son (Victor) and a deceased daughter who died of diphtheria in Birmingham. Thick-set, burly man with a shock of grizzled hair, brown weather-beaten face, and keen blue eyes. Had a reputation for kindness and charity, noted for lenient sentences from the bench. Had boxed in his youth, made money at the gold fields, traveled to New Zealand and Japan. Had a J.A. tattoo on his arm (initials of a former lover) which he tried to obliterate. As a young man (James Armitage), worked at a London banking house and embezzled money to pay a debt of honor. Convicted at age 23 and sentenced to transportation. Was convict aboard the bark Gloria Scott from Falmouth (Oct 8, 1855). After the mutiny and explosion, was among dissenters who took a boat, picked up by brig Hotspur, landed at Sydney. Changed name, went to gold diggings with Evans, returned to England as a rich colonial and bought a country estate. Blackmailed by Hudson the sailor for over 20 years. Died of apoplexy/stroke upon reading a coded cipher letter from Beddoes warning that Hudson had betrayed their secret." ;
    ex:occupation "Justice of the Peace; landed proprietor; former banking house clerk" ;
    ex:formerName "James Armitage" ;
    ex:causeOfDeath "Apoplexy (stroke) triggered by reading coded warning letter" ;
    ex:parentOf :victorTrevor ;
    ex:parentOf :trevorDaughter ;
    ex:knows :beddoes ;
    ex:knows :jackPrendergast ;
    ex:knows :evansConvict ;
    ex:knows :hudsonSailor ;
    ex:livesAt :trevorEstate ;
    ex:survivorOf :gloriaScottExplosion ;
    ex:blackmailedBy :hudsonSailor ;
    ex:hasParticipant :gloriaScottMutiny ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :gloriaScottDoc .

:jamesDesmond a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "James" ;
    ex:lastName "Desmond" ;
    ex:prefLabel "James Desmond" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. James Desmond" ;
    ex:description "Distant cousin of the Baskervilles, next heir to the estate after Sir Henry. Elderly clergyman in Westmoreland. Man of venerable appearance and saintly life. Visited Sir Charles once and refused any settlement. Holmes investigated and found him to be of amiable disposition, eliminating him as a suspect." ;
    ex:occupation "clergyman" ;
    ex:knows :charlesBaskerville ;
    ex:livesAt :westmoreland ;
    ex:memberOf :desmondFamily ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :houndOfTheBaskervillesDoc .

:jamesMcCarthy a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "James" ;
    ex:lastName "McCarthy" ;
    ex:prefLabel "James McCarthy" ;
    skos:altLabel "young McCarthy" , "young Mr. McCarthy" , "Mr. James McCarthy" ;
    ex:description "Only son of Charles McCarthy, eighteen years old. Accused of his father's murder based on circumstantial evidence. Had been away three days in Bristol visiting his secret wife. Carried a gun when walking toward Boscombe Pool. Witnessed the aftermath of his father's murder and ran to the lodge for help. His right hand and sleeve were stained with blood. At the inquest, refused to reveal the cause of his quarrel with his father (it concerned the proposed marriage to Alice Turner, which his secret marriage made impossible). Reported his father's dying reference to 'a rat' (actually 'Ballarat'). Saw something grey (a cloak) near the body that disappeared. Secretly married a barmaid in Bristol at a registry office about two years prior. Not quick-witted but comely and sound at heart. Madly in love with Alice Turner. Acquitted at the Assizes based on objections drawn by Holmes." ;
    ex:age 18 ;
    ex:childOf :charlesMcCarthy ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :jamesMcCarthyBarmaidWife ;
    ex:knows :aliceTurner, :williamCrowder ;
    ex:owns :jamesMcCarthyGun ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :boscombeValleyMysteryDoc .

:jamesMcCarthyBarmaidWife a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "James McCarthy's Barmaid Wife" ;
    ex:description "An unnamed barmaid from Bristol whom James McCarthy secretly married at a registry office about two years before the story events, when he was only a lad. Upon learning from the papers that James was in serious trouble and likely to be hanged, she threw him over and wrote to say she already had a husband in the Bermuda Dockyard, meaning there was no legal tie between them. Her name is not given in the text." ;
    ex:occupation "barmaid" ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :jamesMcCarthy ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :boscombeValleyMysteryDoc .

:jamesMortimer a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Doctor ;
    ex:firstName "James" ;
    ex:lastName "Mortimer" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Dr. James Mortimer" ;
    skos:altLabel "Dr. Mortimer" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mortimer" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Mortimer" ;
    ex:description "Medical practitioner, M.R.C.S. (1882). House-surgeon at Charing Cross Hospital from 1882 to 1884. Winner of the Jackson Prize for Comparative Pathology. Corresponding member of the Swedish Pathological Society. Author of 'Some Freaks of Atavism' (Lancet, 1882) and 'Do We Progress?' (Journal of Psychology, March 1883). Medical Officer for the parishes of Grimpen, Thorsley, and High Barrow. Personal friend and medical attendant of Sir Charles Baskerville, and trustee and executor of his will. Tall, thin man with a long beak-like nose, keen gray eyes, gold-rimmed glasses. Enthusiast in craniology and anthropology. Married. Owns a curly-haired spaniel. Received one thousand pounds from Sir Charles's will. Traveled round the world with Sir Henry after the case to restore the baronet's health." ;
    ex:occupation "medical practitioner, medical officer" ;
    ex:knows :berylStapleton ;
    ex:knows :charlesBaskerville ;
    ex:knows :frankland ;
    ex:knows :henryBaskerville ;
    ex:knows :jackStapleton ;
    ex:knows :johnWatson ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:livesAt :grimpen ;
    ex:memberOf :swedishPathologicalSociety ;
    ex:owns :mortimersSpaniel ;
    ex:worksAt :charingCrossHospital ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :houndOfTheBaskervillesDoc .

:jamesMurdoch a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim ;
