:jamesWindibank a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "James" ;
    ex:lastName "Windibank" ;
    ex:prefLabel "James Windibank" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Windibank" ;
    ex:description "James Windibank is Mary Sutherland's stepfather, about thirty years of age, clean-shaven and sallow-skinned, with a bland insinuating manner and sharp penetrating grey eyes. He is a traveller in wines for Westhouse & Marbank, the great claret importers of Fenchurch Street. Only five years and two months older than Mary. Married Mary's mother, who is nearly fifteen years older than him, soon after her first husband's death. Made his wife sell the plumbing business for 4700 pounds. Draws Mary's quarterly interest and pays it to his wife. Disguised himself as Hosmer Angel -- covering his eyes with tinted glasses, masking his face with a moustache and bushy whiskers, disguising his voice as a hesitating whisper -- to prevent Mary from marrying and losing her income to the household. With his wife's connivance, he courted Mary as Angel at the gasfitters' ball, became engaged, and arranged a wedding at St. Saviour's, then vanished from a four-wheeler using the trick of stepping in one door and out the other. His typewritten note to Holmes showed the same defects as Hosmer Angel's letters. Confronted by Holmes, admitted the scheme, claimed it was not actionable, and fled down the street when Holmes reached for a hunting crop." ;
    ex:occupation "traveller in wines" ;
    ex:age "about thirty" ;
    ex:disguisedAs :hosmerAngel ;
    ex:employedBy :westhouseAndMarbank ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :mrsWindibank ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes, :johnWatson, :marySutherland ;
    ex:livesAt :31LyonPlace ;
    ex:stepparentOf :marySutherland ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :caseOfIdentityDoc .

