:jeffersonHope a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal, ex:Cabman ;
    ex:firstName "Jefferson" ;
    ex:lastName "Hope" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Jefferson Hope" ;
    ex:description "Jefferson Hope is the murderer of Enoch Drebber and Joseph Stangerson. A cab driver in London, he is tall, powerfully built, with a dark sunburned face. From the Jefferson Hopes of St. Louis. A former hunter, scout, trapper, silver explorer, ranchman, and pioneer in California. Loved Lucy Ferrier and was engaged to marry her. After Lucy was forced to marry Drebber and died, Hope spent over twenty years pursuing Drebber and Stangerson across America and Europe for revenge. Tracked them from Cleveland to St. Petersburg to Paris to Copenhagen to London. Poisoned Drebber at 3 Lauriston Gardens using pills containing South American arrow poison alkaloid. Stabbed Stangerson at Halliday's Private Hotel in self-defence. Had an aortic aneurism from years of exposure. Captured by Holmes at 221B Baker Street. Died in police cell the night after capture when his aneurism burst." ;
    ex:occupation "cab driver, hunter, scout, trapper, silver explorer, ranchman" ;
    ex:causeOfDeath "aortic aneurism burst" ;
    ex:nationality "American" ;
    ex:engagedTo :lucyFerrier ;
    ex:murders :enochDrebber ;
    ex:murders :josephStangerson ;
    ex:knows :cowper ;
