    skos:altLabel "Barrymore" ;
    skos:altLabel "the butler" ;
    ex:description "Butler at Baskerville Hall. Tall, handsome man with a square black beard and pale, distinguished features. Son of the old caretaker who is dead. Family has looked after the Hall for four generations. Received 500 pounds in Sir Charles's will. Found Sir Charles's body. Signaled with candle to Selden (his wife's brother) on the moor at night to indicate food was ready. Somewhat deaf. Revealed the L.L. letter clue about Sir Charles's appointment. Gave Sir Henry's old clothes to Selden via Mrs. Barrymore." ;
