:johnTurner a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:LandOwner, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "John" ;
    ex:lastName "Turner" ;
    ex:prefLabel "John Turner" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Turner" , "Turner" , "old Turner" , "Black Jack of Ballarat" ;
    ex:description "The largest landed proprietor in Boscombe Valley, Herefordshire. About sixty years old. Made his money in Australia. A strange and impressive figure with a slow limping step, bowed shoulders, tangled beard, grizzled hair, and enormous limbs. Suffering from diabetes and in failing health — his doctor gave him a month to live. In the early 1860s, was a highway robber known as Black Jack of Ballarat, leader of the Ballarat Gang in the Colony of Victoria. During a gold convoy robbery from Ballarat to Melbourne, spared the wagon-driver Charles McCarthy. Returned to England wealthy, bought the Boscombe Valley estate, married (wife died young), and raised his daughter Alice. Was blackmailed by McCarthy for twenty years after McCarthy recognized him on Regent Street, London. Gave McCarthy Hatherley Farm rent-free and provided extensive financial support. Murdered McCarthy at Boscombe Pool with a jagged stone when McCarthy demanded Alice marry his son James. Left-handed, limped on right leg, wore thick-soled shooting boots and a grey cloak, smoked Indian cigars with a cigar-holder. Confessed to Holmes and signed a written statement witnessed by Watson. Died seven months after the interview with Holmes." ;
    ex:occupation "landowner, former highway robber" ;
    ex:hasFormerAlias "Black Jack of Ballarat" ;
    ex:hasMedicalCondition "diabetes" ;
    ex:age 60 ;
    ex:blackmailedBy :charlesMcCarthy ;
    ex:employs :williamCrowder, :patienceMoranFather ;
    ex:hasAsTenant :charlesMcCarthy ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :johnTurnerWife ;
    ex:knows :charlesMcCarthy, :drWillows ;
    ex:livesAt :turnerHall ;
    ex:memberOf :ballaratGang ;
    ex:owns :hatherleyFarm, :turnerHall, :greyCloak ;
    ex:parentOf :aliceTurner ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :boscombeValleyMysteryDoc .

