:juliaStoner a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Julia" ;
    ex:lastName "Stoner" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Julia Stoner" ;
    ex:description "Julia Stoner is the twin sister of Helen Stoner and daughter of Mrs. Stoner and Major-General Stoner of the Bengal Artillery. She was thirty years old at the time of her death, with hair already beginning to whiten. She died approximately two years before April 1883 in her locked bedroom at Stoke Moran Manor House. She had become engaged to a half-pay major of marines whom she met at Miss Honoria Westphail's house at Christmas. Within a fortnight of the date fixed for her wedding, she was found dying, having screamed in terror. Her last words were 'Oh, my God! Helen! It was the band! The speckled band!' pointing toward Dr. Roylott's room. In her right hand was a charred match stump and in her left a matchbox. She had heard a low whistle in the night for several nights before her death. She was killed by a swamp adder sent through the ventilator by her stepfather." ;
    ex:causeOfDeath "Bitten by a swamp adder" ;
    ex:childOf :majorGeneralStoner ;
    ex:childOf :mrsStoner ;
    ex:engagedTo :juliaFiance ;
    ex:knows :helenStoner ;
    ex:livesAt :stokeMoranManorHouse ;
    ex:nieceOf :honoriaWestphail ;
    ex:stepchildOf :grimesByRoylott ;
    ex:twinOf :helenStoner ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :speckledBandDoc .

