:lauraLyons a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Laura" ;
    ex:lastName "Lyons" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Laura Lyons" ;
    skos:altLabel "L.L." ;
    skos:altLabel "Mrs. Laura Lyons" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mrs. Lyons" ;
    ex:description "Daughter of Frankland of Lafter Hall. Married an artist named Lyons who publicly deserted her. Lives in Coombe Tracey. Extremely beautiful woman with rich hazel eyes and hair, freckled cheeks. Had a Remington typewriter. Supported partly by Sir Charles's generosity, arranged through Stapleton. Stapleton, representing himself as unmarried, led her to believe he would marry her if she obtained a divorce. At Stapleton's dictation, she wrote a letter to Sir Charles asking him to meet at the gate at ten o'clock on the night of his death, but claims she did not keep the appointment because Stapleton dissuaded her. When Holmes revealed Stapleton was married, she cooperated fully." ;
    ex:childOf :frankland ;
