:lordRobertStSimon a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Aristocrat, ex:Client, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Robert" ;
    ex:lastName "St. Simon" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Lord Robert St. Simon" ;
    skos:altLabel "Lord St. Simon" ;
    skos:altLabel "Lord Robert Walsingham de Vere St. Simon" ;
    skos:altLabel "Robert" ;
    ex:description "Lord Robert Walsingham de Vere St. Simon, second son of the Duke of Balmoral, born in 1846. Forty-one years of age. Former Under-Secretary for the colonies. Inherits Plantagenet blood by direct descent and Tudor on the distaff side. His only property is the small estate of Birchmoor. A man with a pleasant, cultured face, high-nosed and pale, with something of petulance about the mouth, slight forward stoop, grizzled hair thin on top. Foppish dresser with high collar, black frock-coat, white waistcoat, yellow gloves, patent-leather shoes, light-coloured gaiters, and golden eyeglasses. Married Hatty Doran at St. George's Hanover Square, but she disappeared at the wedding breakfast. The marriage was arranged partly because his father had been compelled to sell his pictures and the family needed the Doran fortune. He engaged Holmes to find his wife and Lestrade of Scotland Yard was also investigating. The bride was ultimately found to have a prior husband, Francis Hay Moulton. Lord St. Simon received the news with offended dignity and refused Holmes's invitation to supper." ;
    ex:occupation "Aristocrat, former Under-Secretary for the colonies" ;
    ex:birthYear "1846"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ex:formerTitle "Under-Secretary for the colonies" ;
    ex:childOf :dukeOfBalmoral ;
    ex:childOf :duchessOfBalmoral ;
    ex:clientOf :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:formerPartnerOf :floraMillar ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :hattyDoran ;
