:lucyFerrier a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Lucy" ;
    ex:lastName "Ferrier" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Lucy Ferrier" ;
    skos:altLabel "Lucy" ;
    ex:description "Lucy Ferrier is the adopted daughter of John Ferrier. Found as a child of about five on the Great Alkali Plain, carried in a grey shawl by Ferrier. Fair-skinned, chestnut-haired. Grew up on Ferrier's farm in Salt Lake Valley, becoming a skilled rider. Fell in love with Jefferson Hope. After her father's murder by the Avenging Angels, she was forced to marry young Enoch Drebber. Died within a month of the forced marriage, broken-hearted. Her wedding ring was taken by Hope from her dead finger and carried for twenty years." ;
    ex:causeOfDeath "died of heartbreak within a month of forced marriage" ;
    ex:nationality "American" ;
    ex:adoptedByPerson :johnFerrier ;
    ex:engagedTo :jeffersonHope ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :enochDrebber ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :studyInScarletDoc .

:lucyHebron a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:firstName "Lucy" ;
    ex:lastName "Hebron" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Lucy Hebron" ;
    skos:altLabel "Lucy" ;
    ex:description "Daughter of Effie Munro and John Hebron. A little girl who took after her father's African heritage, described as darker than her father was. Her health was weak when her mother left America. Left in the care of a faithful Scottish woman who had been a servant to the Hebrons. Secretly brought to England by her mother and installed in a cottage at Norbury, where she wore a livid-colored mask and long white gloves to conceal her appearance during the daytime. Dressed in a red frock. Described as a little creature who ran to nestle against her mother. Holmes removed her mask at the climax of the story, revealing her identity." ;
    ex:childOf :effieMunro, :johnHebron ;
    ex:livesAt :cottageAtNorbury ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :yellowFaceDoc .

:lucyParr a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Servant ;
    ex:firstName "Lucy" ;
    ex:lastName "Parr" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Lucy Parr" ;
    ex:description "The second waiting-maid at Fairbank, only in Alexander Holder's service a few months. Came with an excellent character and gave satisfaction. Described as a very pretty girl who attracted admirers. Her sweetheart is Francis Prosper, a greengrocer with a wooden leg. Was present when Holder mentioned the coronet in the drawing-room. Slipped out the back door to meet Prosper by the side gate on the night of the theft." ;
    ex:occupation "waiting-maid" ;
    ex:employedBy :alexanderHolder ;
    ex:romanticPartnerOf :francisProsper ;
    ex:livesAt :fairbank ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :berylCoronetDoc .

:lucysMother a ex:FictionalPerson ;
