:maryHolder a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "Mary" ;
    ex:lastName "Holder" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Mary Holder" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mary" ;
    ex:description "Niece of Alexander Holder, daughter of his deceased brother who died five years before the story events. Adopted by Alexander and treated as his daughter. Age twenty-four, rather above middle height, slim, with dark hair and dark eyes against very pale skin. Described as sweet, loving, beautiful, a wonderful manager and housekeeper, yet tender, quiet, and gentle. Was secretly in a romantic relationship with Sir George Burnwell, seeing him nearly every evening. On the night of the theft, passed the beryl coronet through the hall window to Burnwell in the stable lane. Fled the Holder household overnight, leaving a farewell note, to join Burnwell." ;
    ex:age "24" ;
    ex:childOf :holderBrother ;
    ex:adoptedBy :alexanderHolder ;
