:mrsSawyer a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Mrs. Sawyer" ;
    ex:description "Mrs. Sawyer is the identity used by a young male accomplice of Jefferson Hope. He came to 221B Baker Street disguised as a very old wrinkled woman to claim the wedding ring. Claimed to live at 13 Duncan Street, Houndsditch, and that the ring belonged to her daughter Sally Dennis. The disguise was so effective that Holmes was fooled; the accomplice escaped from a four-wheeler cab while in motion." ;
    ex:knows :jeffersonHope ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :studyInScarletDoc .

