:tobiasGregson a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Detective ;
    ex:firstName "Tobias" ;
    ex:lastName "Gregson" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Tobias Gregson" ;
    skos:altLabel "Gregson" ;
    ex:description "Tobias Gregson is a Scotland Yard detective described by Holmes as the smartest of the Scotland Yarders. Tall, white-faced, flaxen-haired, with a notebook. Investigates the Lauriston Gardens murder. Arrests Arthur Charpentier based on his theory. Rival of Lestrade. Inspector Gregson is picked up at Scotland Yard by Holmes and party to accompany them to Beckenham for the rescue at The Myrtles. Referred to as 'Inspector Gregson' in this story. Works with Inspector Baynes of Surrey Constabulary on the Wisteria Lodge case. Traces Scott Eccles through his telegram to Holmes." ;
