:wilhelmVonOrmstein a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Monarch, ex:Client ;
    ex:firstName "Wilhelm" ;
    ex:lastName "von Ormstein" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Wilhelm Gottsreich Sigismond von Ormstein" ;
    skos:altLabel "Count Von Kramm" ;
    skos:altLabel "His Majesty" ;
    skos:altLabel "King of Bohemia" ;
    ex:description "Wilhelm Gottsreich Sigismond von Ormstein is the Grand Duke of Cassel-Felstein and hereditary King of Bohemia. Age thirty. Enormously tall (hardly less than six feet six inches) with the chest and limbs of a Hercules. Thick hanging lip and long straight chin. Arrived incognito from Prague to consult Holmes. Uses the alias Count Von Kramm. Stays at the Langham Hotel. Five years prior, during a visit to Warsaw, became entangled with Irene Adler. A compromising photograph of the two exists. About to marry Clotilde Lothman von Saxe-Meningen, second daughter of the King of Scandinavia. Five attempts to recover the photograph have failed (two burglaries, one luggage diversion, two waylayings). Offers carte blanche and pays 1000 pounds (300 gold, 700 notes). Offers emerald snake ring as reward but Holmes prefers the photograph. Arrives at Baker Street in a brougham. Wears astrakhan-trimmed double-breasted coat, flame-coloured silk-lined blue cloak, and a flaming beryl brooch. Referred to as 'the late King of Bohemia' in His Last Bow, indicating he had died by 1914." ;
    ex:occupation "King of Bohemia" ;
    ex:alias "Count Von Kramm" ;
    ex:nationality "Bohemian" ;
    ex:betrothedTo :clotildeLothmanVonSaxeMeningen ;
    ex:clientOf :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes, :ireneAdler ;
    ex:memberOf :houseOfOrmstein ;
