:abeSlaney a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "Abe" ;
    ex:lastName "Slaney" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Abe Slaney" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Abe Slaney" ;
    ex:description "An American criminal, described as a tall, handsome, swarthy fellow with a bristling black beard, a great aggressive hooked nose, blazing black eyes, wearing a grey flannel suit and a Panama hat and flourishing a cane. Identified by Wilson Hargreave of the New York Police Bureau as 'the most dangerous crook in Chicago.' A member of the Joint, a Chicago gang of seven. Had known Elsie Patrick since childhood and was engaged to her before she fled to London. After Elsie married Hilton Cubitt, Slaney tracked her down and stayed at Elrige's Farm near East Ruston, Norfolk for a month, sending messages in the dancing men cipher. His messages escalated from persuasion to threats. In the final confrontation at 3 AM, he tried to pull Elsie through the study window. Cubitt rushed in and fired at him, missing. Slaney returned fire, killing Cubitt with a shot through the heart. He was lured to Ridling Thorpe Manor by Holmes's decoy note in the dancing men cipher, arrested by Inspector Martin, and condemned to death at the Norwich winter assizes, later commuted to penal servitude." ;
    ex:nationality "American" ;
    ex:occupation "Criminal" ;
    ex:memberOf :theJoint ;
    ex:engagedTo :elsiePatrick ;
    ex:knows :elsiePatrick ;
    ex:knows :oldPatrick ;
    ex:kills :hiltonCubitt ;
    ex:livesAt :elrigesFarm ;
    ex:convictedAt :norwich ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :dancingMenDoc .

:elsiePatrick a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Elsie" ;
    ex:lastName "Patrick" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Elsie Patrick" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mrs. Hilton Cubitt" ;
    skos:altLabel "Elsie" ;
    skos:altLabel "Elsie Cubitt" ;
    ex:description "An American young woman, maiden name Patrick. Daughter of 'old Patrick,' the boss of the Joint, a Chicago criminal gang of seven members. She grew up around the gang and learned some of their ways, including the dancing men cipher, but could not stand the criminal business. She had been engaged to Abe Slaney. Having some honest money of her own, she gave the gang the slip and moved to London. She met Hilton Cubitt at a Russell Square boarding-house during the Jubilee and married him at a registry office, telling him she had disagreeable associations in her past but asking him not to inquire. After a year of happy marriage, dancing men messages from Slaney began appearing at Ridling Thorpe Manor, terrifying her. During the final confrontation, she came down at 3 AM to meet Slaney at the window with money to bribe him to leave. After her husband was shot dead, she attempted suicide, shooting herself through the front of the brain. She survived, recovered entirely, and remained a widow, devoting her life to care of the poor and administration of her husband's estate." ;
    ex:nationality "American" ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :hiltonCubitt ;
    ex:childOf :oldPatrick ;
    ex:livesAt :ridlingThorpeManor ;
    ex:knows :abeSlaney ;
    ex:knows :hiltonCubitt ;
    ex:engagedTo :abeSlaney ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :dancingMenDoc .

:hiltonCubitt a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim, ex:Squire, ex:Client ;
    ex:firstName "Hilton" ;
    ex:lastName "Cubitt" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Hilton Cubitt" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Cubitt" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Hilton Cubitt" ;
    ex:description "A tall, ruddy, clean-shaven Norfolk squire with earnest blue eyes and a broad, comely face. His family has been at Ridling Thorpe Manor for five centuries, one of the oldest and most honoured families in the County of Norfolk. He came to London for the Jubilee, stayed at a boarding-house in Russell Square, and met Elsie Patrick, an American woman. They married quietly at a registry office. After mysterious dancing men figures began appearing at his property and frightening his wife, he consulted Sherlock Holmes. He was shot through the heart by Abe Slaney during a confrontation at three in the morning, dying instantly. He had fired the first shot at Slaney." ;
    ex:occupation "Norfolk squire and landowner" ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :elsiePatrick ;
    ex:livesAt :ridlingThorpeManor ;
    ex:owns :ridlingThorpeManor ;
    ex:owns :cubittsRevolver ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:knows :johnWatson ;
    ex:knows :parkerVicar ;
    ex:knows :elsiePatrick ;
    ex:killedBy :abeSlaney ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :dancingMenDoc .

:inspectorMartin a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:PoliceOfficer ;
    ex:lastName "Martin" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Inspector Martin" ;
    ex:description "Inspector of the Norfolk Constabulary. A dapper little man with a quick, alert manner and a waxed moustache. He arrived at Ridling Thorpe Manor from Norwich by dog-cart. He cooperated fully with Holmes in the investigation and arrested Abe Slaney by slipping handcuffs on his wrists. He expressed admiration for Holmes's methods and hoped to work with him again." ;
    ex:occupation "Police inspector" ;
    ex:memberOf :norfolkConstabulary ;
    ex:arrests :abeSlaney ;
    ex:knows :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :dancingMenDoc .

:mrsKing a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Cook ;
    ex:lastName "King" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Mrs. King" ;
    ex:description "Cook at Ridling Thorpe Manor. She was awakened by the sound of an explosion and rushed to Saunders' room. They descended the stairs together and found Hilton Cubitt dead and Elsie wounded. She testified that the first explosion seemed very loud and was questioned by Holmes about whether it could have been two shots fired simultaneously." ;
    ex:occupation "Cook" ;
    ex:employedBy :hiltonCubitt ;
    ex:livesAt :ridlingThorpeManor ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :dancingMenDoc .

:northWalshamStationMaster a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "North Walsham station-master" ;
    ex:description "The unnamed station-master at North Walsham who hurried towards Holmes and Watson upon their arrival, assuming they were detectives from London. He informed them that Hilton Cubitt was dead and his wife gravely injured." ;
    ex:occupation "Station-master" ;
    ex:worksAt :northWalshamStation ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :dancingMenDoc .

:oldPatrick a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:lastName "Patrick" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Old Patrick" ;
    skos:altLabel "Elsie's father" ;
    skos:altLabel "Patrick" ;
    ex:description "Elsie Patrick's father. A clever man who was the boss of the Joint, a criminal gang of seven in Chicago. He invented the dancing men cipher, a secret writing system using stick figures that would pass as a child's scrawl unless one had the key to it." ;
    ex:occupation "Crime boss" ;
    ex:parentOf :elsiePatrick ;
    ex:leaderOf :theJoint ;
    ex:invented :dancingMenMessages ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :dancingMenDoc .

:parkerVicar a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Vicar ;
    ex:lastName "Parker" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Parker" ;
    ex:description "The vicar of Hilton Cubitt's parish in Norfolk. He was staying at a boarding-house in Russell Square when Cubitt came to London for the Jubilee, which is how Cubitt came to stay at the same boarding-house where he met Elsie Patrick." ;
    ex:occupation "Vicar" ;
    ex:knows :hiltonCubitt ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
