:heidegger a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Educator, ex:Victim ;
    ex:lastName "Heidegger" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Heidegger" ;
    skos:altLabel "Herr Heidegger" ;
    ex:description "The German master at the Priory School. Had been at the school for two years with the best references. A silent, morose man, not very popular with either masters or boys. An excellent cyclist. Room on the second floor at the farther end of the building. On the night of May 13th, saw Lord Saltire's flight from his window and pursued on bicycle, going partly dressed (shirt and socks on floor, wore shoes but no socks, open coat over nightshirt). Full-bearded with spectacles. Struck by Reuben Hayes with a metal-headed stick five miles from the school. Suffered a frightful blow to the head crushing part of his skull. Managed to continue riding before dying in gorse bushes on the moor." ;
    ex:nationality "German" ;
    ex:occupation "German master (language teacher)" ;
    ex:employedBy :priorySchoolInstitution ;
    ex:owns :heideggerBicycle ;
    ex:killedBy :reubenHayes ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :priorySchoolDoc .

:jamesWilder a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "James" ;
    ex:lastName "Wilder" ;
    ex:prefLabel "James Wilder" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. James Wilder" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Wilder" ;
    ex:description "Ostensibly the private secretary to the Duke of Holdernesse, but actually the Duke's illegitimate son by an earlier lover. Small, nervous, alert, with intelligent light-blue eyes and mobile features. Demure and courtly in manner but incisive and positive in tone. Rode a bicycle with a patched Dunlop tyre. Hated Lord Saltire and believed he himself should have been heir to the estates. Wanted to break the entail. Opened the Duke's letter to Lord Saltire and inserted a note using the Duchess's name to lure Arthur to Ragged Shaw. Bicycled to the school and told Arthur his mother was waiting on the moor. Arranged for Hayes to take Arthur by pony to the Fighting Cock Inn. After learning of Heidegger's death, made a complete voluntary confession to the Duke. Sent to Australia." ;
    ex:occupation "private secretary" ;
    ex:secretaryOf :dukeOfHoldernesse ;
    ex:childOf :dukeOfHoldernesse ;
    ex:childOf :wildersMotherUnnamed ;
    ex:owns :wilderBicycle ;
    ex:knows :reubenHayes ;
    ex:knows :lordSaltire ;
    ex:knows :thorneycroftHuxtable ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :priorySchoolDoc .

:lordLeverstoke a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Nobleman ;
    ex:prefLabel "Lord Leverstoke" ;
    ex:description "Mentioned as one of the distinguished patrons of the Priory School who entrusted his son to Dr. Huxtable." ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :priorySchoolDoc .

:lordSaltire a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Victim ;
    ex:firstName "Arthur" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Lord Saltire" ;
    skos:altLabel "Arthur" ;
    ex:description "Arthur, Lord Saltire. Ten-year-old son and only legitimate heir of the Duke of Holdernesse. A charming youth who settled in at the Priory School after arriving May 1st. Sympathies strongly with his mother the Duchess after his parents' separation. Disappeared from the Priory School on the night of May 13th. Dressed in black Eton jacket and dark grey trousers. Lured to Ragged Shaw by a note inserted by James Wilder into the Duke's letter, using the Duchess's name. Met Hayes at midnight with a led pony and taken to the Fighting Cock Inn. Confined in an upper room under the care of Mrs Hayes. Found safe and well but horrified by witnessing Heidegger's death." ;
    ex:age "10" ;
    ex:childOf :dukeOfHoldernesse ;
    ex:childOf :duchessOfHoldernesse ;
    ex:attendsSchool :priorySchoolInstitution ;
    ex:knows :jamesWilder ;
    ex:knows :heidegger ;
    ex:knows :reubenHayes ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :priorySchoolDoc .

:mrsHayes a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Mrs Hayes" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mrs. Hayes" ;
    ex:description "Wife of Reuben Hayes. Described as a kindly woman but entirely under the control of her brutal husband. Cared for Lord Saltire in an upper room at the Fighting Cock Inn during his confinement." ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :reubenHayes ;
    ex:livesAt :fightingCockInn ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :priorySchoolDoc .

:priorySchoolConstable a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:LawEnforcement ;
    ex:prefLabel "Country Constable at Priory School" ;
    ex:description "Unnamed country constable on duty from twelve to six at the first cross road on the east side of the main road past the Priory School on the night of Lord Saltire's disappearance. Positive that neither boy nor man passed that way unseen. Holmes spoke with him and found him a perfectly reliable person. Not named in the text." ;
    ex:occupation "country constable" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :priorySchoolDoc .

:redBullLandlady a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Red Bull Landlady" ;
    ex:description "Unnamed landlady of the Red Bull Inn on the main road west of the Priory School. Was ill on the night of May 13th and had sent to Mackleton for a doctor who did not arrive until morning. Not named in the text." ;
    ex:livesAt :redBullInn ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :priorySchoolDoc .

:reubenHayes a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Criminal ;
    ex:firstName "Reuben" ;
    ex:lastName "Hayes" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Reuben Hayes" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Reuben Hayes" ;
    ex:description "Landlord of the Fighting Cock Inn, about two miles from Holdernesse Hall park gate near the Chesterfield high road. Squat, dark, elderly man who smokes a black clay pipe. Cunning eyes, swarthy features. Former head coachman to the Duke of Holdernesse, sacked without a character on the word of a lying corn-chandler. Tenant of the Duke with James Wilder acting as agent. Used horses shod with medieval cloven-foot iron horseshoes from Holdernesse Hall museum to disguise tracks as cow prints on the moor. Waited at Ragged Shaw at midnight with a led pony, took Lord Saltire to the Fighting Cock. Struck Heidegger with a short metal-headed stick, killing him. Fled by dog-cart toward Chesterfield but arrested there at eleven o'clock at night on Holmes's information." ;
    ex:occupation "innkeeper, former head coachman" ;
    ex:landlordOf :fightingCockInn ;
    ex:formerlyEmployedBy :dukeOfHoldernesse ;
    ex:isMarriedTo :mrsHayes ;
    ex:killedWith :hayesStick ;
    ex:arrestedAt :chesterfield ;
    ex:knows :jamesWilder ;
    ex:knows :dukeOfHoldernesse ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :priorySchoolDoc .

:sirCathcartSoames a ex:FictionalPerson ;
    ex:prefLabel "Sir Cathcart Soames" ;
    ex:description "Mentioned as one of the distinguished patrons of the Priory School who entrusted his son to Dr. Huxtable." ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :priorySchoolDoc .

