:thorneycroftHuxtable a ex:FictionalPerson, ex:Doctor, ex:Educator ;
    ex:firstName "Thorneycroft" ;
    ex:lastName "Huxtable" ;
    ex:prefLabel "Thorneycroft Huxtable" ;
    skos:altLabel "Dr. Huxtable" ;
    skos:altLabel "Dr. Thorneycroft Huxtable" ;
    ex:description "MA, PhD. Founder and principal of the Priory School, a preparatory school near Mackleton in the North of England, in the Peak country. Author of 'Huxtable's Sidelights on Horace'. Large, pompous, dignified man with heavy white face seamed with lines of trouble, leaden pouches under closed eyes, loose mouth drooping at corners, rolling unshaven chins. Collapses from exhaustion upon arriving at Baker Street. Prostrated by the tragedy of Heidegger's death." ;
    ex:occupation "school principal, author" ;
    ex:founderOf :priorySchoolInstitution ;
    ex:authored :sidelightsOnHorace ;
