:136LittleRyderStreet a ex:FictionalLocation, ex:Residence ;
    ex:prefLabel "136 Little Ryder Street" ;
    ex:description "Nathan Garrideb's residence in London. A large, old-fashioned, Early Georgian edifice with a flat brick face broken by two deep bay windows on the ground floor. The house had a common stair with names painted in the hall indicating offices and private chambers. Previously occupied by Rodger Prescott under the alias Waldron. Contains a secret cellar beneath the ground floor accessed by a trapdoor under the carpet, which housed Prescott's counterfeiting press and equipment." ;
    ex:locatedIn :england ;
    ex:locatedIn :littleRyderStreet ;
    ex:locatedIn :london ;
