:13CaulfieldGardens a ex:Residence ;
    ex:prefLabel "13 Caulfield Gardens" ;
    ex:description "Hugo Oberstein's house in Kensington. A considerable house in a line of flat-faced, pillared, porticoed houses of the middle Victorian epoch. Back windows overlook the Underground railway line. Trains frequently halt beneath due to intersection with a larger railway. Crime scene where Cadogan West was killed and his body placed on a train roof. Blood marks found on window-sill and stairs. Holmes burglarized the house and found coded advertisements in a cash-box. Upper rooms unfurnished. Oberstein lived there with a single valet." ;
    ex:locatedIn :caulfieldGardens ;
