:16GodolphinStreet a ex:Residence ;
    ex:prefLabel "16 Godolphin Street" ;
    skos:altLabel "No. 16 Godolphin Street" ;
    ex:description "Eduardo Lucas's residence in Westminster. A small but select mansion, a high, dingy, narrow-chested house, prim, formal, and solid, an eighteenth-century house. The front room was luxuriously appointed with a magnificent trophy of weapons over the fireplace, a sumptuous writing-desk in the window, pictures, rugs and hangings suggesting taste luxurious to the verge of effeminacy. Beautiful old-fashioned wood-flooring in square blocks highly polished. Lucas was murdered in the front room. A small square drugget carpet lay in the centre of the room. A hinged wooden square beneath the drugget concealed a small black hiding cavity. The crime scene where the 'second stain' was discovered." ;
    ex:locatedIn :england ;
    ex:locatedIn :godolphinStreet ;
    ex:locatedIn :london ;
