:abbeyGrange a ex:ManorHouse ;
    ex:prefLabel "Abbey Grange" ;
    ex:description """A low, widespread house in Marsham, Kent, pillared in front after the fashion of Palladio. The central part is of great age and shrouded in ivy, with large windows showing modern changes and one wing entirely new. Approached through a noble park with an avenue between lines of ancient elms. Residence of Sir Eustace and Lady Brackenstall. The dining room is a very large and high chamber with carved oak ceiling, oaken panelling, deer's heads, and ancient weapons on the walls, with a high French window leading to the lawn. A pond in the park, frozen over with a hole for a solitary swan.""" ;
    ex:locatedIn :england ;
    ex:locatedIn :kent ;
    ex:locatedIn :marshamKent ;
    ex:locatedIn :unitedKingdom ;
    ex:inCity :marshamKent ;
