:barOfGold a ex:OpiumDen ;
    ex:prefLabel "The Bar of Gold" ;
    skos:altLabel "the Bar of Gold" ;
    ex:description "The Bar of Gold is an opium den in Upper Swandam Lane, east of London Bridge. Located between a slop-shop and a gin-shop, approached by steep steps leading down. A long, low room thick with brown opium smoke, terraced with wooden berths. Has a trap-door at the back near Paul Wharf that has been used to dispose of bodies. The upper floors contain a sitting-room and small bedroom with a window overlooking a narrow strip between the building and the wharf, covered at high tide. Neville St. Clair used the upper rooms as a changing space for his beggar disguise, paying the Lascar proprietor. Holmes used the den in disguise during his investigations." ;
    ex:locatedIn :england ;
