    ex:description "Ancestral home of the Baskerville family in Devonshire on the edge of Dartmoor. A large building with twin towers ancient and crenellated. Age-blackened ceiling with great oak rafters, stags' heads mounted on walls, coats-of-arms in stained glass windows. Dining room has minstrels' gallery. Features the Yew Alley (a walk between two lines of old yew hedge twelve feet high), a moor-gate at the far end leading to the moor, and an avenue of trees. Sir Charles died in the Yew Alley. Sir Henry inherited and planned renovations. Barrymore and Mrs. Barrymore served as butler and housekeeper." ;
