:becherHouse a ex:Residence ;
    ex:prefLabel "Dr. Becher's House" ;
    skos:altLabel "Stark's house" ;
    skos:altLabel "the house near Eyford" ;
    ex:description "A great, widespread, whitewashed building near Eyford, Berkshire, owned by Dr. Becher. Colonel Lysander Stark stayed here as an ostensible patient. The house contained the counterfeiting operation with a hydraulic press on an upper floor. It was an old, labyrinthine house with corridors, passages, narrow winding staircases, and little low doors with worn thresholds. No carpets or furniture above the ground floor; peeling plaster and damp. A waiting room contained German books and a harmonium. The house was destroyed by fire when Hatherley's oil lamp was crushed in the hydraulic press. Located about seven miles from Eyford Station (actually nearby, with the long carriage drive being a ruse)." ;
