    ex:prefLabel "Briarbrae" ;
    ex:description "Large detached house standing in extensive grounds within a few minutes' walk of Woking station. The Phelps family home. Contains a drawing-room, dining-room, bedrooms on the upper floor, and a ground-floor room used as Phelps's sickroom (formerly Joseph Harrison's bedroom, furnished partly as sitting-room and partly as bedroom). Has a side entrance for trades-people, a lawn, flower beds with moss-roses, rhododendron bushes, three fir-trees by the fence, and a wooden fence with rails skirting the road. The naval treaty was hidden under a floorboard covering a gas-pipe T-joint in the sickroom." ;
