:cheesemans a ex:FictionalLocation, ex:ManorHouse ;
    ex:prefLabel "Cheeseman's" ;
    ex:description "Cheeseman's is the isolated and ancient farmhouse in Lamberley, Sussex, where Robert Ferguson and his family live. It is a large, straggling building, very old in the centre and very new at the wings, with towering Tudor chimneys and a lichen-spotted, high-pitched roof of Horsham slabs. The doorsteps are worn into curves and the ancient tiles lining the porch are marked with the rebus of a cheese and a man after the original builder. Inside, the ceilings are corrugated with heavy oaken beams and the uneven floors sag into sharp curves. The house is named after the man who built it centuries ago." ;
    ex:locatedIn :england ;
    ex:locatedIn :lamberley ;
    ex:locatedIn :sussex ;
    ex:locatedIn :unitedKingdom ;
    ex:inCounty :sussex ;
    ex:inRegion :england ;
    ex:inCountry :unitedKingdom ;
