:fulworthBathingPool a ex:Location ;
    ex:prefLabel "Fulworth Bathing Pool" ;
    skos:altLabel "The bathing-pool" ;
    skos:altLabel "The lagoon" ;
    ex:description "A tidal lagoon and bathing pool at the base of chalk cliffs near Fulworth. The coast is entirely chalk cliffs descended by a single steep, slippery path of clay and marl. At the bottom lies a hundred yards of pebbles and shingle, with curves and hollows forming splendid swimming pools filled with each tide. Under the cliff the pool is four or five feet deep with pellucid green water. This is where Fitzroy McPherson was fatally stung by a Cyanea capillata jellyfish, where his dog later died, and where Ian Murdoch was also stung." ;
    ex:locatedIn :fulworth, :sussex, :england, :unitedKingdom ;
    ex:inCity :fulworth ;
    ex:inRegion :sussex ;
    ex:inCountry :unitedKingdom ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :lionsManeDoc .

:fulworthCliffPath a ex:Location ;
    ex:prefLabel "Fulworth Cliff Path" ;
    skos:altLabel "The cliff path" ;
    ex:description "A single, long, tortuous path descending the chalk cliffs to the beach near Fulworth. It is steep and slippery, with clay or soft marl mixed with the chalk. McPherson died at the top of this path after ascending from the beach, and Holmes examined footprints on it as part of his investigation." ;
    ex:locatedIn :fulworth, :sussex, :england, :unitedKingdom ;
    ex:inCity :fulworth ;
    ex:inRegion :sussex ;
    ex:inCountry :unitedKingdom ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :lionsManeDoc .

