:hurlstone a ex:ManorHouse ;
    ex:prefLabel "Hurlstone" ;
    skos:altLabel "Hurlstone Manor House" ;
    ex:description "The Musgrave family seat in western Sussex, perhaps the oldest inhabited building in the county. Built in the shape of an L — the long arm being the more modern portion and the shorter arm the ancient nucleus. Over the low, heavily-lintelled door in the centre of the old part is chiseled the date 1607, but experts agree the beams and stonework are much older. The enormously thick walls and tiny windows of the old part drove the family to build the new wing in the last century. The old wing is now used as a store-house and cellar. The corridors have walls decorated with trophies of old weapons. A splendid park with fine old timber surrounds the house. A rambling old place requiring a considerable staff of servants including eight maids, a cook, a butler, two footmen, and a boy, with separate garden and stable staff." ;
    ex:locatedIn :england ;
    ex:locatedIn :sussex ;
    ex:locatedIn :unitedKingdom ;
    ex:inCounty :sussex ;
    ex:inRegion :england ;
    ex:inCountry :unitedKingdom ;
    ex:constructionDate "1607 or earlier" ;
    ex:ownedBy :reginaldMusgrave ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :musgraveRitualDoc .

