:peterCareyCabin a ex:Building, ex:FictionalLocation ;
    ex:prefLabel "Peter Carey's cabin" ;
    skos:altLabel "the cabin" ;
    skos:altLabel "the outhouse" ;
    ex:description "A wooden outhouse built by Captain Peter Carey a few hundred yards from Woodman's Lee. A little single-roomed hut, sixteen feet by ten, with wooden walls, shingle roof, and small curtained windows on each side. Carey always called it 'the cabin' and slept there every night, keeping the key in his pocket. Furnished like a ship's captain's room with a bunk, sea-chest, maps and charts, a picture of the Sea Unicorn, and a line of log-books on a shelf. Scene of Peter Carey's murder." ;
    ex:locatedIn :woodmansLee, :forestRow, :sussex, :england, :unitedKingdom ;
