:reichenbachFalls a ex:FictionalLocation, ex:Waterfall ;
    ex:prefLabel "Reichenbach Falls" ;
    skos:altLabel "the fall of Reichenbach" ;
    skos:altLabel "the falls of Reichenbach" ;
    ex:description "A fearful waterfall about halfway up the hill from Meiringen, Switzerland. The torrent, swollen by melting snow, plunges into a tremendous abyss lined by glistening coal-black rock, narrowing into a creaming, boiling pit of incalculable depth. A path has been cut halfway round the fall to afford a complete view, ending abruptly at a three-foot-wide ledge with sheer wall on one side and sheer drop on the other. Site of the final confrontation between Sherlock Holmes and Professor Moriarty on May 4, 1891, where both fell into the abyss." ;
    ex:locatedIn :meiringen ;
    ex:locatedIn :switzerland ;
