    skos:altLabel "Ridling Thorpe" ;
    ex:description "The country seat of the Cubitt family in Norfolk for five centuries, one of the oldest and most honoured family homes in the county. An old house with brick and timber gables projecting from a grove of trees, with a porticoed front door, tennis lawn, black tool-house, and pedestalled sun-dial. Inside, the old hall is oak-panelled and high-windowed. The study is a small chamber lined with books on three sides with a writing-table facing a window overlooking the garden. A flower-bed extends beneath the study window. The house became a household word throughout England after the shooting tragedy." ;
    ex:locatedIn :eastAnglia ;
