:soamesBedroom a ex:Room ;
    ex:prefLabel "Soames's Bedroom" ;
    ex:description "Bedroom connected to Soames's sitting-room at the College of St. Luke's. Described as charming and old-fashioned. Has lattice-paned, lead-framework windows — three separate windows, one swinging on hinge and large enough to admit a man. Overlooks an angle of the courtyard, partly invisible from outside. Contains a curtain behind which clothes hang on pegs, a bed (too low to hide under), and a wardrobe (too shallow). Gilchrist hid here after being surprised by Soames's return." ;
