    ex:description "The ground floor sitting-room of Hilton Soames at the College of St. Luke's. Opens by a long, low, latticed window onto the ancient lichen-tinted court. Has a Gothic arched door leading to a worn stone staircase. Contains a central writing-table with a fine surface of red leather (new), and a side table near the window. Has double doors — a green baize one within and a heavy oak one without. Connected to Soames's bedroom." ;
    ex:locatedIn :collegeOfStLukes ;
