    ex:prefLabel "Stoke Moran Manor House" ;
    skos:altLabel "Roylott Manor" ;
    ex:description "The ancestral house of the Roylotts of Stoke Moran. A two-hundred-year-old building of grey lichen-blotched stone with a high central portion and two curving wings. One wing has broken windows and a partly caved-in roof. The right-hand block is inhabited. The bedrooms on the ground floor of the inhabited wing include Dr. Roylott's chamber (first), Julia/Helen's room (second), and Helen's original room (third), all opening onto the same corridor. A ventilator connects Roylott's room to the second bedroom, and a dummy bell-rope hangs beside the bed. The bed in the second room is clamped to the floor." ;
