:theHavenLewisham a ex:Residence ;
    ex:prefLabel "The Haven" ;
    skos:altLabel "Mr. Josiah Amberley's house" ;
    ex:description "The home of Josiah Amberley at Lewisham. An old house surrounded by a high sun-baked brick wall mottled with lichens and topped with moss, described as a little island of ancient culture amid monotonous brick streets. The garden was neglected and running to seed. Inside, the house was slatternly but contained a strong-room with an iron door and shutter that Amberley used as a gas chamber to murder his wife and Dr. Ernest. The smell of gas was concealed by painting the house with strong-smelling green paint. The bodies were hidden in a disused well concealed by a dog-kennel in the grounds." ;
    ex:locatedIn :lewisham ;
