    ex:description "Tuxbury Old Park, also called Tuxbury Old Hall, is a great wandering house standing in a considerable park near Bedford in Bedfordshire. It is five miles from anywhere and inaccessible. The house is of various ages and styles, starting on a half-timbered Elizabethan foundation and ending in a Victorian portico. Inside it is all panelling and tapestry and half-effaced old pictures. It is the residence of Colonel Emsworth and his family, and the location where Godfrey Emsworth was hidden in a detached lodge on the grounds." ;
