    ex:prefLabel "Vernon Lodge" ;
    ex:description """Baron Gruner's residence near Kingston. A large, beautiful house with a long winding drive with banks of rare shrubs opening into a great gravelled square adorned with statues. Built by a South African gold king during the great boom. A long, low house with turrets at the corners, architecturally nightmarish but imposing in size and solidity. Contains an outer study with Chinese crockery in a big glass cupboard between the windows, and an inner study behind the desk with a door leading to it, where papers and things are kept including the brown leather book in a pigeon-hole of the old bureau. Has a burglar alarm at night.""" ;
