:woodmansLee a ex:FictionalLocation, ex:ManorHouse ;
    ex:prefLabel "Woodman's Lee" ;
    ex:description "A small place near Forest Row in Sussex, bought by Captain Peter Carey after his retirement in 1884. A long, low stone house approached by a curving drive running through fields, set in a clearing upon the green slope of a hill amid the remains of widespread woods once part of the great Weald forest. Scene of the Black Peter tragedy." ;
    ex:locatedIn :forestRow, :sussex, :england, :unitedKingdom ;
