:yoxleyOldPlace a ex:ManorHouse ;
    ex:prefLabel "Yoxley Old Place" ;
    ex:description "Country house in Kent, seven miles from Chatham and three miles from the railway line. Taken some years ago by Professor Coram. Contains a study with a writing-table and locked bureau, connected by cocoanut-matted corridors to the Professor's bedroom. The bedroom has a secret hiding place behind a bookcase. Garden has a path from the gate (100 yards from London-Chatham road) to the back door with direct access to the study. Mortimer's cottage at the far end of the garden." ;
    ex:locatedIn :england ;
    ex:locatedIn :kent ;
    ex:locatedIn :unitedKingdom ;
    ex:inCounty :kent ;
    ex:inRegion :england ;
    ex:inCountry :unitedKingdom ;
    ex:ownedBy :professorCoram ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :goldenPinceNezDoc .

:yoxleyStudy a ex:Room ;
    ex:prefLabel "Professor Coram's Study" ;
    skos:altLabel "the study" ;
    ex:description "Scantily-furnished room in Yoxley Old Place where Willoughby Smith was murdered. Main article of furniture is a large writing-table with a fixed bureau consisting of a double column of drawers with a central small cupboard locked with a Chubb's key. Connected to the garden by a corridor lined with cocoanut matting and to Professor Coram's bedroom by another similar corridor. The study door leads to the passage." ;
    ex:locatedIn :england ;
    ex:locatedIn :kent ;
    ex:locatedIn :unitedKingdom ;
    ex:locatedIn :yoxleyOldPlace ;
    ex:inBuilding :yoxleyOldPlace ;
