:vitriolAttackOnGruner a ex:Crime ;
    ex:prefLabel "Vitriol Attack on Baron Gruner" ;
    ex:description """Kitty Winter throws vitriol (sulphuric acid) at Baron Gruner through the open window at Vernon Lodge during Holmes's burglary. A woman's arm shoots out from among the leaves and the Baron utters a horrible cry. The vitriol eats into his face everywhere, dripping from his ears and chin. One eye becomes white and glazed, the other red and inflamed. His features are horribly disfigured. Watson administers first aid with oil, cotton wadding, and a hypodermic of morphia.""" ;
    ex:hasParticipant :kittyWinter ;
    ex:hasParticipant :adelbertGruner ;
    ex:occurredAt :vernonLodge ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :illustriousClientDoc .

:visitToVioletDeMerville a ex:Meeting ;
    ex:prefLabel "Visit to Violet de Merville" ;
    ex:description """Holmes and Kitty Winter visit Violet de Merville at her father's residence at 104 Berkeley Square at half-past five, arranged through General de Merville. Holmes pleads with Violet about Baron Gruner's character but she dismisses everything as slander. Kitty Winter makes an impassioned appeal revealing she was Gruner's mistress, but Violet remains unmoved. The visit nearly turns violent when Kitty tries to attack Violet.""" ;
    ex:hasParticipant :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:hasParticipant :kittyWinter ;
    ex:hasParticipant :violetDeMerville ;
    ex:occurredAt :104BerkeleySquare ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :illustriousClientDoc .

:vonBorkEspionageCampaign a ex:Event, ex:Crime, ex:Conspiracy ;
    ex:prefLabel "Von Bork's Espionage Campaign" ;
    ex:description "A four-year intelligence operation conducted by Von Bork in England, gathering information on naval signals, harbour defences, aeroplanes, fortifications, and other military secrets while posing as an English sportsman and country squire. Employed multiple agents including Jack James, Hollis, and Steiner. Much of the intelligence was deliberately corrupted by Holmes working undercover as Altamont." ;
    ex:hasParticipant :vonBork ;
    ex:hasParticipant :jackJames ;
    ex:hasParticipant :hollisAgent ;
    ex:hasParticipant :steinerAgent ;
    ex:narrativeYear "1914" ;
    ex:occurredAt :vonBorkCountryHouse ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :hisLastBowDoc .

:voodooRitual a ex:Event, ex:VoodooRitual ;
    ex:prefLabel "Voodoo ritual at Wisteria Lodge" ;
    ex:description "A voodoo ritual performed by the mulatto cook at Wisteria Lodge before Garcia's assassination attempt. Involved sacrificing a white cock (torn to pieces alive), burning a lamb or kid (charred bones found), and spilling blood (pail of blood under sink). The cook's voodoo fetish was kept on the kitchen dresser." ;
    ex:hasParticipant :wisteriaLodgeCook ;
    ex:occurredAt :wisteriaLodge ;
    ex:narrativeYear "1892" ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :wisteriaLodgeDoc .

