:adelaideSouthamptonLine a ex:ShippingCompany ;
    ex:prefLabel "Adelaide-Southampton Line" ;
    skos:altLabel "Adelaide-Southampton company" ;
    ex:description """A shipping company operating steamers connecting South Australia with England. Their office is at the end of Pall Mall in London. Their largest and best boat is the Rock of Gibraltar. Captain Jack Croker was to command their new ship, the Bass Rock. Holmes visited their office to trace Mary Fraser's voyage and identify Croker. A second line of steamers also connects South Australia with England.""" ;
    ex:locatedIn :adelaideSouthamptonLineOffice ;
    ex:operates :rockOfGibraltar ;
    ex:operates :bassRock ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :abbeyGrangeDoc .

:admiralty a ex:NavalAuthority ;
    ex:prefLabel "The Admiralty" ;
    ex:description "British naval authority. Described as 'buzzing like an overturned bee-hive' over the theft of the Bruce-Partington plans. Sidney Johnson reported to the Admiralty on the technical viability of the stolen papers. In His Last Bow, the Admiralty got the alarm about Von Bork's espionage and changed every code, rendering his existing naval signals dossier out of date." ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :brucePartingtonPlansDoc ;
    dc:source :hisLastBowDoc .

