:britishCabinet a ex:GovernmentBody ;
    ex:prefLabel "The Cabinet" ;
    skos:altLabel "the British Cabinet" ;
    ex:description "The British Cabinet, the senior decision-making body of government. Awaited Holmes's final report with the utmost anxiety in the Bruce-Partington case. The Prime Minister was upset over the stolen plans. Each member was informed of the provocative diplomatic letter's existence the day before it was stolen from Trelawney Hope, with solemn warnings increasing the secrecy pledge at the Cabinet meeting. Lord Holdhurst is a cabinet minister. Phelps thought of his uncle and his colleagues in the Cabinet when contemplating the shame of the treaty theft." ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :brucePartingtonPlansDoc ;
    dc:source :navalTreatyDoc ;
    dc:source :secondStainDoc .

