:kuKluxKlan a ex:SecretSociety, ex:CriminalOrganization ;
    ex:prefLabel "Ku Klux Klan" ;
    skos:altLabel "K.K.K." ;
    skos:altLabel "KKK" ;
    ex:description "A terrible secret society formed by ex-Confederate soldiers in the Southern states after the American Civil War. According to the American Encyclopaedia consulted by Holmes, the name was derived from the fanciful resemblance to the sound produced by cocking a rifle. It rapidly formed local branches in different parts of the country, notably in Tennessee, Louisiana, the Carolinas, Georgia, and Florida. Its power was used for political purposes, principally for the terrorising of negro voters and the murdering and driving from the country of those who were opposed to its views. Its outrages were usually preceded by a warning sent to the marked man — a sprig of oak-leaves, melon seeds, or orange pips. The organisation flourished for some years despite the efforts of the United States government. Eventually in 1869 the movement rather suddenly collapsed, coinciding with Colonel Elias Openshaw's departure from America with their papers. In the story, the KKK's agents — led by Captain James Calhoun — pursue and murder three generations of the Openshaw family to recover the incriminating papers." ;
    ex:hasLeader :captainJamesCalhoun ;
    ex:hasMember :eliasOpenshaw, :captainJamesCalhoun, :hudsonKKK, :calhounMates ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :fiveOrangePipsDoc .

