:scotlandYard a ex:Organization ;
    ex:prefLabel "Scotland Yard" ;
    skos:altLabel "The Yard" ;
    ex:description "Scotland Yard is the headquarters of the Metropolitan Police in London. In The Sign of the Four, Athelney Jones represents Scotland Yard. Holmes directed Hatherley to Scotland Yard; Inspector Bradstreet of Scotland Yard accompanied them to Eyford. In the Blessington case, it was surmised at Scotland Yard that the three murderers perished aboard the steamer Norah Creina. Blessington/Sutton was well known at headquarters. Holmes picks up Inspector Gregson here before proceeding to Beckenham for the rescue at The Myrtles. In the Naval Treaty case, Forbes worked here as the detective on the case. Mrs. Tangey was brought here and searched by a female searcher. Holmes and Watson visited Forbes here after lunch. Referenced in The Adventure of the Norwood Builder. Referenced in the context of Holmes's battered appearance making him a fitting object of a Scotland Yard investigation. Scotland Yard investigates the murder of Charles Augustus Milverton at Appledore Towers. Lestrade visits Holmes to request assistance but Holmes refuses. Holmes drove to Scotland Yard after visiting the Adelaide-Southampton line office, but sat in his cab thinking rather than entering. Inspector Gregson of Scotland Yard participates in the Wisteria Lodge investigation. Lestrade referred to as 'our old friend Lestrade, of Scotland Yard' in the Bruce-Partington plans case. In the Red Circle case, Gregson takes Emilia Lucca to see the chief at Scotland Yard. In His Last Bow, Scotland Yard is the destination where Holmes and Watson take the captured German spy Von Bork. Holmes threatens to go to Scotland Yard when confronting Isadora Klein. Holmes visited to consult rogues' portrait gallery. CID men celebrated discovery of Prescott's counterfeiting outfit. Referenced by Sergeant Coventry who says he would rather have Holmes than Scotland Yard on the case. In the Mazarin Stone case, Watson is sent to Scotland Yard with a note for Youghal of the C.I.D. to bring police for the arrest of Count Sylvius and Sam Merton. Holmes commended Von Herder's air-gun to the Scotland Yard Museum. Overton visited Scotland Yard before coming to Holmes; Inspector Hopkins there referred him to Holmes." ;
    ex:hasMember :peterJones ;
    ex:hasMember :lestrade ;
    ex:inCity :london ;
    ex:locatedIn :london ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
