:deduction_crookedMan_holmes_06 a ex:Deduction ;
    ex:prefLabel "Holmes Deduces a Third Person Entered the Morning-Room" ;
    ex:description "Analyzing the mystery of the missing door-key at Lachine, Holmes applies eliminative logic to conclude that an unknown third party was present." ;
    ex:deductionSequence 6 ;
    ex:deductionSummary "A third person must have entered the morning-room and taken the key, since neither Colonel Barclay nor his wife could have removed it." ;
    ex:deductionReasoning "The door-key had vanished from the locked room. A thorough search found it neither on Mrs. Barclay's person, nor on the Colonel's body, nor anywhere in the room. Since neither occupant could have taken it, a third person must have entered the room and carried the key away." ;
    ex:deductionOutcome "correct" ;
