:deduction_crookedMan_holmes_11 a ex:Deduction ;
    ex:prefLabel "Holmes Deduces the Animal Is Long-Bodied With Short Legs" ;
    ex:description "Holmes reconstructs the animal's physical dimensions from its footprints, attempting to identify the species." ;
    ex:deductionSequence 11 ;
    ex:deductionSummary "The animal is approximately two feet long with a long body and very short legs, probably of the weasel or stoat family." ;
    ex:deductionReasoning "Standing prints showed fifteen inches from fore-foot to hind, suggesting at least two feet in total length including neck and head. Yet the stride was only about three inches, indicating very short legs relative to the long body. The creature could also climb curtains. Holmes concluded it was probably of the weasel and stoat tribe, though larger than any he had seen." ;
    ex:deductionOutcome "correct" ;
    ex:deducedBy :sherlockHolmes ;
