:deduction_dancingMen_holmes_20 a ex:Deduction ;
    ex:prefLabel "Holmes Deduces Slaney Will Come When Summoned by Dancing Men" ;
    ex:description "Holmes writes a note to Slaney using the dancing men cipher, confident that Slaney will come to Ridling Thorpe Manor believing it was written by Elsie." ;
    ex:deductionSequence 20 ;
    ex:deductionSummary "Slaney will come to the Manor when he receives a note written in the dancing men cipher, believing it is from Elsie." ;
    ex:deductionReasoning "Holmes was convinced that a message written in the dancing men cipher would be an invitation Slaney could not refuse, since Slaney could never imagine it could come from anyone but Elsie — no one outside the Joint knew the secret of the dancing men. Holmes used this knowledge to lure Slaney into a trap." ;
    ex:deductionOutcome "correct" ;
