:deduction_engineersThumb_holmes_06 a ex:Deduction ;
    ex:prefLabel "Holmes Deduces the Woman and Englishman Carried Hatherley to Safety" ;
    ex:description "After the fire, the soft mould in the garden reveals footprints that allow Holmes to reconstruct how Hatherley was moved from the garden to the roadside where he regained consciousness." ;
    ex:deductionSequence 6 ;
    ex:deductionSummary "The silent Englishman Ferguson, being less murderous than Stark, assisted the woman Elise in carrying the unconscious Hatherley out of the garden to safety near the road." ;
    ex:deductionReasoning "Holmes read the footprints in the soft mould, which showed Hatherley had been carried by two persons — one with remarkably small feet and the other with unusually large ones. The small feet belonged to the woman and the large to the Englishman, indicating Ferguson helped Elise bear the unconscious engineer away from danger." ;
    ex:deductionOutcome "correct" ;
    ex:deducedBy :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:deductionSubject :victorHatherley ;
    ex:deductionSubject :mrFerguson ;
    ex:deductionSubject :elise ;
