    dc:source :engineersThumbDoc .

:deduction_engineersThumb_watson_01 a ex:Deduction ;
    ex:prefLabel "Watson's Theory: Stark Spared Hatherley Because the Woman Softened Him" ;
    ex:description "On the train to Eyford, Watson suggests an explanation for why the criminals did not kill Hatherley after finding him unconscious in the garden." ;
    ex:deductionSequence 1 ;
    ex:deductionSummary "The villain Stark was softened by the woman Elise's entreaties, which is why they spared the unconscious Hatherley." ;
    ex:deductionReasoning "Watson could not understand why the criminals would spare Hatherley when they found him lying unconscious in the garden, and suggested that perhaps the woman's pleading softened the villain's resolve to kill him." ;
    ex:deductionOutcome "incorrect" ;
