:deduction_finalProblem_professormoriarty_01 a ex:Deduction ;
    ex:prefLabel "Moriarty Deduces Holmes Is Concealing a Firearm" ;
    ex:description "During their confrontation at 221B Baker Street, Moriarty immediately detects that Holmes has slipped a revolver into his dressing-gown pocket and is covering him through the cloth." ;
    ex:deductionSequence 1 ;
    ex:deductionSummary "Holmes is fingering a loaded firearm concealed in the pocket of his dressing-gown." ;
    ex:deductionReasoning "Moriarty observed Holmes's hand movement and the positioning within his dressing-gown pocket, deducing from these physical cues that Holmes had armed himself upon Moriarty's entrance. He warned Holmes that it was a dangerous habit to finger loaded firearms in one's pocket." ;
    ex:deductionOutcome "correct" ;
    ex:deducedBy :professorMoriarty ;
