:deduction_greekInterpreter_watson_01 a ex:Deduction ;
    ex:prefLabel "Watson's Theory: Latimer Abducted Sophy and Her Brother Came to Interfere" ;
    ex:description "On the walk home from the Diogenes Club, Holmes invites Watson to share his theory of the case. Watson constructs a comprehensive explanation of the Kratides affair." ;
    ex:deductionSequence 1 ;
    ex:deductionSummary "Sophy was persuaded to elope with Latimer; her brother Paul came from Greece to interfere and was seized; the captors are forcing him to sign over the family property; they needed an interpreter to negotiate with their prisoner." ;
    ex:deductionReasoning "Watson reasoned that Sophy had come to England on a visit and Harold Latimer persuaded her to fly with him. The male prisoner must be her brother, who came from Greece to intervene. Latimer and his associate seized the brother and used violence to make him sign papers transferring the girl's fortune. They required an interpreter because the brother spoke only Greek, and had previously used a different interpreter before engaging Melas." ;
    ex:deductionOutcome "correct" ;
    ex:deducedBy :johnWatson ;
    ex:deductionSubject :sophyKratides ;
    ex:deductionSubject :paulKratides ;
    ex:deductionSubject :haroldLatimer ;
    ex:deductionBasedOn :interrogationOfKratides ;
    ex:confirmedBy :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :greekInterpreterDoc .

:deduction_hisLastBow_holmes_01 a ex:Deduction ;
    ex:prefLabel "Holmes Identifies and Exposes Von Bork's Spy Network" ;
    ex:description "Over the course of his two-year undercover mission as Altamont, Holmes systematically identified each of Von Bork's agents and arranged for their arrest, resulting in five agents being imprisoned while Von Bork remained unaware of the source of his losses." ;
    ex:deductionSequence 1 ;
    ex:deductionSummary "Holmes identified and exposed Von Bork's agents one by one over two years, leading to five arrests." ;
    ex:deductionReasoning "Working undercover within Von Bork's spy ring, Holmes observed the agents' identities, methods, and activities from the inside. He watched them and, in his own words, 'picked them as they ripened,' passing intelligence to the British authorities who arrested them at opportune moments." ;
    ex:deductionOutcome "correct" ;
    ex:deducedBy :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:deductionSubject :vonBork ;
    ex:deductionSubject :vonBorkEspionageCampaign ;
    ex:deductionBasedOn :holmesCounterEspionageMission ;
    ex:confirmedBy :captureOfVonBork ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :hisLastBowDoc .

:deduction_hisLastBow_holmes_02 a ex:Deduction ;
    ex:prefLabel "Holmes Recognizes Von Herling's Car on the Road" ;
    ex:description "As Holmes and Watson drove toward Von Bork's house in their Ford, Baron Von Herling's large Benz car nearly passed over them going in the opposite direction. Holmes later confirmed to Martha that he knew the secretary had been present because his car had passed theirs." ;
    ex:deductionSequence 2 ;
    ex:deductionSummary "Holmes identified Baron Von Herling's departing car as it passed his own vehicle on the village road." ;
    ex:deductionReasoning "Holmes recognized the distinctive large Benz motorcar belonging to Baron Von Herling as it swung round the village street and nearly collided with their small Ford, confirming the secretary's presence at Von Bork's house and his subsequent departure." ;
    ex:deductionOutcome "correct" ;
    ex:deducedBy :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:deductionSubject :baronVonHerling ;
    ex:confirmedBy :marthaHisLastBow ;
    ex:memberOfOntology ex:SherlockOntology ;
    dc:source :hisLastBowDoc .

:deduction_hisLastBow_holmes_03 a ex:Deduction ;
    ex:prefLabel "Holmes Deduces the Coast Is Clear from Martha's Signal" ;
    ex:description "After arriving near Von Bork's house, Holmes waited for Martha's prearranged signal before approaching. When her lamp went out, Holmes knew Von Herling had departed and Von Bork was alone." ;
    ex:deductionSequence 3 ;
    ex:deductionSummary "Holmes deduced that Von Bork was alone and it was safe to approach when Martha extinguished her lamp." ;
    ex:deductionReasoning "Holmes had arranged a signal system with Martha, his planted housekeeper. When Martha's lamp in the window went out, it indicated that Baron Von Herling had left and Von Bork was alone in the house, making it safe to proceed with the operation." ;
    ex:deductionOutcome "correct" ;
    ex:deducedBy :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:deductionSubject :vonBork ;
