:deduction_mazarinStone_holmes_03 a ex:Deduction ;
    ex:prefLabel "Holmes Traces the Air-Gun to Straubenzee's Workshop" ;
    ex:description "Holmes reveals that he followed Count Sylvius to Straubenzee's workshop in the Minories, where he determined that Straubenzee manufactured the air-gun intended to assassinate Holmes through the window of 221B Baker Street." ;
    ex:deductionSequence 3 ;
    ex:deductionSummary "Straubenzee made the air-gun that Sylvius intends to use to shoot Holmes through his window." ;
    ex:deductionReasoning "While shadowing Sylvius in disguise, Holmes followed him to old Straubenzee's workshop in the Minories, identifying it as the source of the air-gun. Holmes deduced the weapon was aimed at the window of 221B, which prompted him to place the wax dummy as a decoy target." ;
    ex:deductionOutcome "correct" ;
    ex:deducedBy :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:deductionSubject :straubenzee ;
