:deduction_missingThreeQuarter_holmes_02 a ex:Deduction ;
    ex:prefLabel "Holmes Interprets Staunton's Telegram as a Plea for Help" ;
    ex:description "At Bentley's Hotel, Holmes recovers the tail end of a telegram Staunton dispatched by reading the impression left on a blotting pad, and interprets its meaning." ;
    ex:deductionSequence 2 ;
    ex:deductionSummary "Staunton's telegram proves he and another person faced a formidable danger and sought protection from a third party." ;
    ex:deductionReasoning "Holmes recovered the words 'Stand by us for God's sake!' from the blotting-pad impression. He reasoned that 'us' indicated another person was involved — likely the pale-faced bearded man who delivered the note — and that both Staunton and this man were seeking help from a third party against some pressing danger." ;
    ex:deductionOutcome "correct" ;
    ex:deducedBy :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:deductionSubject :godfreyStaunton ;
