:deduction_redHeadedLeague_watson_01 a ex:Deduction ;
    ex:prefLabel "Watson Observes Wilson Is a Commonplace British Tradesman" ;
    ex:description "While Wilson searches for the newspaper advertisement, Watson attempts to read his appearance in the manner of Holmes, endeavouring to deduce facts about the visitor from his dress and bearing." ;
    ex:deductionSequence 1 ;
    ex:deductionSummary "Wilson is an average commonplace British tradesman, obese, pompous, and slow, with nothing remarkable about him save his blazing red hair." ;
    ex:deductionReasoning "Watson observed Wilson's baggy grey shepherd's check trousers, not over-clean black frock-coat, drab waistcoat with heavy brassy Albert chain, frayed top-hat, and faded brown overcoat, concluding that the man bore every mark of being an ordinary tradesman." ;
    ex:deductionOutcome "correct" ;
    ex:deducedBy :johnWatson ;
    ex:deductionSubject :jabezWilson ;
