:deduction_reigateSquires_inspectorforrester_01 a ex:Deduction ;
    ex:prefLabel "Forrester's Theory: William Was in League With the Thief" ;
    ex:description "After presenting the torn paper fragment found in the dead man's hand, Inspector Forrester offers his theory about the coachman's possible involvement in the burglary." ;
    ex:deductionSequence 1 ;
    ex:deductionSummary "William Kirwan may have been in league with the burglar, with the note representing an appointment between accomplices who then fell out." ;
    ex:deductionReasoning "The fragment appeared to set an appointment for the exact time of William's death. Forrester theorized that despite William's honest reputation, he may have arranged to meet the thief, helped him break in, and then the two fell out, leading to the shooting." ;
    ex:deductionOutcome "incorrect" ;
    ex:deducedBy :inspectorForrester ;
