:deduction_scarlet_holmes_08 a ex:Deduction ;
    ex:prefLabel "Holmes Deduces a Private Wrong Involving a Woman" ;
    ex:description "From the absence of robbery, the deliberate lingering at the scene, and the wedding ring, Holmes concludes the murder was motivated by a private grievance connected to a woman." ;
    ex:deductionSequence 8 ;
    ex:deductionSummary "The murder was motivated by a private wrong involving a woman, not politics or robbery" ;
    ex:deductionReasoning "Nothing was stolen, the killer lingered deliberately at the scene unlike a political assassin who would flee, and the wedding ring confirmed the crime was connected to a dead or absent woman, prompting Holmes to telegraph Cleveland about Drebber's romantic history." ;
    ex:deductionOutcome "correct" ;
    ex:deducedBy :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:deductionSubject :drebberMurder ;
