    ex:deductionSequence 9 ;
    ex:deductionSummary "The killer was the cabman himself" ;
    ex:deductionReasoning "The cab driver must have been inside the house since the horse wandered unattended, no sane murderer would act in front of a witness, and driving a cab was the ideal way to shadow someone through London, making the driver and the killer the same person." ;
    ex:deductionOutcome "correct" ;
    ex:deducedBy :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:deductionSubject :jeffersonHope ;
