:deduction_threeGarridebs_holmes_06 a ex:Deduction ;
    ex:prefLabel "Holmes Identifies John Garrideb as Killer Evans" ;
    ex:description "After visiting Scotland Yard and consulting their records, Holmes identifies the man calling himself John Garrideb as a dangerous American criminal known as Killer Evans." ;
    ex:deductionSequence 6 ;
    ex:deductionSummary "John Garrideb, Counsellor at Law, is actually James Winter, alias Morecroft, alias Killer Evans — a convicted murderer and dangerous criminal from Chicago." ;
    ex:deductionReasoning "Holmes visited Lestrade at Scotland Yard and searched their criminal records for the American's description. He found the man's chubby face in the rogues' portrait gallery, identified as James Winter, alias Morecroft, alias Killer Evans — aged forty-four, native of Chicago, known to have shot three men in the States, and the killer of Rodger Prescott, a famous forger and coiner." ;
    ex:deductionOutcome "correct" ;
    ex:deducedBy :sherlockHolmes ;
