:deduction_threeGarridebs_holmes_07 a ex:Deduction ;
    ex:prefLabel "Holmes Deduces Waldron Was Rodger Prescott" ;
    ex:description "After visiting the house agent Holloway and Steele, Holmes connects the previous tenant of Nathan Garrideb's flat with the murdered counterfeiter Rodger Prescott." ;
    ex:deductionSequence 7 ;
    ex:deductionSummary "The previous tenant of 136 Little Ryder Street, known as Waldron, was actually Rodger Prescott, the American counterfeiter whom Killer Evans shot and killed." ;
    ex:deductionReasoning "Holmes learned from the house agent that the previous tenant was a gentleman named Waldron who had suddenly vanished, described as a tall, bearded man with very dark features. Scotland Yard's records described Prescott, the man Evans killed, as a tall, dark man with a beard. Holmes connected the matching physical descriptions and Waldron's sudden disappearance with Prescott's death to conclude they were the same person." ;
    ex:deductionOutcome "correct" ;
