:deduction_threeGarridebs_holmes_08 a ex:Deduction ;
    ex:prefLabel "Holmes Deduces Evans Seeks Prescott's Hidden Criminal Equipment" ;
    ex:description "While waiting in ambush at Nathan Garrideb's flat, Holmes explains to Watson his theory about what Evans is after in the rooms formerly occupied by Prescott." ;
    ex:deductionSequence 8 ;
    ex:deductionSummary "Evans is seeking something connected to Prescott's criminal activities that is hidden within the rooms, likely counterfeiting equipment or proceeds." ;
    ex:deductionReasoning "Holmes initially considered that Nathan Garrideb's collection might contain something valuable enough to attract a big criminal, but rejected this because Prescott's prior occupation of the rooms pointed to a deeper reason. Since Evans killed Prescott and was the only person who knew where Prescott manufactured his counterfeits, Holmes deduced that a guilty secret connected to the forgery operation was hidden in the room." ;
    ex:deductionOutcome "correct" ;
