    ex:prefLabel "Watson Notices American Spelling in the Advertisement" ;
    ex:description "When Holmes asks Watson if he noticed anything curious about the Howard Garrideb advertisement, Watson identifies the misspelling of 'plough' as a significant clue." ;
    ex:deductionSequence 1 ;
    ex:deductionSummary "The Howard Garrideb advertisement contains the American spelling of 'plough,' indicating it was not written by an English firm." ;
    ex:deductionReasoning "Watson observed that the word 'plough' was misspelled in the advertisement purportedly from an English agricultural machinery firm in Birmingham. Holmes confirmed this was American rather than bad English, validating Watson's observation as a genuine clue to the advertisement's true origin." ;
