:deduction_threeStudents_holmes_01 a ex:Deduction ;
    ex:prefLabel "Holmes Deduces the Sequential Order of Displaced Proof Pages" ;
    ex:description "When Soames describes finding the proof slips displaced, Holmes immediately infers their order before being told, demonstrating his understanding of how a copier would work through the pages." ;
    ex:deductionSequence 1 ;
    ex:deductionSummary "The proof pages were displaced in sequential order: the first page on the floor, the second at the window table, and the third unmoved where Soames left it." ;
    ex:deductionReasoning "A person copying the proofs would work through them in order. The first sheet, once copied, would be set aside carelessly. The second would be at the copying location by the window. The third would remain untouched if the copier was interrupted before reaching it." ;
    ex:deductionOutcome "correct" ;
    ex:deducedBy :sherlockHolmes ;
    ex:deductionSubject :fortescueExamPaper ;
    ex:confirmedBy :gilchristsConfession ;
